text: I have been coming here for several years, and I love this place. Tina and Jenny are the best. Always clean and reasonably priced.

Just ordered the yellow eyed snapper special that's crusted in Parmesan.  It was good on its own but felt it needed sauce.  Chef George was cool enough to give me three of their sauces to try which were all good but not the right fit. Then, he brought out the volcano red sauce and man that was a perfect pair!! Coming back here again soon.  Tiffany was our waitress and she was fast and very friendly.

I was visiting my best friends sister on music row and she recommended Edgehill Cafe to us because we were looking to grab a quick bite to eat. I walked in around 10:30 and walked up to the counter and was told the kitchen was closed. Talk about feeling bummed out after looking over their tasty menu options. We were standing outside for about 10 minutes and got called back in because the kitchen was some how opening. I am not sure what happened, but I am sure glad I was able to order my Belgian waffle. I added bananas and chocolate chips for a .50 cent up charge and it took the waffle to the next level. The waffle is made with a cinnamon vanilla buckwheat batter and topped with walnuts and syrup. The waffle also comes with a side and I went with the bacon of course. It was nice thick and crispy. You can tell they only use the freshest of ingredients. The coffee mugs are a pretty decent size which allowed me to enjoy more of my peach white tea. 

What I thought made this cafe unique was that it served beer. This isn't your typical coffee shop. They have something for everyone. You also order at the counter and they will bring the food out to you when its ready. The interior was very modern chic. I loved the tufted benches and light fixture in the larger dining area. They also have a really neat patio and lots of tables inside. I would recommend this place if you are looking to grab a quick breakfast.

I've enjoyed delicious lunches from Three Carrots' City Market stand for years and was excited to try supper at their new sit-down restaurant. We loved the  poutine as an appetizer. The BBQ seitan was great. I enjoyed the fettuccine Alfredo--it had a strong nutmeg flavor that was an unexpected but festive touch for the holiday season. They have a good selection of Indiana beer. It's great to have a vegan restaurant downtown, and it's a good place to try if you're skeptical of or intimidated by vegetarian food, since they have some traditional comfort foods. The place was busy on a Saturday night, but we were seated quickly and the staff was friendly and attentive.

I've never had an issue with this location until now. I went through the drive thru and ordered 3 entrees. After getting home my husband and I began to chow down on our food. I always look at my food before each bite and I'm glad I do otherwise I would never have noticed the long nasty hair wrapped in my food. It is definitely not my hair because I have black hair. The hair in my food was light brown. Let's just say this ruined my appetite and I will never come back here again! Disgusting!

Such a St. Pete gem! Delicious pastries, great selection of wines, fresh pasta, pizza, and sandwiches. It's always packed but the wait isn't usually long. They are a well oiled machine at Mazzaro's. If you experience a long wait it's definitely worth the wait.  

Don't let the sensory overload get you down, take your time, you won't regret it!

This is a fantastic place to dine. The food is absolutely delicious. We ate the bruschetta sampler as our appetizer. I would return just to eat that with a salad! I ordered the Gorgonzola encrusted medallions and my boyfriend had the sea bass. We couldn't stop talking about how delicious our food was. Our server was first class. She knew her menu and her service was spot on!

The Alaskan crab is way overpriced for it's size/taste and preparation. Oh and it's cold. You eat against a wall and the coleslaw is not fresh. 
Overall cheap restaurant, very touristy and overpriced, not recommended.
Best food I've had in a long time. This place should have 5 stars hands down. Highly recommend anyone that wants to try really unique and flavorful dishes.
Filipino breakfast was delish! Owner Loida was awesome & super friendly! My family & I will definitely come back!
Finally, finally a "real pizzeria"!!! Food is fresh! And absolutely delicious.  Service is great- so friendly and helpful. What a find!

This Publix is beautiful! Remodeling about 1 year ago and I love the set-up. It's a lot different from how it used to look. They even added a drive-thru for the pharmacy. All the mangers and staff are extremely kind and courteous.

Buyer Beware: Please be cautiously aware when placing an order that you are trying to get the advertised discount for.  They cited a BOGOF offer so I order two pizzas that I told the lady I wanted to use the BOGO deal on.  I then ordered cheese bread and regular breadsticks afterwards.  When I picked up the order and reviewed the receipt, I noticed that they had taken off the cheapest thing on the order (the breadsticks). I called them back and they would not refund the difference and stated that the discount applied to the cheapest thing on the order.  They were not willing to compromise at all so therefore please be aware of their business practices before ordering.

This might be my favorite Indian place in Bucks County! The service is great, the food incredible and dietary restrictions are met by everyone at the table. (Gluten free, dairy free and vegan) all at the same table. The recommendations are incredible and never disappoint!

Always have had a great time here! Exceptional selection of beer, great bartenders! And Ezra know how to light the place up!!! come join us Thursdays for drinking games and prizes!!! Make this a stop on your beer tour of Boise!!

This is a beautiful restaurant. We dined with a large group and it was not good. Food was served cold and 2 hours after being seated. The City Park salad was very good and served a little more promptly than the main dish. The redfish was below average. Service was slow and with a poor attitude.  It is off our list.

Growing up here in the Bay Area I don't seem to take advantage of the nice long sidewalks. Today we started at the Vinoy and followed the side walk to the other end of the bay. Leading to this park.  Such a cute little playground on the water, lots of enclosed play space and with the airport right next to the park. Kids get up close to a plane taking off. Great local park with things to do for all ages.

Took an hour and a half for the oil change, never waited this long. Then somehow the $50 price became 80$ because my car took more oil. Never was I asked if I wanted the extra oil. I could have bought that myself. And that still hardly explains how it suddenly costs $30 more. And that's before tax and with the coupon. $100 full price for an oil change? That's a joke. People were nice though, not their fault pep boys robs you.

The Logan Inn was a beautiful setting in New Hope, and the food was good, but our service was disappointing.  We were seated quickly as the restaurant was not busy.  A table directly adjacent to us had their water glasses filled as soon as they sat down.  We waited for about 5 minutes before anyone acknowledged our presence, and the waiter appeared disinterested in helping us when he finally came.  We had to ask for water and repeatedly ask for everything else, and generally received poor service.  The food was good, nothing special for the price and upscale setting.  I see that others had excellent service experience, including everyone around us that night with different servers.

We have had nothing but excellent experiences with TKO.  We used them for our wedding and for other family parties and have found them to be very accommodating and versatile.  They can match the personality of their DJ's to your needs.  In the words of the great Levar Burton "But Don't take my word for it". Try em out!

Lovely decor, very friendly and helpful staff and five star food. Fried oysters were amazing, the sushi was the best I have had in the phili area. The dumplings were also superb. They are updating their liquor list so the whiskeys were not listed BUT you can still order whatever you want. I will be back I ate this on Saturday and am already craving it again! I just wish they had fried rice but honestly everything was amazing

Can't beat 50 cent wings during Saints' games - every flavor is delicious! Who Dat!

Great environment, delicious drinks, and perfect football food. Try the Kentucky Sunrise - bourbon, maple syrup, red wine - sounds unusual but tastes better than you can imagine.

Love mellow mushroom!

Not just for breakfast anymore!
We are locals and would go for breakfast now and then, but did not care for lunch or dinner.
We heard it was under new management and decided to give it a try for dinner.
I will admit, we are food snobs. The food was unbelievable. We had chicken wings for an appetizer  ( recommended by a friend) chowder, mushroom Risotto and a special Cajun dish. Everything was delicious.
I hope they can hang on to that chef. 
Our server, Gabby was delightful and went the extra mile.
We will definitely be back.

We have been back several times and the food just gets better and better. Our new 'go to'

Great happy hour food and bartenders. Doesn't get too busy on the weekdays or during Saturday brunch. 
Would only change the pickle spears that comes with the chicken sandwiches. They taste like they were brined in just salt.
It's a coffee shop, not a breakfast place.  Sorry, but Yelp got it wrong with this one.

This place is literally heaven , i lived in NY and still visit every few months , I've tried so Many thai food places there , nothing like this place , what ever you get , you genuinely can't go wrong, and then the owner and his wife are just Strolling in the store with there smiling faces , i tell everyone about this place and i always will  , can't imagine my life without there chicken cashew. GOOD GOD it's hella awesome

My wife and I went there for dinner last night. It is a bit pricey, but the variety is amazing. Now to critique the food.  things that I would say were exceptional; the Dungeness crab legs and the frog legs. I have never seen a bigger frog leg in a restaurant, much less a buffet. The boiled seafood with the exception of the Dungeness were over-spiced with crab boil to the point that they were not good. Most of the fried food was too salty.  For $40 per person I wouldn't return very often.

With a reservation from start to finish was over 75 minutes for an acrylic fill in.  The polish was tacky and never dried. I ruined my manicure on the way home.  I had to take it off when I got home and paint them again. Maybe it was old polish but that is not what I paid for
It's like walking into another time and place, super magical.

Came in to try this place out for the first time on a Saturday night. The bar area was packed so I had to sit in the dining area. They have 120 taps of beer! 

I tried the broiled lump crab cakes and they were delicious! 

Jordan was our server and she was knowledgeable and helped us through the menu.

I'm not a big fan of Mac n cheese but decided to try the buffalo Mac because the only place I have had Mac and cheese is at the District Tap so I wanted to compare and I think honestly the Mac n cheese at the District Tap tastes better.

Really enjoyed the tour.  Discovered mufalettas at the Napolean House that were outstanding. We later went back for more. Tour guide was very nice, but didn't seem too popular at a couple of the okaces. Groupon pricing is the only way to go.

India Palace apparently is under new management.  They sent out a mailer advising they had renovated the place and were serving a complementary buffet from 11am-4pm on Saturday December 16th, 2017.  We arrived at 3:00pm to find they were not honoring their advertisement and had locked the doors to the restaurant to ensure no one could get in.   On top of that they even had a policeman outside telling people they couldn't get in.   I called the restaurant asking what was going on.  They gave me the owners phone number and said the owner had ordered the doors closed early.  I called the  owner and left a message.  The owner responded via a text message telling me I shouldn't be contacting him and to basically leave him alone.  

There are other Indian restaurants in this city.   This "new" India Palace won't be getting my business again.   They won't have to lock the doors to keep me away.  I'll go somewhere else.

Great donuts in the Garden district. DD was a block from our Airbnb and we went there 2 times! So good and I love the atmosphere. Casual and local. I'm sure there were lots of visitors like us but it didn't feel like a touristy place. 

I ordered the cinnamon donut.. perfection!

Booked a 90 deep tissue massage with a male therapist. Unfortunately when I showed up, they only had a female. I specifically requested a male and friends with me during the booking recall me asking for one. Very disappointed as I was looking forward to this escape. 

I get 2-3 massages a month at home and I know exactly what style and technique I need. When willing to pay over $150 a session I could not settle for a different session.

The food is more expensive, portions were smaller, and took longer to come out than the Camellia Grill which is next door. The fried potatoes for brunch were about the size of the palm of my hand and were frozen and not even fresh cut. The Avocado Chicken sandwich that my girlfriend had, the chicken was about the width of a French fry, was unseasoned, bland, and the bread was hard and dry. Don't waste your money unless you want bottomless mimosas solely and do not order food, which of course, no one would do. The Camellia Grill is going to run this place out of business and rightfully so
I love this gym!  Been here for a few years and I always feel welcome.  Its clean and the staff is friendly. Only wish they had some other equipment like a standing calf raise machine.

Burger Republic is a good choice for a casual meal! Their burgers aren't my favorite in Nashville, but they're still certainly worth ordering. You can't leave without ordering a milkshake though! That's where BR really shines.

Went to this location last Thursday as I was in the neighborhood working.  My first visit to this Taco Bell.  I used the bathroom before ordering  and when I went to wash my hand I put soap on my hands and tried to turn on the water and it was dead.  No hot or cold water.  No towels either to wipe the soap off.  Lovely.  Now I have to go out to the there restaurant area to wipe the soap off using napkins.  No biggie, things happen.  However, when I mentioned the problem to an employee She looked me in the eye, then turned around and walked away.  2 other employees right next to Her also pretended not to hear me.  So how many others belted out a deuce only to have their dirty hands touch the door, napkins and soda fountains etc.  How are the employees washing their hands? Mama Mia Diarrhea! How do places like this survive?

Charming interior, but hit-or-miss on the food.  The Poulet de Bergerac was good, imagine a Beef Wellington but with chicken.  Unfortunately the crab cakes were not good.  When a menu in St. Louis describes "lump" for a crab cake, I expect lump; there was no lump in evidence here, instead the crab cake contained bits of shell.  Portions for the meat are huge -- in particular the rack of lamb lasted three meals.

I have been several times and recommended to visitors.  Everybody has been very pleased.  I am a foodie from the East and Europe and was quite surprised by the quality of the food and the freshness.  I very rarely eat fried food but was totally happy with the pakoras (spinach and vegetable).  It was apparent that they had just been made and the chickpea flour covering was a tasty combination of crunch and chewiness.  With our guests they were gone in a heartbeat.  We had several curries, mostly lamb and chicken as well as naan and papadam.  A nice assortment of well priced Indian and other beers to match.  Friendly, knowledgeable and efficient service.  I think they are seeing the success they well deserve.

The service was horrible. We waiting on a table forever luckily the waitress came over and cleaned one for us.(due to the large group we needed a big table) The kitchen staff trying to rush out messing up everyone food. The silverware was so dirty. It wasn't as packed today thank god. They really need to step it up with the kitchen staff. And yes it wasn't that packed yet we waited to be seated and they had 7/8 empty tables.  The games was fun and the kids did have a blast besides the bad food experience.

I went to the old Sunset Grille location at sunrise this morning to give Biscuit Love a try. I shared several intimate lunches over the years at Sunset Grille with native Nashvillian, John Siegenthaler. So the location holds special memories for me. I was apprehensive about visiting the "super hip" and "trendy" Biscuit Love for fear of having to stand in line with tourists and hipsters with their beards w/ wool skullcaps that have become the rage in determining local restaurants success. I found neither. 

The place was quiet, the staff super friendly and "loving". Reasonably priced, for Nashville, the food was awesome. The coffee was intense and I am sure sourced "locally". I really enjoyed it. As I sat there thinking about my last lunch with John, I could see that this would have been a place we would have enjoyed together. A win for the locals, the tourists, and the beards! Watch out Pancake Pantry, there is a new breakfast joint in "the Village"!
Had some for a building holiday party. Very good food. Meatballs and sweet potato's were delicious

We came here on a Sunday evening around 730 and had 7 people in our party with chicken tender , club sandwich and grilled chicken orders and it took 50 minutes to get our food and it was missing 2 people's side items . While it wasn't the waitress's fault she also didn't attempt to recitify the situation and we saw her a total of 3 times during our wait with one of those being when she took our drink and food order. The manager did take 2 entrees off the Bill but we won't ever be going back .
My favorite grocery store, I think they are wonderful but they need more gluten free items like Safeway.

If you know me, you know I do not try different burger joints at all!! Nothing compares to my local Beach Corner joint. Well I tried this Smashburger place and it was tasty. I've only been twice, and both times was great.

One my last visit, I had a double cheeseburger with bacon on it. The meat cooked perfect. One my first visit, i had fries to go with it but it was not regular fries ( I prefer the regular fries over the fancy fries that were ordered). 

The location is great. Magazine street right where all of the great bars are located. The service is good and the location is impressively clean. 

The only complaint I have with the burgers are, they are very very greasy.
Lyndel our waitress was helpful and accommodating for our family and 2 year old daughter. Appreciated the care and many thanks!

Loved this place! I came here for a senior dinner. While the menu is pretty small, I love how it's so focused on Korean fusion food. I ordered the salmon bibimbap with my rice on the side. I thought the flavors balanced perfectly. Compared to other bibimbaps I've had in the past, the one I had at Southgate wasn't too heavy on the sauce. The ingredients were also seasoned just right, so that the main star of the dish was the actual salmon. While I don't drink, I was also extremely impressed by their drink specials. Would definitely reconsider this place if I'm in the mood for awesome food in a cozy environment.

I read about this Restaurant in the Sauce magazine and thought it would be a good spot to dine. I was disappointed in the seating,food, and price. 

For the price I would think you would have a waiter or waitress. Food was average. Portions where ridiculously small. 2 deviled eggs for $6.....GEESH.

I'm not sure if the cook knows what the original recipes looked like before he prepared it but h has to do some research. 


I had the catfish, sweet potatoes, and pork cracklings cornbread. Catfish was average and small portions. Sweet potatoes where bland, and the cornbread had NO pork cracklings in it, google it when you get a chance. 

Overall I didn't enjoy it.

This Walmart has appallingly bad reviews and a low rating. I'm giving them a pass. It's Walmart you guys. Are you expecting white glove service? I'm not. It serves its purpose. That doesn't mean you shouldn't wipe down your cart really well with those sanitizing wipes by the door and try not to touch anything you don't have to touch. You should!
Parking is not the best but the service and food is a must visit. They don't serve pork so everything is turkey based. Order the favorites and you can't go wrong! Cheese grits are so good!

Every time we are in town visiting family we HAVE to stop by Mr Ice Cream...usually multiple times. All the flavors we have tried have been excellent. Pricing is reasonable, and you get as many toppings as you like. If you want ice cream, this is THE place to go.
Amazing!!!! Famous shrimp cocktail is to die for~~WOW! The cocktail sauce is awesome! Service impeccable. Steaks were incredible.

I would definitely recommend Helzberg Diamonds. I purchased Christmas gifts for my whole family and Joanna was so helpful. She made great suggestions for what I should get for each person and showed me many options in all different price points, taught me about diamonds and different stones and even showed me under the microscope. I will be returning for all my occasions in the future and I look forward to working with Joanna again.

True Mexican taqueria. True authentic Mexican Food. Muy buenos tacos, sopes y gorditas.

My family and I were at UCSB for a Softball camp and stopped at this restaurant on our way back home to San Diego. I must say, it was well worth our stop. 

As a Tijuana native, hime of street tacos, I approve this taqueria.

Room smells like cigarette smoke, Dog in room 505 or 504, barked all night, No towels, no room service in two days. Clogged up bathroom sink, with someone's hair Ana no toilet paper in bathroom... slow .. very slow elevators... Come on guys you can do better then this. The Super 8 is better then this.... very disappointing...

This is a small family run restaurant with really authentic Vietnamese food. I really enjoyed going to Pho Cam Ly regularly when we lived in NOLA.

The people in the restaurant are very nice and friendly. We went so often and got to know them well. Once they even recognized our voices on the phone when we called in with different numbers -- just shows you a personal touch you don't see in many Vietnamese restaurants.

The food is excellent, affordable, authentic. The Pho is great, perfect for cold days. Very generous serving at low prices. We also always order spring rolls (eat wrapped in lettuce) and she shaken beef/ bo luc lac. The place is very clean and the location is great.

Ate here many times and is always consistent!

Highly recommended.

Good find for Greek food in a cozy restaurant with beautiful decor. Seated immediately on a Friday night, slightly before the dinner rush. Service was quick and to the point, the menu included many traditional options- unfortunately the moussaka was unavailable at this time. The food came out in a timely manner and our server was attentive to our enjoyment of our meals. Overall good food and a great environment. A little pricey, however seemed fair given that this is a intimate family run restaurant. Would eat here again.
Brooklyn NY is the vibe here!!! Super cool baristas and an open feel. We had a cafe con LecHe. Smooth and creamy and was the perfect end to a great day!

Today I finally tried this place which I've had bookmarked for at least a month. When I pulled up the outside looked different than I expected. It was very weird and not aesthetically pleasing. The inside wasn't bad looking by any means I just felt the name "mason jar" didn't really fit the ambiance. I guess I expected something more rustic and homier.

When you walk in you enter the line to order and there's two huge menus on the wall. They have burgers, sandwiches, salads, desserts, a kids menu, and daily specials. They also serve alcohol here. The lady who took our order at the counter was so sweet and gave exceptional customer service.

Once we took our number we got our drinks and sat. There were several people ahead of us but the food only took maybe 10 minutes to come out. I had ordered the shrimp poboy and my boyfriend had ordered the angus cheese burger. My shrimp poboy was just average and the fries had way too much Parmesan on them. My boyfriend didn't care for his burger at all but he's a much harder food critic to please than I am.

Other things about this place: you can call ahead and pick up orders through the drive through. There's also one television inside.

We had to wait a while for a table, then the order I made was made incorrectly, granted the server was new. The Peanut Butter Chocolate waffle was good, my companions had the pecan waffle, which we agreed was too many pecans in the waffle. Fluffier waffles would have been nice.

Nice little restaurant/ bar near Vanderbilt. Free parking for 1.5 hours (which is super awesome because there's barely any free parking in this town anymore!) service and food are good. Menu and drinks are also reasonably. The verde dip is one of my favs, as well as the gang feathers on a Caesar salad!

I've gotten dry aged steaks and fillet-both were excellent. The staff is very knowledgeable and friendly and they do a great job trimming the cuts. This is one of my favorite shops in philly- definitely a must for meat lovers that cook.

11 different protein options. Each are 3oz. Unlike other places that squash their patties flat and removes most of the juices, these are thicker and juicer with more flavor, they are just smaller in diameter. These are truly mini burgers with many fresh toppings. Sliders are typically 1oz or less. The sweet potato fries are awsome.

This was a great meal! So worth the money!! Had the Hey Lucy omelette and it was just so good! Plenty to fill you up for a long day on the beach. My daughter wanted a salad that came with salmon on it and she's a vegetarian so she asked it without and they did it and then adjusted the price which was really awesome!! Fun drinks and great services! I would recommend this place to all.

I've been to this Panera few times before and it's always fine but tonight I ordered food to go, got home, realized they didn't make my sandwich correctly, drove back got a new sandwich! When I  got home and took a bite out a sandwich I found a nice long piece of blonde hair...  I am never coming back here or to any other Panera again.

Went last night before his company Christmas jamboree and the food and service were wonderful!

This place was moderately busy on a Friday night, we were way overdressed because we had to do his party afterwards. The hostess was quick to greet us and super friendly.

We were led to a booth and our server was Katie, who was on the ball and incredibly charming. I ordered the scallops, subbed out mashed potatoes for the rice and my food was perfect. The scallops were perfectly cooked and succulent. The mash was tasty and even the vegetables were fantastic. The two drinks I had were really tasty and strong too, the bartender is on it! 

My date had the steak which comes with a killer marinade and was perfectly cooked and juicy. I was delighted with my scallops but the steak was so good! I wish they would do a surf and turf! 

Finished with cheesecake that was dense and creamy and it ended the night perfectly. 

Bathrooms were cute and clean with kitschy beach signs in the stalls. The crowd was upbeat and the staff were all smiles and laughter. 

Wonderful. We can't wait to go again!

Excellent shrimp and grits but portion sizes are way too small for the price. I give 5 stars for Kevin's customer service because they were closing the kitchen and we had a few friends who were running behind that joined us right as they we closing the kitchen, they allowed us to still put the order in so they wouldn't be hungry for the night.

I've never been to a nail salon this beautiful! The decor is simple, clean and modern. The staff is very friendly and talented. You won't be disappointed. I will definitely recommend this place to my friends and family.

Groupers is definitely one of my favorite spots on the beach. My boyfriend and I come here at least twice a week. The seafood is FRESH and delicious. The staff is amazing and will always remember your name. The location is perfect and the restaurant is clean. A must try in Irb!
The market have a lot of healthy options and seem to be more health conscious, but I'm sure everyone knows that.  What I like the most is that they have a buffet with a lot of healthy options.

Amazing amazing amazing. Definitely put preservation hall on your to do list. The band is incredibly gifted, it was a moving performance. As most reviewers have mentioned, purchase tickets in advance - there was a line out the door and with reserved seating you do not have to worry about the line. The performance was at 10:15pm, they opened the doors at 10pm. We arrived around 9:50, checked in and went to bourbon street, which is next door, grabbed some drinks and headed right in before they started. I hope to see this band in the future again!

I eat here a lot and the food is very good.  Our server was gross last time with a dirty apron, licked her fingers and then touched the top lip of my water glass.  At least a couple of critical health violations.
Please train your servers on the health code.
This place is amazing. Excellent sushi burritos. Everything is fresh and delicious. Choose from several suggested burritos or create your own. Very clean restaurant, good service.

I really wish they wouldn't put BBQ in their name. I hail from Memphis, so I am a bbq snob. This is NOT bbq! I like their brisket, cornbread, and Mac and cheese, but if you want real BBQ, go somewhere else.

I was in from out of town and Deluxe is my sister in laws salon so she made an appt for me 12/30 And Jen was my stylist. I received a cut and color and I LOVE IT. She listened to what I had to say and price was less expensive than what I pay going to a Wmington, DE salon. Same day appt. too.
Rude, rude, rude! Hung up on me on the phone twice when I was asking about wait time. Food can't be their redeeming quality if you never get that far.

My first visit to the area the menu by the entrance of the pier caught our eye.  My wife, son (3) and I enjoyed the service.   The mussels with white wine sauce was amazing 5 stars for sure.   The grouper blackened was well seasoned but was essentially an average dish and for the money expected a little more elegant finishing touch, like a fruity or garlic salsa / sauce.   My Tilapia was average, blackened was good but average in flavor and presentation.   I could come again but will likely try something else.   Nothing wrong with the place but nothing making me feel I need to come back.

Warning: they do not stand behind their work nor will they do right by the customer. 

I've been going to their Westampton location since the previous owner, Mike ran it. Always found them to be the most honest and reliable mechanics I'd ever encountered and as a result I've sent a ton of business their way. Sadly I can't say this about the new owner, Tim. This guy definitely doesn't stand by his work. 

A year ago my car had an engine failure. After discussing with the mechanic we decided to replace the engine. That's when the nightmare started. A year later and after $5000 spent I'm still without the car. The mechanic admits they can't or don't know how to fix it but the owner refuses to give me a refund. I've been beyond patient giving them every opportunity to make good, but Tim can apparently care less about his clients. 

Fair warning, they DO NOT Guarantee they're work. If they screw up, you'll be eating the cost and may even be without a vehicle. Not worth the risk. Find another shop. I sadly have to now prepare a filing court one year after I have them my car to fix so I could pass it on to my daughter.

I'm so incredibly happy with our pictures! Angela Clifton Photography have worked with us 3 times and we have been happy with every single picture that was taken! Not only are the photos fabulous, but we had such a fun experience. The price is extremely reasonable and the pictures will be a keepsake we will cherish forever!

Since I travel so much for my job. I have he rare opportunity to eat at so many different places. I chanced on this place. Parking isn't exactly the easiest. But where in Santa Barbara is easy for parking?! This place makes that all go away. Service is outstanding. I accidentally left my CC there for a week. They remembered who I was, and had it waiting for me. This just doesn't happen in today's service related establishments. I've since taken family and friends to experience this first hand. Funny that I haven't got to the best part. Their food is off the charts. I frequent this place for breakfast while I'm working in the city. I've had lunch here a couple times. Same as B-fast. Doesn't disappoint. Highly recommend the Santa Barbara local omelette, add try-tip. A lot of food but you have to try it. I could go on and on. One last thing. One of the waiters there asked me my name after my second visit. Several weeks later, ran into him. Remembered my name. Just great food with sincere friendly service.

Lee was amazing. I was stranded on the side of the road with a dead car and dead phone and he offered to move me to a parking lot and use his phone. He ended up towing me to a mechanic and was so helpful and friendly. Life saver!
The hibachi experience is amazing! The place get pretty crowded, expect long waits if you have no appointments on the weekend nights.
Great environment! The ambiance was just right to be able to talk to people across the table from you. Food was great with many options to enjoy. Large drink menu with several beer tabs.

My first ever yelp review. I'm not the type to write reviews but Tuna Bar was just fantastic and I wanted to support the new restaurant in the neighborhood.

We ordered the pork gyoza, tuna crudo, toro sashimi and two sushi rolls. All were out of this world good. You could tell how fresh the fish was. 

Only house sake being served right now but waiter told us a full sake menu will be offered shortly.

I highly recommend Tuna Bar and I can say for sure that I will be back.
Like their wings, not too big therefore very flavorful! The price is less competitive though. New location is further east than the old one but much bigger.

You know it's going to be a good latte, when you don't have to wait to let it cool down before you drink it.
When espresso is made at the right temperature, it has a beautiful, not bitter taste.
That's exactly what I got from this coffee shop when I ordered a latte.

Bad Monkey was a fun location with true diversity.  Many different types of locals and travelers of various ages enjoying a good draft beer or mixed up cocktail. 
The atmosphere had a miltary/airforce type of look and feel, helicopter hanging from ceiling to Ammunition style draft pours/decor.
Plenty of games like darts, billards and Jenga to help you spend the time while listening to live DJ playing 80's to current (2017) songs.
Not going to lie it was great to hear some of those fun 90s hits while sipping on my Jack Honey, while friends downed local pale ale drafts of Jai Alai.
Pricing was fair and good time was had by all. If in these parts again, would consider another stop for sure. 
*Also note upon 'checking in' they were nice enough to offer 10% off the bar tab.
Pizza is good. The pepperoni pizza isnt as greasy/oily as most places. It tastes pretty good to me. Delivery doesnt take too long either.

First Burrito Sushi I ever ate.   Has to be in the top 5 Sushi items I have eaten. Phenomenal taste and fresh. I live in the other side of the state but I will be back to devour many more sushi burritos in the future.

This is a very nice hotel near downtown Boise. It's conveniently close to the university, downtown, and the airport. It's quiet and clean. The rooms have recently been remodeled. We had a suite, so we had a very nice kitchen and full size fridge. The hotel is close to several restaurants and fast food joints if you don't want to make use of the kitchen. There is a grocery store and at least one drug store nearby if you need to run out for anything. A free shuttle service is available to and from the airport. The suite was comfortably sized. This is a great place to stay for a business trip or pleasure visit.

Beautiful building.  Good location.  Polite service.

Rooms themselves are average appearance and quality.  We had trouble with room keys not working. We had plumbing problems in both rooms.  Grey water backed up into showers.  Difficult to park without valet which costs $38 per day.  Recommend factoring it into the cost when comparing.
Seriously tho, why change the noodles from beef noodle soup to some cheap non chewy dry noodles!!??

I am just updating this review, it took a lot longer than expected to hear back from someone at The Grove Hotel but we received many apologies and they are doing everything to make it right, it's not our wedding night but they have done above and beyond to show that they absolutely are sincere and they did what they could. We appreciate it more than ever and hope that we we get to use our free stay, we can actually enjoy it. Thank you Grove Hotel!

This is an amazing buffet.  Really good food, adequate parking, and good location if you live or work near the Feather Sound area.  Good service as well.

The buffet is large and everything I've ever tried has been really good to great.

Snoballs are definitely hit or miss and this was a miss for me. They got points for their hours and proximity to my house, but I did not enjoy the flavors. The staff was friendly and there wasn't a wait, but I doubt I'll be back.

Now in our 7th week (awaiting completion of a new residence not far away.) PERFECT. Not only the value..(monthly)..but this well run motel has a kitchenette in every room. It is comfortable and clean. Andy, proprietor has the best staff I have ever seen in a facility such as this. Megan Melia, Luz at the front desk are very helpful and really enjoy their job. Other support staff are most friendly and eager to be of service.

We're staying at Grand Sierra for New Year and the kids love Johnny Rockets here on the ground floor. Our server was Keith, an energetic, career made, fun and had a great sense of humor. Our foods were great, chicken strips, Route 66 with onion rings, Philly cheese steak and the shake of the month, too rich and sweet for my taste.
A simple lunch and everyone was full and happy. We got to bring our shake and Iced tea to go. Kudos to Keith.

Fantastic food. And knowledgeable staff. Very happy with our experience. The grilled cheese was a family favorite but the burger, waffles and salads were to die for. Only complaint is that they did not have any lamb stew left! We'll have to go back to try it.

I wandered in here today with my boyfriend bc a silver shirt caught my eye from the street. The ladies working were so awesome. Friendly, helpful, and not annoying or pushy. The woman had to help me dress and clip the shirt on. She was very professional and it was a wonderful shopping experience. The store itself has so many great unique things. I wanted to buy it all. Don't miss this neat little shop. Also--- the prices are very reasonable. Nothing like some of the other boutiques. You could very easily get a one of a kind outfit with accessories for less than $100, maybe even less than $75. I love this store
Best Indian restaurant in Pinellas County. Unfortunately too far for me to visit as much as I want!! delicious

Disappointed today. Took my family to the Christmas show and had a blast. Went to the Brew Brothers and was very disappointed. We started out with chips and salsa with the guacamole. I tasted the guacamole and it was spicy to me. Even my wife who likes spicy items said it was a little hot, and she's Mexican. I asked the waitress what was in the guacamole and she did not know. Later she said it was jalapeo. I'm can't have anything spicy due to an ulcer. I told the waitress why don't you tell people it has jalapeo in it? She did say anything.             So we order and I had the smoked chicken and pineapple. At that time I asked for more water and my daughter asked for ranch. A few minutes later our food arrived everyone but mine. The waitress said it would be only a few minutes. So everyone started eating. 10 minutes later I man came over and apologize for my dinner said they had some problems in the kitchen and it would be a few minutes. So about 5-7 minutes my chicken arrived. Now my family was mostly done eating. I looked at my plate and it's small chicken peace's with chunks of pineapple. Not much chicken. The bbq sauce was lightly poured on to it. So I tried it and no smoke flavor and it was very dry. I was expecting a little more the that.  The waitress forgot our water and ranch dip we had to ask several times. No apology or compensation for the spicy guacamole or dinner issue. I'm not saying I should get a free meal but come on, try to make it right!

As a vegetarian/vegan for over 15+ years, this place is so worth the stop. I wish it was a little bigger, but it fit the bill for me, my wife and my 3 year old. DOPE Food, seriously I need this in Maryland.

Looked for a recommended place as we were traveling through, and this one had great reviews.  Decided to stop and walked in at 732 on a Friday night and was told by someone they were closed already.  Another person walked in behind me and was told the same thing.  Well they should fix their website so that it reflects their hours of operation accurately! Besides what type of resturants closes at 730 on a Friday night.

Another great spot to get a good cup of coffee! Great atmosphere inside with lots of tables to sit down and catch up with friends. Cafe au lait was excellent, the milk was steamed piping hot, just how I like it! They offer complementary simple syrup and honey as well. The entrance has the quintessential Instagram spot for your pics. Go nuts.

As a Greek looking for a nice restaurant in Philly, I stumbled upon Zorba's which was excellent!! The food was spot on, and reminded me of the food I grew up with. The service was wonderful and the food was amazing. We came in on a busy Saturday night and were seated right away and taken care of all night!!

This bar is more depressing than the Eagles SNF effort against Seattle. All the employees seem like the type of people who use an umbrella in a light drizzle, but Roger was an especially sensitive specimen. The beer list was unimpressive and overall there are much better places to drink in Philly such as under the bridge with Duncan and his crew.

We had a Noritz N-084M with an error 98- which is a combustion error- basically Gas of Fan issues; this is a large Tankless rated for 5+ bathroom homes.  While i'm a high functioning DIY'r- these types of repairs (involving Gas) are best left to Plumbers.  My experience with most Electricians and Plumbers over the last 10 years has not been good- ridiculous pricing reflecting a disconnect from reality and common sense- AND most are so incompetent- one plumber quoted $400 to replace a pressure reduction valve- a $20 part and a 15 min repair.

Now we had a pretty good idea of what the repair would be- which most plumbers don't like - but the Lee Technician that showed up- John (their tankless guy) was great.  

Low key but very knowledgable- which makes you forgive his lack of responsiveness with respect to time; he was about 3 hours late ;)-  but actually that gave us time (my tenant and i) to pull apart the unit and start in on some of the work- he showed up- took a look at what we had done (made sure we didn't make any egregious errors)- he took over and finished up- spotted a small leak that had caused corrosion in one of the electrical harnesses.  He cut the harness and direct wired it. 

His work was excellent, his demeanor should be a training video for all in home subcontract technicians (great ability to read the room), he was respectful and informative and a general pleasure to be around- the entire visit was probably around 3 hours- although, i left after about 90 min.  He let himself out and my tenants didn't even know that he had left.

I got the bill a couple of days later and thought it was very reasonable- in-fact - he probably under charged and over delivered....  how often do you hear that !

we've built several homes over the years and are not the typical call for most of these types of contractors- i have been reticent to call a company the size of Lee- as it is hard to maintain quality when a company grows past a certain head count- my hats off to Lee- we will definitely put them at the top of our call list when we do our next reno in the spring

thanks so much !!

expensive for what it is. I got the potatoes and sausage with a fried egg medium. the dish has onion, bell pepper, sausage, and potatoes. it didn't really taste like it was cooked together but rather it was pieced together. the sausage looked like cafeteria sausage. the egg was funny. REALLLLY runny. like the egg white was puddling down my potatoes into a pool.

They had coffee but it was burnt and they served in mugs which retained the heat like molten lava (perhaps so we would drink less?)
Excellent food, great friendly service. Big portions and tasty. I visit regularly and have left overs for lunch the next day.

Let me start out by saying that the food was excellent though my main course of a fish stew was at best warm when delivered. The different courses were very tasty and even with the relatively small menu - there was enough variety that anyone should be able to find something that they would like. 

A restaurant experience relies not only on the food, but also the ambiance of the place and that is where Zeppoli is definitely lacking. The restaurant  is small and the tables are extremely close to one another and also relatively tiny. We felt like we were on top of the people near us. We had a party of six and the waitress had difficulty even trying to place food on the table without us having to either remove or shift our plates around. It is also pretty noisy. It was difficult to hold a conversation with a person across the table. The seats are also small, wooden and after 75 minutes we were all kind of shifting in the seats to find a comfortable way to sit. 

Again, the food was very good and the Italian donuts that we had for desert were absolutely worth the calories. Figure on spending approximately $60 per person (incl. tip) and without wine (BYOB). Overall, the experience though good was not the off the chart experience we had heard about.

We stayed at the NOPSI Hotel for 5 days and 4 nights. This entry covers two reviews: one is for a dinner and the other is for a breakfast.

On the 7th of December we did not get enough of the local food on our first dinner round so we decided to indulge in some more. After looking at the menu we could not really see many choices that are considered local or, at least, at a decent price (most of the stuff is on the pricey side). As I considered my options I eventually identified a few and I decided I was going to eat some fish so I ordered a black drum for $24 (not specifically listed on the menu because it's the catch of the day and it was disguised as "Louisiana Gulf fish"). As a drink I ordered an iced tea, nothing that deserves paragraphs or standing ovations so I will not digress on that. The seafood arrived a reasonable time later. It consisted of stacked slices of fish on top of some dark beans pointing towards the center of a plate with a buttery sauce drizzle. The dish itself was good and enjoyable. It had a bold but sophisticated flavor that you find in fine restaurants. From what I tasted it seemed to me the cook knew what he/she is doing.

On the morning of the 8th of December we woke up early and we decided to have breakfast at the restaurant. The weather was horrible (cold and rain) so we decided to start the day in a relaxed way. We arrived early in the morning (0700-0730), a great time to have breakfast because I like quiet places and the place was quiet. We ordered Belgian waffles (spelled Belgiam in the menu in the room). Since I don't like butter in/on most stuff, particularly on waffles, I asked not to put butter on the waffles. After 20 minutes our food was not yet available. Considering the fact the restaurant was deserted and we showed up rather early, I came to the conclusion they must have went to Belgium to get the waffles. After a while I looked over and I read the mannerism of our waitress. The entire thing translated into "he does not want butter and there is butter on these waffles" which in turn translated into "you gotta do them again lady cook" so in the end I believe we waited about 30 minutes before eating. When the waffles arrived (presumably from Belgium) they landed on our table and they had a nice appearance. The syrup that came with them was sweet and tasty. It wasn't the regular cheap waffle syrup you find at IHOP or Denny's. It had a higher quality, it was pure cane syrup and I could taste the difference. The waffles were good but they eventually got chewy after a while. Still, they were good, a little pricey ($12) but nonetheless a good way to start a day.

The service at night was good so I cannot complain about that. Our waiter was patient although somewhat unprepared in terms of mannerism and the way you would talk to customers, almost as if shy or on the first day at work. The service in the morning was mediocre. The lady serving us was a little stiff, disappeared for a long time.
The thing I liked the least about the restaurant was that the utensils were sitting directly on the table. For a place with a nice, relaxed and sophisticated ambient like the one in this restaurant forks and knives on the table a big minus in my book. Aside from the fact it's not elegant, it's not even clean. I wonder how this place can pass regular health inspections. Luckily, the manager on site at night understood the point when I asked for clean utensils and helped promptly. The person who served us in the morning paused when I asked for clean utensils (almost as if my request was totally unreasonable).

I have one suggestion to the management which has two facets: train your personnel to be more friendly and relaxed and never take utensils back to the kitchen before bringing clean ones to the table (I am not sure to this day we got clean forks and knives at breakfast).

I would give 4 stars to the place but the service can be improved and the utensils mustn't lay on the bare table so I can only award 3 stars.

The people there are very friendly but I was not a fan of their pizza. We ordered a large pepperoni pizza and when we got home to eat it the cheese fell off the pizza for each slice. They did have good mozzarella sticks though.

Food was very well prepared here...the only reason they are getting two stars.  The service SUCKED. So slow. Server would ask as walking by if anything was needed but not stop to hear the answer. Ordered beer and waited for it while the server rolled silverware. Place offer a $1 off beer when train goes by but when they did go by it seemed every server and bartender hid behind the bar doing side work. Beer was ok. Go to untapped for reviews on that. On a positive side, the Reuben sandwich was excellent. Recommend the beer battered fries.

I was excited to eat at Timpano. We were seated outside which has nice ambience, the only good part of the restaurant. I ordered the steak and broccoli. The steak which I ordered medium came out cold and was well done. Not to mention for a $29 steak the portion was very small with no add ons without paying extra. I ordered a side of broccoli for $10 expecting the best due to the price of a side only getting stalks that had no taste and barely resembled broccoli. The service was also sub par for what you expect at a fancy place like this. Will not go back, waste of money I could make better food at home.

Huge portions, great service. Had the fried chicken with the crawfish sauce. The chicken wasn't seasoned at all but paired with the sauce it was very good. I only ate half have a whole meal left over.

This place is very strategic with how the food is portioned. The special comes with little meat to force you to pay for extra meat. When I brought it to the owner's attention he dismissed it. Of course he's not going to stop the scam for little ol me who he still received a profit from. These ppl are very greedy.

Hubbard's Marina Offers 5 hr trips that go out about an hour offshore, fish for 3 hours, and then travel an hour back to trhe dock.  I do not recommend  these 5 hour trips to experienced ocean anglers. Simply put, this 5 hour trip does not go out far enough or deep enough to get to large grouper, large snapper, amerjack, tuna and other larger fish that most of us experienced fisherman are looking for. It is strictly 3 hrs of bottom fishing for grey snapper, hogfish, sand perch, and many other fish that are not very big at the approximately 50 ft depth they fish at on these trips.  I went on 10 trips from December of 2017 through July of 2017, then quit going because I never saw a fish bigger than 6 lbs caught on any of the 10 trips. This 5 hr trip, in my opinion, is a good experience for tourists, and children, but not for serious fishermen.  The pictures of all the huge fish they display on their website and emails, I conjecture, were probably taken from rare instances over long periods of time, and from the more expensive longer trips to deep waters.

The food was delicious and tasted really authentic. Moving to Indy from LA, I've been missing authentic Asian food! We will definitely be coming back. This is a family run business and the owners were really nice too.

Very good experience. There were five of us. Everyone enjoyed the appetizers, main entree and drinks. Service was excellent and personable. The prices good.  Ambiance is pleasant and relaxing. Cost is reasonable. Looking forward to our next visit!

Great little place ....and it is little.......but the service, food and price can't be beat .......I have been driving by this place for three months now and finials stop in    Should have sooner.  Nice place.   Wil return again

It was my first time getting this type of massage- Michael was great, personable, and made me feel comfortable. After the massage my body felt rejuvenated and relaxed. I recommend it for anyone that feels like they have a stiff back- I feel completely aligned after working with him.

When I went to pick up my pizza, I saw that the girls making the pizza were not wearing any gloves! I asked about it, and they confirmed that they don't wear gloves to make the food! Well, I went against my better judgement and still ate it after reheating it. Big mistake! After eating my Chicago style pizza, which was pretty average, I ended sick for the rest of the night. Definitely not going back here!

Mobile check-in was easy. The location is just off I40 at Donelson near BNA. The guy at the front desk was super friendly. They put me in a suite, but I did not care for it. I called down stairs
And the front desk moved me to a standard king room. Much more comfortable. About like a Hilton Garden Inn.

I assume this is the BP we get delivery from. Which is always amazing! I admit they are a few $$ more but in the end they are my fav. pizza delivery place. Prompt and tasty. Lunch wasn't that great. The service was good. I mean not amazing. I did ask for a second to pick a drink but it did take a few minutes. The ceaser I had was great though. While the ribs were tasty the size was tiny. Overall it was a decent lunch but I wish I had stuck to the pizza or pasta I know is always good there. It is the delivery that gives this place a 4/5 in the end!

This place is delicious! Consistently. Their smoothies are amazing, sandwhichs and wraps are well balanced and delicious, their salads are flavorful, though a bit wet towards the end. Friendly service. Be mindful of lunch time as it can take quite some time to get your food but if you order ahead, you'll be fine! LOVE this place.

I love the menu,but im a local an i been here many times and there is never a good satisfying  good welcome or would u like to oreder!! Nothing not even a hi! Just a straight face!! Love love the items on the menu!!! But costumers service sucks !!!    
 Worst part!!! When i ask for a container to go! The cashier did not even bother to strive to make up for the straight face! Without a word she just pointed at the to go containers!!!!

Stumbled upon this place because all the other bars were closed because of a water main break. We were going to order food until we walked in and saw it was a little run down and the bathroom was disgusting. Decided to just get a beer and leave. Wasn't worth our time.

I LOVE the food and drinks here, I've never had anything I didn't like. My favorite is the grilled cheese, mixing apples and cheese is my favorite, so this sandwich is a hit for me. The decor is awesome as well, very unique and and fun. What I find really disappointing is the service. The past few times I've been in I've had the same male server who has been less than stellar. We wait maybe 10 minutes to give an order, waited 30 minutes for our first drinks, and then another 20 for the check. I would have loved to order a couple more drinks and maybe some desert, but waiting on the server 30 minutes per drink is something I don't have time for. The other staff seemed to be working really hard and even helped us out a little when our server was no where to be found, I wish I would have had one of them instead.

This is my favorite restaurant! My husband and I go to Nirvana Indian Bistro every chance we get. We've probably tried the entire menu at this point and it's all fantastic. The owner is the nicest guy and he's very health-conscious, so you never need to feel bad about ordering extra! The staff are all incredibly helpful and attentive. Don't forget to order orange kulfi for dessert!

Okay so I have to start this review by saying (1) that the food was actually really good and (2) that this was one of the weirdest experiences of our entire lives.

We came here to use my $30 off birthday certificate and it was also our first time at Benihana.  We'd been to Hibachi before so somewhat knew what to expect but went into it with no expectations.  We sat down with two other couples and immediately knew this was going to be a weird night.  The couple next to us told us that they were regulars and came roughly once/week so we leaned on them for guidance and expertise.  I ordered the Rocky's choice and my husband got the teriyaki steak - both were good but the problem was our experience.  Immediately my water was overfilled and the woman to the other side of the table made a huge deal about it and we knew that they were going to be persnickity and make all of the servers and chefs very flustered and because of that my husband and I just tried to smile, laugh and enjoy our date night and not pay attention to them.  They went on to correct the chef multiple times during his presentation, tell the servers that they were getting them the incorrect sauces, extra dressings, multiple waters and sodas even if they weren't finished with the ones that they had (people, i tried to tell you that this was the weirdest experience we've ever had).  With how shaken the staff was, our presentation was not the best and our food wasn't cooked properly because the chef had to cater to this couples ridiculous demands (more butter, cooked more, i want my vegetables and meat mixed together, cut my meat in the opposite direction).... and then the weirdest part was that the couple ordered an additional steak which when the server went through to ensure that our orders were accurate was never brought up but then when the couple didn't receive it at the end of the meal were OUTRAGED.  To the point where the manager came over and assured them and guaranteed that he put the steak on the plate himself (he didn't) and they called his bluff and everyone got even more uncomfortable.  phew.  Now they forgot my white rice as well as the entire table's ice cream and tea and gave us the incorrect check twice.  The bathroom floors were incredibly sticky and gross and two people at our table had to request new flatware or plates because they weren't cleaned properly.  This review is after a dinner on a Monday night so maybe it was just an off time for this crew and I know that the customers were not helping the cause but we're not willing to try again to find out if it was just a fluke.

Recently joined and have been really happy with the gym!!  It has good equipment, classes and staff, couldn't be more excited.  The bonus is having multiple locations so can always stop at another facility if I am out of my neighborhood...the cost is GREAT:-)

This place has grown on me over the years. I find myself going here more and more, despite the (fantastic) proliferation of coffee places in the northern Camden County area. It's just a solid place to come back to again and again, and hopefully this'll give you some insight into why.

Let's start with the seating. It's got a lot of different areas to hang out; aside from two large seating areas on either side of the counter, there's an awesome courtyard right on the corner of Haddon and Redman Avenues and plenty of sidewalk seating out front for the warmer months. Not enough places in the suburbs have outside areas for hanging out, so these spots for people - and puppy - watching is much appreciated.

Their coffee's always been pretty good, and I think they keep switching up what beans they get. From what I can remember, I've seen Rival Brothers, Square One. They do pour overs, which I love, and they've got some more exotic things sometimes, like the Gibraltar (a variation on a cortado) and the "Americola", a fascinating mix of Mexican coke and a shot of espresso. To eat, there've got a variety of pastries like muffins and homemade pop tarts and quiches.

Also, it's worth noting that this is one of the only coffee places open on a late Sunday afternoon/early evening worth going. There're a lot of coffee places around here, but they all seem to close between 1 and 3PM. For years now, Jersey Java's open open til 6PM on Sundays, which I really appreciate. I don't know if the other places think people just hide out at home on Sunday afternoons or what, but it's great this place stays open.
I love this place. The food and coffee are excellent. On the weekends, expect a bit of a line but as a local, It's great and I would highly recommend their "Build your own" hashes.

My favorite -- the chicken pot pie on Sundays and their herbal iced tea!  Much of the rest of their food is good -- I try to avoid the fried foods as my heart isn't appreciating those these days, but the sweet potatoes, cauliflower (OMG -- yum), and banana pudding are pretty darned good.
Definitely give this place a stop if you enjoy good old comfort food.

Always delicious. Fresh, beautifully prepared food. This is a must-visit locale anytime I'm in STL. Wait staff is always very nice and friendly. Sometimes you have to wait for your food but it's a tapas restaurant; things come out as they're prepared. In nice weather I always enjoy the outdoors seating and summer drinks. In winter it's cozier seating inside this old gas-station turned restaurant. Fun & funky decor. But come for the food! Best hummus (King of Kings) but just know it's heavy on the tahini (it's in the middle so you can swirl in as much as you'd like). Zucchini carpaccio (it's actually grilled think ribbons) is sublime. Charred tomato bruschetta... these are my go-to three choices and it makes for an amazing and delicious vegetarian lunch. My friends always get the egg salad (w/anchovy) and rave about it.  Home made breads. The larger dishes all look beautiful and scrumptious. They also do an honest and generous wine pour-/ which I always appreciate!

Nothing fancy but it does have some delicious Vietnamese food.  My son loves it here especially the shrimp rockets and shrimp & pork noodle soup.  The beef pho is yummy.  Perfect on a cold day too!  Great service - quick and attentive but they aren't obnoxious about it.  Love coming here.
Place looks like a speak easy from outside. I went on trivia night, it was fun, didn't try the food.

This casino was a joke. So let me get this right, $900 for two night stay during the middle of the week. $900 for a basic room.The high prices were definitely attract people to spend money at the casino. What a joke

This is easily the best cuban sandwich, pastelito and espresso i have ever had. the espresso shot is included with your meal, which is a nice touch and a nice caffeine postwould definitely recommend and will be back for more!
These guys are artists! Their beer selection and relaxed environment is always great. Love this place!

The place makes you miserable... The only good thing about it is the music. The prices make no sense and the owner is always feeling the need to introduce himself to his customers and to bother them. My friends and I certainly couldn't enjoy our stay here.
I came in with pretty high expectations about there pizza.   I do have to say that I'm pretty disappointed with it. The atmosphere was Great. Since, being from the Chicago area. My search continues..
Delivery driver didn't bring entire delivery, said he would go back to store to grab it and didn't return. Store refused to refund money!

The people were friendly and it was nice and clean, location was great too. I tried the salad and a sugar donut. Both were really delicious and i'd eat them again. I was afraid the salad was going to be underwhelming and soggy or something since they are a donut shop but it was surprisingly fresh & well prepared. Someone i came with tried a chocolate covered donut (i think it was the salted caramel) and they said it was so-so. I ate my sugar donut with an iced coffee so i liked the mildness of mine. No complaints here.

According to my experience, there is just one place in Tokyo at the fish market where you get your seafood a little fresher. Here in Santa Barbara, it does not get any fresher. Right from the fish tank in the cooking pot on your plate. Don't expect a fancy restaurant with a nice ambiance because this is not the reason you come here (though the outside seating has a nice ocean/harbor view). It is the variety of fresh shellfish prepared according to your appetite and taste buds. The wait can be long during peak hours but it is worth it. Put your name down and take a walk on the peer to free-up some extra room in your stomach - you'll need it!

Found this restaurant in the New Orleans dining guide. I'm a writer, so the concept sounded fun. Not only was the ambiance right up our alley, but the food was amazing and our server, Tracy, was awesome. We had the Cuban sandwich, the Cajun Poutine, a  Scorpion cocktail, and a Death in the Afternoon cocktail. I recommend all of them. I also bought a William Faulkner T-shirt on my way out. Great music, too. Highly recommend.

Stopped in for  some food after hearing so many good things about his place. Let me tell you this...THE FOOD DID NOT DISAPPOINT! We had the shrimp creole and the shrimp and crepes! The creole was cooked perfectly! Great flavor and spices. The spice wasn't overbearing and shrimp cooked perfectly. Would give this meal a 10/10. The crepes and shrimp scared me because I've never had such a combination but man I was in for a surprise! Kudos to the chefs for balancing the savory flavor of the crepes and the spices of the shrimp. It was a beautiful dish and could eat this fish every day. This dish was definitely 100/100

Costco is always great. Bulk purchases, cheap food court,  good prices on gas, unbeatable return policy.  The only reason why it lost a star is because it frequently gets backed up -- need to open up more registers when the line extends past the snack aisles.  Although I guess that happens at most costcos...

Ola, my waxer, was literally amazing! (Let's rewind a bit)... so I haven't been waxed in a while...for a few reasons. One reason being that my previous wax experience went terribly. This was basically experiencing my first Brazilian all over again, so I was completely freaking out and almost canceled my appointment while I was only two blocks away. My skin is extremely sensitive... and maybe I was being a little over dramatic. I used to get brazilians regularly. Once I met with Ola, my entire mood changed. She did an amazing job and it wasn't even that painful. Can't be more thankful and relieved that this experience went well. I highly recommend booking an appointment with Ola!
Really enjoyed our visit here last weekend. The veggie burger sandwich and fries were just scrumptious!! And the hubs loved the beer flights! Awesome restaurant in a great location!

This is a great local bar that has many different drink specials  (listed on the website newtavernbar.com ).

They have DJ nights, karaoke night, open mike night and they also have a second room up from the bar.

They are very friendly!  And can hold birthday parties and give you a free cake.

Tired Hands Fermentaria reminds me of that old chestnut: There was a little girl, who had a little curl, right in the middle of her forehead. And when she was good, she was very very good. And when she was bad, she was horrid. 

Pretty much sums up Fermentaria in a nutshell. The beer? Always good. The food? Not so much. When it is good, it's great. When it's bad? It's really bad. Case in point, the fish tacos. Which I confess to having gotten several times. Until the visit when they arrived with a distinctly fishy odor that haunts me to this day.

And then there are the hipsters. My problem with hipster-owned restaurants is that they act like it's a privilege for YOU to be patronizing THEIR restaurant. Good customer service - a truly memorable dining experience - is the polar opposite.

========================
Update: I visited today and was so blown away by the pretzel appetizer that I had to login and add a star back! Nom, nom, nom!!!

Outstanding flavors on each pizza.  The arugula salad is great too.  The flavor of the crust makes one not want to leave any pizza bones behind on the plate.  They also just got their liquor license so you can have a local Dragoon beer with your pizza.  I think the sausage pizza is my fave - spicy and delicious.  Best pizza in Tucson!

Excellent shrimp and grits! I kinda am a shrimp and grits snob and this sweet little neighborhood hang knocked them out the park!! Add in a homegrown feel, cool artwork everywhere, and what I could tell were regulars, and you have a recipe for a stupendous breakfast spot
Worth the wait!! Chocolate chip pancakes are amazing, unlimited coffee refills, and waiter Corey was awesome!! Line moves quick.. wait it out!

I loved this place!! Service was bar none from the young lady taking orders and the young man preparing the food. I asked their favorite meal there the young man suggested the classic burger but prepared slightly different. He said don't worry, I'll take care of you. My first bite I knew he DID take care of me. It was so delicious!!! My head's down, mouth full, no time for talking (besides an inaudible murmurs of so good, yum and delicious)- gotta focus on killing this burger with no evidence left behind. Even if you're not vegan try this place. Everything plat based. Even the cups are made from plants. Gotta go back before I head home to California.

This place is unsanitary. I got a foot fungus from here which I had to see a doctor about for treatment. And my good friend witnessed a few of the nail techs washing towels in the foot baths instead of the washing machines. I will never go back and would encourage people to go elsewhere. Also, the parking is a nightmare and I've been blocked in before by other clients.

Ok so we finally made it to the Wesley Chapel location! The bar service was excellent! the food was good! The service was...stupid!
I don't mid paying 20.00 for fried chicken or scallops or pizza but when you take 35 minutes to serve 3 people at 9:30pm when the restaurant was down to 15 guest and 7 people in the kitchen, is not acceptable. My wife has never had Frangelico and coffee so I decided to order her one, epic fail! Coffee was stale to the point of overwhelming the Frangelico! Sad! And when I pointed it out to the manager who said I'll make a fresh pot, well I guess he did but forgot to serve it? So waitress #3 finally showed up with the coffee and Frangelico 45 minutes later we could careless at that point!
If you want to make it in the restaurant business service is everything! Your people need to be better trained and have there head in the game until closing not before but all the way to the end! You can deduct all of the items you want from a bill but if your service and food doesn't cut it your doomed!
We will give you a second chance but lets get it together and make it a goto restaurant in Wesley Chapel

Dont shop here... The furniture is crap... Breaks in less then a year... You will wait a month for the part and servive to find out wrong part sent and start all over... Customer service is horrible... 45 minute hold times

Before I share the main issue, I want to share the reason I give any stars is because of our awesome server, LaToya. She was thoughtful and engaging! 

The black bean burger was dry. Sweet potato fries were good. 

Today while at lunch with a group of colleagues the most disturbing thing happened. I noticed the manager in a green sweater lingering around the entrance and then two cop cars with lights flashing pulled up and 3 officers rushed in walked to the table next to us that the manager was pointing to and one of the officer's proceeded to pull out their handcuffs and tell the guy delivering food to put food down at the table and hands behind his back. They escorted him near the front door and had him sit down for a moment before taking him outside in freeZing cold with no jacket where he stood for a few minutes while cops came in and out of restaurant. 

This entire thing was poorly handled, disturbing and unsettling not only to the customers but the other staff. They should have had the cops walk back away from where customers were and deal with it there. Then all the managers disappeared not available to talk to any of the customers let alone apologize or acknowledge people being unsettled. 

No one needs to know why the arrest happened but there needed to be more care for customers and staff in how it was handled. 

Not ok!!!
Love this bakery!! Great breakfast sandwiches, coffee, and donuts! My friend and I love coming on weekend mornings

Beautiful restaurant on the water. Great drinks and delicious food makes you feel right at home. Loved drinking outside on the patio with good music and televisions. Definitely the perfect spot to spend my weekends!

Not a bad place for the price. Had the crab cakes and veggies.   I took several soccer players while at a tournament and there were so many options for everyone to chose from. Including kids with nut and wheat allergies.

This is a hidden gem in Kenner. The food is authentic and fresh. The restaurant ambience itself isn't what you go for... you go for the fresh authentic food. Recommended dishes: chicken shawarma, falafel, baba ganoush, and baklava. We've never disliked anything here.

Great place, great staff, great beer. The owners are always on site and are very welcoming. It's obvious to see how proud they are of their place and the process, for good reason! Many of the beers are on the lower abv spectrum (by today's imperial standards), but each is done with care to produce full bodied and fresh pint. The stout and porter are roasty and perfect for the Winter. They have a double IPA that packs a punch, and the rest of the ales are very well balanced...you can't go wrong here. Swing by for one or fifteen, you'll love it.
Surrey's is by far the best brunch go to! It's worth every second of the wait! Everything is always fresh, always good and every employee there is ALWAYS FRIENDLY!
This food was very good and the service was fast and friendly. A wide variety of dishes, chicken, beef and vegan.

We have more problems that tonight we have decided to not go back. Have it your way is a joke at this place. We have orders missed, made incorrectly. Today my wife ordered a Chicken sandwich, when we got home .....no sandwich, she decided to go back it was there, just wasn't put in our bag. One time we even got someone else's order........WE ARE DONE

NEVER again in my life will I go to any of the Dream Tea locations. Last week, my husband and I got two bubble tea drinks which caused us to get food poisoning. It was so bad we had to go to the hospital. I am currently pregnant and this could've seriously harmed my baby. I didn't even know you could get food poisoning from bubble tea but apparently it is possible because it happened. I would never recommend anyone to go there. If I could give a 0 star rating I would.

Stopped in here on a Friday awhile back. No one acknowledged me when walked into the store for a good 5 minutes. Finally the assistant manager came over to talk to me. I told him what I was looking for new wheels/tires for my Jeep. He said that the bolt pattern is rare (people change their wheels/tires on Jeeps all the time, so don't know what that was about), but said he could find me some wheels to fit. He also gave me some false information regarding the size of the wheels, saying I couldn't go with a certain size of rim, even though I know people with the same Jeep that have that size rim. Anyway, he took my number down & a few rim styles that I liked, & said he would call me back the following Monday after checking with the warehouse. He never called back. I finally called almost a month later, & he gave me three different rim style numbers & said to look them up on Google & see if I liked them. I did, but they were none of the styles I had looked at in the store. I called him back to tell him which one I liked since we hadn't even talked a price yet. I had told him I was on a budget, & wanted to stay under a certain price, preferably. He came back with a ridiculous price point that was way above what I said I wanted to spend, with no options for anything cheaper at all. Maybe the other RNR locations besides Fletcher are different. but I definitely will be looking elsewhere for rims/tires. I know this place is supposed to help people with poor credit, but they are really screwing people over if that's the service & prices they are offering.
