Meh, even drunk food can have standards. As always, this place is just okay with a stellar location. That parcel they pay for must be a fortune because it is in scenic downtown Boise. They're decently quick with an order on a slow, sparse early evening. It's simple burgers and topping. Apparently they're getting a milkshake maker soon?

One of our favorite places in STL. 
Gals night out Sat began w/Drinks, dinner & dessert at The Fountain before a show at the Fox.  Everyone was greatly satisfied!
And look forward to our next visit!!!
Really nice staff that made excellent recommendations.  Had a acai bowl and immune tea and the tea was brewed perfectly and the acai bowl was out of this world.   Highly recommend this place.

Upland Nachos

A coworker and I took off early on a Friday to enjoy shooting some guns at the local gun range and then enjoy some food and drinks nearby at Upland Brewery's Tap House in Carmel, IN. Upland Brewing Company is actually based out of Bloomington, IN but this tap house in Carmel is a nice little getaway as not only do they have delicious craft beer but great food too! On this particular visit we shared two dishes. This review is focused on the Upland Nachos with Pulled Pork.

To start my review let me begin with the APPEARANCE of this dish. I will be honest that my first thought was "Wow, that's a lot of tomatoes!" and the thought had crossed my mind that there was just way too many vegetables on this plate. As I look at the picture above and refresh my memory of the plate the look of the nachos is very eye appealing as the tomatoes have a fresh and vibrant red color and the placement of the fresh jalapenos really jumps out too.

Nachos are a tough dish to review because there's two main trains of thought on the cheese. One train says to use runny nacho cheese and pour it over all the chips and stuff. The second train says to use shredded cheese and melt it at the end. I tend to lean more towards the first train when it comes to nachos...nacho cheese that's gooey and sticky and that unique after taste that nacho cheese has over cheddar, mozzarella, or colby jack cheese. So putting my "preference" aside on how I like my nachos, the overall flavor profile of this plate is quite astonishing. The pulled pork topping is definitely a bonus, but the nachos by themselves without the pulled pork are still worth a taste. If you get a little bit of everything on a chip then it will EXPLODE your taste buds. The veggies are crisp, the chip is crunchy, you do taste the cheese, the black beans add a really good texture and a bit of a salty salivating left hook of flavor. Depending on if you have the jalapenos in the middle, bottom or top will determine when the heat and bite of the jalepeno come in but it's a great accent flavor to the bite. The pulled pork was more sweet than tangy for pulled pork which was a good compliment to the bite and heat of the jalapeno. The sides of guacamole, pico de galo, and sour cream are available if you'd like but it will make for a very messy chip if you try to get all three of those on top of what already usually comes on a chip.

The only "negative" I could come up with is a challenge that every order of nachos has...getting cheese on every chip. The chips on the bottom middle of the plate are always bare by the time I get to them. The struggle is real for the nachos out there...all the chips just aren't getting treated fairly. The ones on top get everything...but those on the bottom get nearly nothing besides the scraps the chips on top leave for them.

SUMMARY

Overall...the Upland Nachos at Upland Brewing Company Carmel Tap House are great for an individual or sharing with friends. Pair it with a nice craft beer of your choice and you've got great food, great drinks, great friends, and a great time!

I had been wanting to go here since it opened and I finally made it! Thankfully, yelp has the new handy reservation feature and I was able to make a reservation from the app just 30 min from when I looked. That gave me enough time to jump in the car and make it for my reservation! So simple and super useful on a Saturday night!

First off, the modern decor inside the historical building makes for lots of easy conversation. There are some really cool, old city planning maps and trendy butcher block table tops. I loved everything about it! 

I also loved that when I sat down, some very delicious cornbread fritters were delivered. They are so tasty and have the perfect amount of jalapeo kick balanced with a bourbon honey sauce. 

The cocktail menu is definitely worth making a couple visits for. I got an Albee's Knees and it was the bees knees! I'm not usually a fan of gin, but this cocktail was delicious!

We ordered an Artichoke, Cheese and Kale dip appetizer. It was heavenly! I would go back exclusively for the dip! It was served with fresh pita and was a great appetizer. 

I couldn't decide what to order for dinner, but landed on the shrimp tacos and was happy with my decision! The corn tortillas were very crispy, almost tostada like and the spicy slaw and cojita was perfect! I would definitely order them again.

I was too full to try any dessert, so I'm going to have to come back! The Mac and cheese bites are also calling to me, so it won't be long!

We had a great experience buying an engagement ring at Gossage. We had gone into half a dozen other stores, and neither the jewelry nor the service felt quite right. The rings were beautiful, but the service was phenomenal. The lovely lady that helped us (Kim) was not pushy but was very attentive. She was really good at pulling out ring after ring for me instead of just waiting for me to point out specific ones. I felt like I could take a close look at a wide variety of rings when I didn't know exactly what I wanted. She was also great at finding things at our price range; at one point I found a couple I liked that were too expensive, so she isolated similar ones that were cheaper. We got a same-day sizing on the ring for free. We had a fantastic experience, thank you!!
We really enjoyed this place. Good atmosphere, great staff, and delicious drinks & tapas. We had the scallops, chicken spring rolls, and charcuterie board. All fantastic!

So many wonderful choices on the menu made it hard to pick. We choose the Fruit & Yogurt Power Jar along with the Chicken Biscuit with City Grits. The food was very good, we had great service from Linda and I was amazed how clean the kitchen was since I got a good view whenever the enter door opened.u

I ordered delivery, food was an hour ad a half late and cold when it arrived. I was told they would be sending a free drink and dessert due to the tardiness, but those items never arrived. When I called to inquire, they said they would remake my order - though since it had been two hours since I originally ordered, I was not surprised nor did I care when that never arrived either. Food, service and punctuality were all terrible. I recommend spending your money elsewhere - this was the worst dining experience I've ever endured.

Visiting SB from the Midwest and after a long day in wine country, our host treated us to carry out Pizza Mizza.  All pies were tasty, but my favorite was the one with chicken, mushroom, and rosemary white sauce.  Not a combination I would have come up with, but they're the creative people.  Yum.
I believe the owner greeted me at the door. She was rude and threatened service if I didn't get gel. The quality received is not worth the price.

Fantastic, I repeat fantastic place to go for breakfast or brunch. We were steered here by 2 different locals, a bar tender and a fellow working in a hot sauce shop. The grits, andouille sausage, bacon were all perfect. The grits in particular.....we came back a few days later and had their breakfast burrata. It was spectacular. Deconstructed to its individual parts then allowing you to put each bite together however you like. So unbelievably good.......we will definitely be back next time in town!!

We had so much fun at this place! Lisa, Erika and and Sean  were phenomenal bartenders and really made our Saturday night the best. We will be bringing all our friends here to watch eagles games. Very friendly and makes you feel like home!
This place is the best and if you want healthy, hello it is guaranteed to be organic with many gluten free dishes. Check it out. You will not be disappointed.

This is probably my favorite trap and skeet club in the entire United States. Top-notch facilities, and top-of-the-line instruction from Tim Miles of Coyote Springs (he's the best in the business). Call Tim today and arrange for a lesson. You won't be sorry.

Excellent tasty hamburgers and especially their steak fajitas.
Very friendly service. Great bargains in drink at happy hour.

So disappointed...pho broth was just ok and they really skimped out on the beef brisket. My husband's bahn mi pork sandwich was mostly bread again with very little meat. We've had much better bahn mi and pho in Philly/NY/NJ area and were excited to try the local Vietnamese influence. Sadly did not live up to the hype.

Overall I thought it was a great experience. Service was a bit slow, but the bartenders were doing a good job. Burgers were tasty and fresh. I would definitely recommend this place to try. I would go back for sure the next time I am in the STL.

Stopped in to check out this new spot around the corner from us, as my boyfriend has been anticipating its opening for quite some time. Can I say it- FINALLY! Am amazing place for sushi in the city. We were there for what they were calling their soft opening, where apparently they are testing out menu and cocktail items for their "official" opening sometime soon. We were very pleased with the ambiance, service and food/drink. The fish is top quality. We said hello to the owner/executive chef and he seemed to be beaming over his accomplishments, rightfully so! This is a must stop if you're a sushi/Asian fusion fan. We look forward to seeing what's in store for Tuna Bar and are thrilled to have this a two minute walk away!
Stoped in for lunch and ordered the crunchy fish sandwich & fries. The waiter was professional and polite. Cant remember his name but never the less the entire meal was worth it.
Gelato was amazing, light and creamy and full of flavor, very similar to ones sold at famous/popular gelato places in Italy.
YUM! Great dinner, our service Gabby was Awesome! Grilled fish delish, fried shrimp to die for, bone appetite.

Don't be deterred by the exterior - this place is definitely a diamond in the rough.

All around super impressed by the quality of the food and service. Got the chirashi bowl which was amazing and extremely fresh with a wide variety of fish. Was especially fond of the salmon as this was some of the best I've had in a while. Nice to see great sushi outside of the city. 

Pro Tip: make a reservation ahead of time to avoid waiting as this place only has a handful of tables.

Best meal enjoyed when traveling to Tennessee. Smart eclectic flavors make the sandwiches a real hit. I loved the smoked turkey and a side of the roasted carrots. Finished off with the apple ricotta cake perfect indulgence without the guilt. 

Cool interiors, too.

I come here often.  My little mexican mom enjoys the food and the pleasant servers.  My wife always likeds coming here as well.  I love the soups.  They have a variety of soups, I have tried them all.  Authentic flavors , like my abuelitas.  Very good mexican comfort food. As well as sonoran seafood.  Mmm mmm.

Maybe this place is still new.. I don't know.. I'll give it a few months and go back to see. I got a burrito bowl... Gave me one scoop of rice..  and one scoop of everything .. I know I can ask more but man I'm not about to say it for everything. I expect a little more when I'm paying $9  . I'll  just have to drive over to the one in Voorhess cause I love Chipotle ! ... They know what's up lol

Normally have a decent meal here but last night was a clusterf***....  had to ask for butter for our rolls, the salads came out before the appetizer?, my steak came out without sides and was told they are out of mashed potatoes .... would be nice to know this when I order or maybe have the cook make some.... my girlfriends steak was undercooked and she stressed it needs to be well done, sent it back and still came back medium .... though the food was decent the service was a step above fast food at best.....  maybe if people should take some pride in their work there would be less complaints and a business would prosper even more....

My sister and I were visiting Arizona all the way from the east coast and our aunt and uncle brought us for breakfast today. Our server, Alma, was out of this world. She had an amazing, positive, and outgoing personality. From the moment we sat down, we felt at ease and comfortable. Her sense of humor kept us entertained and feeling welcome.  We couldn't asked for a better and more upbeat personality.  She definitely deserves positive accolades from all who work with her.  We can't wait to visit again! On top of this, the food here is phenomenal!

Great place to go with both your friends and/or family. You get your food very fast, you never have to wait even during their busiest hoirs. The staff works very fast and is very friendly and welcoming to their customers. I visit the bar weekly, because I always enjoy my time there, along with my food and drinks.
We are from out of town here on vacation. We really enjoyed the restaurant and the fish tank display. There is a lot of interesting Guy Harvey merchandise up front also.
The staff is wonderful, the coffee is great, and the concept is different. An Indonesian cafe right in the heart of fishtown!

Amazing food and service. Excellent EXO coffee. 
Vegetarian and gluten free options. Highly recommended!!
I used the app to put our party on the wait list and by the time we arrived we were seated In under 10 minutes. 
What a gem of a place!!

I was really good pizza and wings. I would definitely come back. We came with kids and it was ok. I guess it depends on what you have in mind for the atmosphere. There's a lot of tvs so with kids it can be distracting but that's what people are there for to watch a game and eat pizza. Overall good and definitely good food.

This was my first visit to a Giordano's outside of the Chicago area and it was the same experience you get in Chicago! There's no higher praise I can offer. The decor is industrial. Service was great.

We went on a Friday night after a movie downtown. It was mostly, but not entirely full. We were seated quickly and ordered right away since the stuffed pizzas take 40 minutes.

We had a BBQ Chicken pizza and a sausage pepperoni pizza, both small deep dish pizzas. They were great! They offer sandwiches, pasta, and salad in addition to the famous pizzas.

I came in, and although parking was small, it was easy to find a space. I walked into a modern, cozy little shop with high ceilings. I asked the very sweet and adorable barista what was popular and told her it was my first time in. I was recommended and received a DELICIOUS peppermint holiday drink with a little almond milk and peppermint pieces on the whipped cream -- I didn't catch the drink's name. I also got a really moist and delicious slice of lemon pound cake. I highly recommend this place and asking the baristas what's good!

The best Chinese food I have ever had. I never ate inside here but have had takeout a couple of times. My boyfriends family has turned me onto this place and our go to entrees are the honey walnut shrimp and the beef with toffee - both are delicious but I like the shrimp the best. The shrimp are huge and the honeyed walnuts are delectable. Their prices are higher than your average Chinese restaurant, but it is so worth it because of the quality. The man at the counter - he may have been the owner - was very friendly and appreciative of our business. I wish this place was closer to me.

Had a grilled chicken sandwich on bun to go. Couldn't hold sandwich due to bottom bun being soggy.  So I decided to just eat the meat.  I saw a piece of hair as I removed the meat. I haven't ate there in years and will not eat there again.  Zero stars from me.

Great haircut, reasonable price, friendly barber!! Highly recommended.

Went in to see Randy after reading such rave reviews, and they are accurate! I went in on a Saturday morning, wait was an hour but was worth it. He understood what I wanted done and did it very well. 

Also as an added bonus he's got a friendly pooch and some sweet vintage bikes sitting around, quite a unique haircut experience!

Alaska Airlines rocks, mostly tight to schedule and always nice and friendly. Can't wait for affiliate Sky West to replace CRJ's with Embraer 175's but flight is short so not a huge deal. I'll fly AS every time!

The customer service was horrible. I called to place an order for pick up. The kids menu was not posted online so I asked the lady who answered for the kids menu. She proceeded to tell me that she was too busy to tell me and placed me on hold. However, she didn't realize that I could still hear her. She proceeded to complain that someone was on the phone asking her to read the entire menu and she didn't have time. I told her to cancel the order and I drove up there. When I got there and asked to speak to a manager, I discovered that the person who answered the phone was the manager. I have never experienced such rude and unprofessional customer service. RUDE RUDE RUDE!

I visit the pint room often for work outings. It's always a nice atmosphere and their food never disappoints. I enjoy the fact you can order a flight of beer and try four different kinds. It makes It easier to bring large work groups here since everyone try different beers. I will say If you're going ask for opinions or questions about the beer to sit at the bar. Several times I've asked the servers and they rarely know about the beers but every time I ask the bartender they can describe them.

We dropped by 21st Amendment for some late-night cocktails in French Quarter without going to the rowdier spots. Given that this was close to where we were staying (the Marriott), it was easy to pop out and roll over to 21st Amendment, which was only a few minutes away. There wasn't a line outside, but it was packed by the time we made it inside (sometime between 10-11 PM)...standing-room only, with the seats at the high-top tables and the bar taken. The decor and ambiance is a bit more retro, but like all New Orleans spots in this fashion, it feels homey, and it was enhanced by the fact that the band in the bar playing live music was absolutely entrancing the audience, with some folks even doing some dancing right at the front.

That said, I did come here initially because it was rated highly for drinks, and on that front, the cocktails do not disappoint. The bartenders make the drinks expertly, whether you stay on-menu or stray off by giving some general preferences. The beer selection is more generic, with specific bottles being the big-label brands, and no names given for listings like 'seasonal' or 'IPA'. Nonetheless, the drinks are made quickly but consistently - something I appreciated given how busy it was that night. Pricing was reasonable, relatively speaking - $13 a cocktail is a bit expensive, but the quality was very good, making it a bargain compared to some places in New York that I have been to.

21st Amendment really has a nice cozy feel to it, and with great drinks and great music, it's hard to go wrong. It doesn't have the kind of 'fun' you'd find half a block over on Bourbon Street, but at my age, it's the kind of fun that I'd rather have. Definitely worth a visit if you are in the area.

Having a 10 year old that prefers Taco Bell quesadillas to anything else makes having a meals out a daily negotiation...
So on our way bowling at Pinsetters she suggested we eat there while bowling.. Their food actually isn't bad for a bowling alley. But that was far from what I wanted my first meal of the day to be..  So my bookmarks showed that we were close to Turning Point, and the debate ended... They closed at 3, and we walked in at 2. Plenty of time to have brunch.. She chose the OMG French Toast. That came loaded with candied pecans and chopped bacon. I went with the Huevos Rancheros... Both we're very good choices. Her dish was, well, sweet!! What else would you expect out of a 10 year old... My dish was great. It was huge... I thought I was hungry, so I ate the whole thing.... Savory and spicy.. Avocados and sour cream on the side to balance the meal... I enjoyed this meal so much that I needed a nap in Pinsetters parking lot before going in....  The service at Turning Point was attentive, but not overbearing. The menu offered plenty of dishes with enough of a twist to not make it the norm, as if you were at an average restaurant or diner. 
I don't really remember how this place got into my bookmarks. But I'm glad that it was there when I needed it.

I was very disappointed. I called on Thursday to inquire about picking up 2 boxes of Buntini's on Friday. I was told that there are no more Buntini's . They are only selling cakes or buntletts .
I ordered a cake . When I went to pick it up, I heard them say they have Buntini's!
When it was my turn, I explained what I was told .the woman who was explaining it appeared to be in charge. I asked her to at least talk to whoever made that error so that they might not disappoint another customer.  She said she would, but at no time did I feel that she was apologetic for their part of this misunderstanding.  To top it off, my red velvet cake was very dry.
Not a big fan of this store right now .
You all reached out to me on yelp after reading 
This post. If I could reply I would 

In the meantime you have my info  you could reach out to me if you thought of rectifying this

This restaurant was so accommodating in getting us in off the rainy street quickly.  Server named Lydia and she was a Gem!  Great smile, friendly and quick!  Exactly what we needed in game day!
If your in the neighborhood stop in and ask for her!
Food was Ihop at its best.  Good experience!

Love this place! Almost all of their menu items can be made vegan. They are super knowledgeable. The Pad Thai with tofu, veggies, and cashews is perfection. The avocado egg rolls are amazing too! A favorite.
The duck was imitation duck not the real thing. The fried rice was good, I was just highly dissatisfied with receiving a pricey fake version of duck.

Met a friend here over Christmas holiday. 
I was immediately a fan of the relaxed and creative ambiance. 

I N T E N T I O N A L I T Y.

The word that best describes Room 901. From the decor, to the drink list, the owner, Peg, has worked tirelessly to create a Whiskey Bar that celebrates the brown liquid through and through. The pours have all been carefully curated for those looking to enjoy all that whisk(e)y has to offer. Her passion really shines here. Would absolutely recommend to anyone who's a fan of fine distilled spirits. Will absolutely be making the trip back to visit the next time I'm in town.

Haven't had Thai food this good, this cheap, and this bountiful in a long time. Small but cozy shop and I love the Polaroids they have on the wall with customer reviews! I had the pangang curry with chicken for $10 (comes with white rice). Got full on about half of it, took the rest home and had it for lunch the following day. The food is served to you in to-go style Tupperware so it's perfect for leftovers. Can't wait to visit this restaurant again and try their lunch bentos!

We went on a quiet Sunday evening and sat at the bar. Service was great. We ordered the bacon fat French fries as an appetizer. They came out hot and crispy and delicious. I ordered the posole and the cornbread which went great together. The posole was better than my dads (don't tell him!). My husband ordered the fried chicken which came with collard greens and coleslaw. It was all perfectly delicious. We will be back.

New brewery: beers are hit or miss but better than I expected for the first few tries.  Small but has a nice feel and very clean cut. Crowded but it's just opened probably a good sign ! iPas better than expected. Will come back to check out new beers as they grow. Welcome addition to Haddonfield

Stopped in for dinner, and we had a fantastic experience. The service was pleasant, the food delicious plus the atmosphere was very welcoming. Mike the owner, said hello to us and just made us feel very at home. We will be back!

This place was disgusting! We used to eat here quite a bit but it sure has gone downhill fast! The place was dirty (garbage cans overflowing, garbage left on tables because the garbage cans couldn't be used). Nothing was filled up (sauce cups, napkins, silverware). The chicken was very dry and couldn't even be cut with the plaatic knife! Well it was good while it lasted but they have seen the last of me!

I wish I can rate them without a star. I am currently here at The Inn at Opryland, A Gaylord Hotel, we have been here since Wednesday Dec 27, 2017. It was Friday night (Dec 29, 2017), came back from a long trip got to our room and they did not clean the room, NO one clean our room. We called the front desk and we spoke to a man, called himself the "manager" and instead of rectifying the situation, blaming us that we are at fault, because we left the sign on (DO NOT DISTURB). We did not have signed on at all. We wanted them to clean the room since we are going to be gone for the whole day and we place was really a mess when we left. The manager did not even apologize for their mistakes. We also did not have any clean towels to used. The management was arguing rather than fixing the problem. Today is Dec 30th, I went out of the door to find a housekeeper, one was walking in the hallway and I asked her a questions about our room, and she said "sorry me no speak English" I knew she was lying. I should have called ICE (homeland investigation for undocumented).

I am writing this review because The Inn at Opryland only wants your money, they don't care about you. They don't care about your concern. until now no one came to clean and bother on our concern. I am from California, San Francisco Bay Area, this is my first and last time here. I was charge $249 a night and double during New Years. THIS IS A CRAP HOTEL. It is noisy, very small tub and bathroom. I DO NOT RECOMMEND THIS PLACE, go to Hyatt, Hampton, Holiday Inn Express, but NEVER HERE... STAY AWAY.
I liked that it is run by the local community. Their selection of films is outstanding, and the projection and sound quality were very high.

Another great taco place near USF! The menu is easy to read and if you have any questions, the employees are very helpful in answering them. I wanted to try everything but had to control myself so I went for a tostada and and three tacos. 

The service is super fast. As soon as we sat down, we were already given our waters and within 5 minutes, our food followed. Both dishes came out extremely fresh and hot. The tostada's ingredients were layered together to create a perfect bite. The beans, cheese, and vegetables complimented each other so well with the crispy base. The tacos weren't as impressive but they were still yummy. I wasn't a big fan of the corn tortillas because it was kind of bland and chewy. The carne asada meat was flavorful but the lengua (beef tongue) had an iron/gamey taste unlike most other Mexican places. The sauces that are given on the table were really flavorful, the red sauce had a smokey peppery taste while the green one (extremely hot) had a citrus/jalapeo like mixture. 

The restaurant is very clean, has plenty of seating, and I definitely will be back to try the other menu items!

We came to the District Tavern for a quick bite before a concert at the Amalie. We sat at the bar and the bartender was friendly and helpful. 
It was around 6 pm, so we reached for the happy hour menu (4-7 pm M-F).  Both my friend and I got the Tavern Jalapeo Margarita. I think this is my new favorite drink! Slightly spicy with charred lemon and unique deep flavor. Most importantly- not sweet! Perfection!
We shared the sandwich shooters. They are the only reason I'm not giving it 5 stars. I had higher expectations. The tomato bisque was kinda bland, and the baguettes were not anything to write home about. For my main entree i had the Southwest bowl- delicious! Great flavors, generous portion and nice presentation. My friend got the district salad with salmon and she was very happy with her choice too. I'd definitely come back again for the jalapeo margarita and to try something else on the menu. 
Tip-you can take the Downtowner to and from here!

This is the worst place to eat! I love barbecue and the pulled pork was so dry I had to drown it in barbecue sauce to try and eat it! The wings were so dry, the collard greens were so bland that I had to put buffalo sauce and salt to make them taste somewhat decent. The food came out slow and we were starving. It was edible, that's about it! Had to place a order to go at tarpon tavern because I was still hungry after eating what little I had!

This is the worst delivery experience I've ever had. I was a delivery driver for another Domino's for 5 years during college, so I know that things can get hectic, but this was ridiculous. Ordered online at 11:00pm, tracker said it would be delivered in 25-35 minutes. At 12:00am, the pizza had still not arrived so I called the store. They said mine was the next one out the door and should be there in a few minutes, because I live about 1 mile away from the store. At 1:00am, still no pizza. I call again and they said the driver left with my order and another order 30 minutes ago, and instead of driving to my house first, which was 1 MILE AWAY, he went to the other house first which was further away, and gave them their pizza AND MY PIZZA. They offered to make a new one and send it out, but I didn't want to wait up until 3 in the morning, so I said no thanks. They offered a free pizza on my next order, but that doesn't do anything to help me right now because it too late to order from anywhere else. This is why Uber Eats and other forms of food delivery will end up crushing stores like this. So to whoever runs this store, seriously, congratulations. You've just won the award for worst store in the franchise.
why did you burn the building down that was my favorite pizza place. I know you guys wanted to vacation but you don't have to burn it down. whatever now I have to eat pasta Mista

I've been here two times and I love it -- the shawarma bowls are so good and the chicken is tender. The pita is pillowy and soft, the naf fries are perfection!! The whole meal + fries came out to only about 11 dollars, and I left feeling full with some to take home. The food is delicious and fresh, definitely worth a try if you're looking for vegetarian/healthy options.

Ordered food at noon. Waited 55 minutes for two salads. Friend ordered House Salad, when it arrived it was spring mix, red onions, cucumbers. No cheese, bacon, tomatoes, pecans. When questioned, response was "the chef changed it." Without asking the customer?? And to what....the only items we have prepped? Asked for the manager but was told she was in the kitchen.  Guess that sums it up. Obviously will never go back. 
One day later UPDATE: A marketing team member reached out to apologize and offered complementary meal as his personal guests should we want to try again. Hope this is indicative of a team trying to right the ship. Stay tuned.

Came to Sierra Car Care to get an oil change. Was offered buy one get one free. Upon realizing it needed an engine flush, was quoted free oil change with their coupon for engine flush that was cheaper than the oil change. These guys were very thorough and gave me good advice on things I asked about that I know needs to be taken care of. They were very kind and helpful and not pushy or try to sell me what I don't need. I will definitely come back to them with my truck care needs.

Ordered the Edamames, The Saint Sushi Roll and the veggie tempura(lil greasy).. My sister ordered the shrimp and and grits. Everything was excellent. Unfortunately the greasy tempura didn't agree with her...

I was lucky enough to get Erin for my blow dry.  I am new to the area and wasn't sure what I would get, but was so pleasantly surprised by the nice people and also Erin's blow dry.  Not to mention the lady who washed my hair massaged my head amazingly!I bought the pack of four and will definitely be going back.  A great little spot and reading the other reviews I will use Erin for other services like cuts and colors as well.  If you are on the fence, definitely go and get Erin.

Last couple of visits food has been average at best. Food served on bare metal tray and luke warm. Mac and cheese tasty but cold. Sweet tea so sweet it leaves an after taste in your mouth. Pretty bummed as this was one of my favorite bbq places when visiting last school year.

My family and I made a quick trip to New Orleans to take the kids to a Saints game and soak up some culture. I was disappointed that Camellia Grill's line was out the door.  Even though it's not the same since Katrina and Marvin passing, I still wanted my kids to see my old stomping ground. 

Anyway, this place was open and ready to seat us. I did a quick yelp & the stars indicated that it was a go. It was a Sunday and were told that they were only serving brunch which was a dealbreaker for me. Another waitress quickly corrected the situation & gave us the lunch menu. Our party of seven was seated on the balcony which is always a treat. 

Now to the food: The food was amazing! I had the chicken Cordon Bleu. It was panned to perfection & covered in an amazing cream sauce!  I let others sample and everybody agreed that it was delicious. My son had the chicken Parmesan (he did not share but he's a picky eater and scarfed it down), my other kid order from the brunch menu.. maybe eggs with crabcakes.. it disappeared too fast to actually see it . There were also couple of sausage/beef burgers at the table.  

But the highlight (for us adults) was the $5 bloody Marys. They were deliciously spicy with extra horseradish. They could have used some extra garnishes but the bloody Mary itself couldn't have been better.

All in all it was a great experience and the lunch menu is definitely a good value!

Came here for breakfast + drinks based on Yelp! Reviews. I love that there's plenty of parking in front and in the back for free. Woo! There's plenty of seating inside which is refreshing and their staff is quick to greet customers. 

We ordered a cap, a tea latte and two breakfast options. My tea latte was delicious and I'd definitely recommend it. Sean's cappuccino had latte art which we loved, but it tasted like a wet latte, and lacked micro foam outside of a very thin layer on top. 

If you're picky about your cappuccino's, keep this in mind, as we ordered and paid for two and both came out the same. A little disappointing but we learned.

Besides that, I can't really recommend the breakfast menu items even though everyone posted photos of them. The breakfast sandwich was super small and didn't have a ton of flavor. The breakfast burrito tasted like day-after leftovers that was in some gravy base. 

In all, if you're looking for a quick place that has easy parking and lots of seating (plus charging stations for the win) this is a great option. But if you're looking to grab breakfast somewhere, I'd suggest coming here for the tea only.
This is the absolute best ice cream I've ever had. Get the homemade ice cream in the waffle ones that they make in-house!

Hits and misses for me. The harvest greens were crisp and fresh and had a tasty dressing, but it was a bit too much, and the blue cheese and candied pecans didn't work terribly well together. The mushroom pot pie filling was wonderfully rich and creamy, with such interesting spices, but the pastry was too tough to cut with my knife and fork. The 7-minute egg was delicious, but the Brussels sprouts were too salty. They have an extensive wine list, though, which surprised me, given it's a beer place. The service was friendly and efficient. It's a bit awkward walking in from the hotel side. There's no hostess station and it feels a bit unfriendly until you catch someone's eye.
Fun place with a great vibe. Doesn't hurt that I just received the best manicure and gel polish I've ever had. Awesome!

We didn't really feel the love here. First off, we were greeted by an unenthusiastic waitress who was very cold and short with all of us. We started off by ordering 3 apps: the pierogies, crispy duck salad and cheese board. All of these items were delicious, however the portions of the cheese were completely underwhelming. Four people were suppose to share the cheese board. While the presentation was cute with the mouse shaped goat cheese, the portions of the individual cheeses seemed as if they were fit for a mouse! Each person basically got a crumb of cheese to taste. Moving on to the entrees, two of us ordered the scallops, one person ordered the lamb and another ordered the beef stroganoff. The scallops were good, but the best dish was the beef. We have dined all over the city and the country. The aspect about The Love that left us with the poorest taste in our mouth was the fact that this place charges $1 per person for water (still or sparkling). Mind you, it's not bottled still or sparkling, it's super filtered Philadelphia water. To top it off, there is no complimentary bread or rolls served. You must pay $5 for the Parker house rolls with chive butter, which, in my opinion, were not worthy of the price tag. Overall, the food was good, not great and we do not plan to recommend or return. At $200 per couple, these ancillary charges made us feel as though we were being nickeled and dimed.

A new go to spot! Ordered take out and was very happy with how my meal held up during the transport. The guacamole is definitely a must, along with the mango chicken taco. The taco menu has a great variety-which means I will have to go back again to try them all. :) The staff was friendly and helpful, I look forward to eating in and getting the full experience.
The food is ok but  service is too bad. I think I will give them ZERO STAR if I can. I dont know the women who is at front desk is boss or manager but she is so weird and rude..

Best breakfast ever.  Haven't had a kolache since we moved from Texas and the sausage one here did not disappoint!  The most amazing thing was the brle cinnamon roll OMG....best cinnamon roll I've ever had.  We debated whether the Uber ride from the hotel would be worth it but I can assure you it was and we will probably find our way back again tomorrow!

Stopped for breakfast ... service was quick and pleasent ...  Food was really good, bacon panini and loved the potatoes it comes with.  They also don't feel the need to charge extra for soda instead of coffee ... I'm good with that
Like University of New Orleans engineering better. No discount for first responders. You have to wait in line for a time limit on a machine because everyone is hogging up their time.

Been there three times. First time wasn't so bad, second time took my son and his fianc and my wife. We all ordered at the same time but we all are at different times. The kitchen couldn't get our food out together. On a $150 bill I was a little disappointed. Manager caught wind of our issue through FB and told us to come back and drop her name and they would take care of us so we did just that. 
The food took 45 mins and was cold. The reason was they forgot we were there and bypassed our order to serve later customers. The poor waitress didn't get to find out I tip in $20 intervals meaning if the service is great I'll throw an extra twenty on top of the tip. I appreciate good hard working employees and waitressing isn't easy at all. Underrated really. 
There's some guest that grace restaurants with eating at those establishments. 
It's bad for business when you can't meet a basic standard. 
Our standard is high. This restaurant is not to par.
Sound "Snooty"? No. Basic expectations aren't Snooty and if a person considers it snooty then it shows how low the standard is for them. 
It's ok to expect your food within 45 mins. Of ordering. It's ok to expect the food to all come out at same time. 
It's a gamble to eat at Sams. Gamble my people won't take again.

Met a family and my daughter 6 of us...ordered drinks then food , came out awesome and fast!!!! I'm impressed, the servers assist each other and I couldn't have asked for a better experience.

The wings were fat and meaty like they should be,  unlike what you get at Hooters now, they need to go to the same vendor as Glory Days ....Duh??

I did not stay in this hotel, however I went with family to enjoy the Christmas events there. The place is gorgeous!!!! They prepare everything in details with attraction to children. This year Charles Brown Christmas was a theme. Just a little pricey. You still have time to enjoy there.
Amazing hospital, amazing staff, beautiful facilities, I can't say enough wonderful things about this hospital. Best in the area for children's care. Highly recommended!

Let me start by saying the food was "Amaaazing" we had the Duck Duck Rice, and the shrimp and Grits, corn and crab soup, shrimp and crab stuffed oysters, French 75 cocktail, apple fall dumpling, and a chocolate tort.

Luke has a great atmosphere the ambiance was very nice. Our server Gary was on point, and was excellent with all of his recommendations and conversation and the same goes for the manager.

 I believe her Name was Elizabeth though we had dinner there on 12/29/17, so it's been a few days....so sorry if I didn't get her name right. Gary and Elizabeth made the experience very enjoyable for us and our little service dog. We will definitely go back, everything on the menu looked appetizing.
AMAZING........we ordered the xl quesadilla and an assortment of tacos. Best Mexican food we have found in Tampa. Reminds us of the Mexican food tents in south Tucson AZ. We will be back!!!

Came to New Orleans to visit and eat as much sea food as possible, so I went to Luke...randomly picked the place..didn't know what to eat but stuffed oysters sounded good so here I was 1/2 dozen stuffed oysters..shortly after I figured how to eat them (with the spoon to get all of it, as the manager said) there were none left!!! So good

Visiting the Tampa/Sarasota area the last 4 days, I ate out for breakfast, lunch, and dinner daily. This was singlehandedly the best place I ate. Authentic food (I ate with 2 middle eastern friends and they confirmed), friendly service, and delicious authentic homemade meals. I ordered the chicken shawarma entree which came with 2 sides, along with vegetables and pita, friend ordered the beef shawarma and the other friend ordered the shawarma sandwich (all pictured). Only thing I noticed was the lack of tea options when there are countless teas served in the Middle East. I got their mint tea (only option) which was decent but I could've made it at home (mint leaves and tea packet). Great place.

The Wine Tap has a great line up of beer and wines.  I love the atmosphere here too.  Its a quiet wine bar with an old world feel.  Their food menu is pretty limited, mainly to brick fire pizzas and meat/cheese plates but its not advertising itself as a restaurant so that's okay.  Their back patio has a retractable roof so its open year round regardless of the weather.  Come on that's kind of cool!

What's holding me back from giving them a 5 star review is their waitstaff.  Sometimes they're hard to track down and none of the are educated on their wine and beer menu.

Chose this as an out of towner looking for a good delivery place to our hotel. Ordered delivery and was brought timely. Shrimp Alfredo was outstanding and was the best thing we ordered! Pizza and bread sticks were both good as well.

Takeout service: I've ordered takeout of the Chicago deep dish pizza on a number of occasions. Each time has been on point with timing estimates - the usual 45 minutes.

Interiors - as the other reviews will tell you, this location is under renovation. I applaud that, as it appears it needed a facelift, and they're achieving that.

Chicago Deep Dish - the closest to true deep dish I've had, outside of Chicago. I always order the pizza with sausage; call it reminiscing my college days in Chicago! The cheese and crust are just what you should expect form a good deep dish pizza. Their sauce, although a rich blend of spices, is all their own, and "distinct" as Black Thorn's Dave has stated in some of these reviews.

In short, give this neighborhood spot a shot!
This is an update to the review I posted in July. Since then my family has returned several times, and the food and the service have been fine. Needless to say, we will keep going back.

If you need a cute place to grab a drink and some food at the bar this is the place. It's very small for the kind of restaurant/bar it is so it's not ideal for large groups but a small group of 2-4 can be seated at one of their few tables. This also isn't a great place for people with any kind of hearing issues because it got quite loud on a Friday night when I stopped in with my mom after a movie. 

If it's just two of you (or you're solo) this is probably a great spot to have a conversation with someone you know well over some very interesting menu items. My mom loved her "Bee Charmer" cocktail with lavender-infused gin, honey, and a few other ingredients. She liked it so much she asked the bartender for the recipe but the key ingredient, the gin, takes two days to soak in lavender before it's drained and ready to be used. 

They have a decent beer selection but nothing particularly impressive. They have a few local brews from the area but this place is definitely known for its inventive cocktails.

We'll be back to try their famous burger but our appetizers of fried pickles (thick but crisp and fresh) and an adult version of pigs in blanket were tasty and worth ordering again although I liked the pickles more. Our visit was cut short for outside reasons but I would recommend this place for close friends, established couples or a couple of family members. It's moderately to expensively priced but something to try out for yourself if you're looking for something a little different.

Very nice korean bibimbap on the go. 
It's a small menu so it's great for people that wanna come and look at a simple menu in front of ur face and go.
I do like the japchae, but it was half the box. And do they mean by "vegetable" japchae because there wasn't any meat.
But in my opinion, you get what you pay for the beef bibimbap.
The vegetables and rice did not even fill up half of the height of the take out bento box. The marinated beef was good though.

I was full but it's not enough for a male tummy FYI.

Unfortunately they don't take reservations.  It was a crazy busy weekend and took about an hour to be seated.
Sat on porch behind bar, they had propane heaters so it was plenty warm despite 15 degree weather.
Service was very attentive and friendly.  Food was great. Shasito peppers were perfect. Cauliflower was good and smoking hot spicy.
Glad we waited.
Food was just mediocre. Nothing was hot just warm. We are not beer drinkers so probably not a great place if you prefer wine.

Not authentic Korean. I ordered the Hwe Dup Bap - Sashimi yesterday and it was a bit basic. The fish was not plentiful but tasted ok. Unfortunately my stomach started convulsing after 10-15 minutes of eating this. It got really messy and I passed out on the bathroom floor in cold sweat for an hour. This happened only one other time for Philly restaurants and that place (Pho-ladelphia) was closed for sanitary reasons. Not saying this place wasn't fresh but just sayin'... mighty Fishy! Two stars instead of one since I'm giving Southgate the benefit of the doubt but I have no doubt in my mind I suffered food poisoning.

I first got into La Colombe coffee from the cans they sell at the supermarket but this was my first time at a store.  I tried the triple shot draft latte and it was so smooth and light and even better than the can when you drink it on tap.  I also tried the Black and Tan which is half latte and half black cold brew coffee and it was good too but I prefer the latte.  They have coffees and sell some pastries but I'm coming back for more lattes.

Cornell and Nicole are great.  Funny and personable.  In terms of personal training it is very personal.  Exercises are goal directed and they go at your pace. Hours are really flexible. I work late so being able to go at 7 or 8 pm is great.  They also are very understanding of last minute changes and are happy to reschedule. They are open on weekends and will also do Skype or give me home regimens when I'm out of town or can't make it.  Gym is clean.  They vary the workouts so it never gets boring. And unlike big chains you don't feel cheated or taken advantaged of or some faceless customer.  I already convinced some of my family to also attend. They do couple or friend/group sessions too.  They have different packages for at little as 1 month to much longer if desired.
Omg!, so good!, this place rocks!, super clean, great food, good service, nice people, food came out fast, great bar with big TVs , bathrooms clean! Thanks guys!

What everyone else said about this laundromat is true: it is exceedingly clean, well kept, safe, priced right and the people who work here are friendly and helpful. What more can you want from a laundromat?

I came here to get my duvet washed. I could have washed it here myself, but as someone smarter than me recently said: "Ain't no one got time for that." So I dropped it off with the friendly launderette who was sitting at the counter. She took my info, told me when I could pick it up, and asked me what kind of detergent to use. (She listed off like five different kinds. I chose unscented Tide.) Three hours and $19 dollars later, I have a clean, fresh, nicely folded duvet ready to be put back on my bed. My clean duvet also came in a nice plastic bag with a handle. It's a dang miracle, I tell you.

If my washer and dryer ever conk out, this will be the place I visit to wash and dry my laundry. In the mean time, I like knowing that I have a place where I can drop off random things that are too big for my washer, and they will come back sparkling (and it won't cost me a fortune).

I've been here 5-6 times over the last couple years. I stay at the pear tree inn when going to Barnes Jewish so it's pretty convenient. The food is above average and I've always had great service. I do not like the signature wing sauce, it's very musterdy. But, everything else is good and the homemade marinara sauce is out of this world.
I'm a coffee lover and this place has the BEST LATTE ever!!!! We had hot latte and my boyfriend had iced vanilla latte. He likes his vanilla latte and I LOVED my hot latte!

Just wait the hour for a table.  The wait staff are so kind and the food is amazing!  Perfect place to stop at if you're visiting from out of town like we were.  Hands down the best brunch experience I've ever had

I stopped by with my family on a Sunday afternoon--middle of the day.  Perfect time to go if you don't want to wait for a table.  I really liked the casual atmosphere.

We were greeted right away and our server was quick to bring us our drinks.  I went with the Bear Creek Farm Classic Burger and a side salad to be just a wee bit healthy.  The burger was awesome.  I usually don't finish burgers but this one went down fast.  I tried some of the sweet potato fries that a family member got.  I can't say that I loved them.  The taste was good but the texture...not so much.  Too limp and undercooked for my taste.

But I did not go to Burger Up for the fries.  I went for a burger and will definitely be back.

Food: 2 / 5 Stars

The Breakfast Poutine: (4 / 5 Stars) The real highlight of today's brunch was my friend's Breakfast Poutine - I stole a few bites. The Poutine had a rich flavor and was very satisfying. 

The Duck Confit: (? / 5 Stars) Did not try but was told that the dish tasted great. 

Smoked Salmon Beni: (0 / 5 Stars) Although I was looking forward to my dish, the Smoked Salmon Beni was a huge disappointment. Not only was the salmon in small supply, it tasted like over-cooked frozen salmon rather than smoked salmon as advertised (definitely not a deal with the $12.00 price tag that comes along with it). Even though the eggs, potatoes, and other fixings of the dish tasted great, the core aspect of the dish was severely lacking - especially compared to the other items ordered at the restaurant. I was able to use hot sauce to mask the flavor of the fish. 

------------------------------------------------

Location: (Not a factor in the rating)

Prep & Pastry is a very nice and aesthetic looking restaurant. There are a lot of places to park even if the lot is full and we only waited about 30 min on a Holiday Sunday at noon. 

------------------------------------------------

Service: 5 / 5 Stars

The servers were very nice and accommodating at the restaurant. Additionally, they were thorough on ensuring that the kitchen staff was notified of my allergy to nuts. 

------------------------------------------------

Overall: 3.5 / 5 Stars 

Overall, I enjoyed my experience at Prep & Pastry and will most likely return to try some of their other food offerings; however, I will be avoiding their Smoked Salmon Beni.

Came in for the first time to fix the band on my Cartier watch and replace the battery in my Balmain watch. The owner and assistant barely welcomed me and seemed to act like I couldn't afford to be in there (my Cartier watch is well over $15k). I asked if they could look at it before I dropped them off and seemed annoyed to walk away from a customer with a Breitling watch. They gave a quick answer that he couldn't fix the band and refused to give any recommendations on where to take it. His exact words were "I don't know any reputable jewelers, but I can't fix it". I allowed them to replace the battery in my Balmain watch but I most likely won't be back due to the poor customer service. I will take my watch to be repaired by a jeweler who can give me more than a minute of their time.
Stopped in for lunch. Had the patty melt. Like most places all bun and no meat. Homemade chips are delicious though. Atmosphere and service was great.

This was my first time having Soup Dumplings outside of NYC and I was very impressed. It's kind of a hole in the wall, but the food was excellent. I had the Chicken Dumplings and my friend had the pork. She had previously lived in China and said they were very authentic. I would go lunch as it isn't the most filling of food, but I would definitely go back!

Kyoto represents that slice of Japanese cuisine which features misoshiru soup, sashimi, sushi & maki rolls, don buri (rice bowls), udon, bento, tonkatsu (a favorite), and a staggering number of appetizers (from gomae (a wilted spinach salad with sesame) to beef tataki to tako yaki (grilled Osaka-style octopus balls festooned with paper-thin bonito flakes).

What it offers it does very well, and the hunnybunny and I have visited numerous times (and done take-away even more) because it's very near to us. Their fare is satisfying and presented straightforwardly. Perhaps a touch pricey, but we don't walk away feeling cheated.

What I really like to do is start here and halfway through head across the street to Kabuki, which offers similar fare with a different take on the presentation. It's the best part of a soy sauce pub crawl :-) and makes for an interesting date night!
Horrible food.  Horrible service.  How do u mess up Wendy's number 1 meal?  Drink had soap in it.  Burger disgusting.   Fire the kids running the windows!
This was our first visit, Zoey did a GREAT job grooming our Maltese, we will be returning soon! The facility was clean and inviting and Sophie was as happy as could be when I picked her up!

The staff was extremely nice, the service superb and fast!  Was visiting and got a bit sick of all the fried foods.  I'm Vietnamese so pho is always a staple and nice to have as an option when you're dehydrated from non stop adult beverages!  Went here with the husband and friend.  The pho was good and I also enjoyed the Vietnamese coffee. The atmosphere is super cute.

We were a bit scared to order food here. The place had some stale smell. But, we decided to be brace & order food anyway since we were starving & felt lazy to find another place. Ceviche is awesome. Would go there again. Burrito & quesadilla were good too. Very reasonable too. Good food & portion!

One of my favorite stores for home goods. Love this location the most as it used to be the iconic Urban Outfitters years ago. Got to pick up a few gifts for some friends and some stuff for myself. Love the product and the service. They wrapped up all my gifts which gives me extra time to enjoy the holidays and less time wrapping.

Let me just tell you that Chanel is the best bartender I've ever had. Her mint mojito just rocked my socks. So personable. So refreshing to see a young professional care about her work and her patrons. She lifted all my stress off my shoulders as soon as I walked in.

The only complaint...When I asked her to hold my water bottle, she said no.

I will start first by saying this place is breathtaking beautiful but not even being here for 24 hrs it has been a nightmare. 
1. We get here at 3:51PM, our reservations are wrong and now we have to wait but there is "a rush" on our rooms. Meanwhile, we go pick up the rest of our party from the airport and eventually receive a call at 5:41PM informing us our rooms are ready.
2. We return to the hotel and let them know we are here and ready to be checked in but Deb from North Carolina is very snappy and refuses to hand us our ID cards and credit cards that we politely handed to her. She even once put here finger up to shh us when we had questions. Her demeanor was very standoff-ish and even somewhat disrespectful and demeaning. But we pushed passed it being exhausted and annoyed.

3. We get to our rooms..... no wash cloths, refrigerator broken, moldy pizza, sticky nightstands, blocked view by banana leaf trees, dirty washcloths, dirty floors......ect. 

Management attempted to remedy the issues by providing $50 credit but at this point, $50 is a joke. 

4. We're told we will be moved to rooms with a better view and cleaned properly but at the time we were out having brunch but told upon our arrival to call the front desk and let them know who we are, our room number, and that we're ready to be moved. When we returned and called, we were to led that the manager we spoke with was in a meeting and would return our call in about 30 minutes. In the meantime, I had to call a friend to explain to housekeeping that we were moving and how it would be more sensible for her to clean the room once we were moved since none of us were proficient in Spanish. 

5. To be continued because we are still under 24-hrs at this resort :-(

I love Three Carrots so much!! So glad they have finally opened a stand alone restaurant! I went for brunch on the second day they were open with a bunch of omnivore friends- all had a great experience!! Of course they are still working out some kinks as they're flooded with business and brand new, but the food was amazing and the atmosphere peaceful. I got the loaded B&G (biscuits and gravy) with tofu scramble and loved every bite- I didn't think that anyone could beat my homemade tofu scramble, but this was pretty close. I also had some of the eggs Benedict and roasted potatoes and really enjoyed that. The wait time was a bit long, but the price was definitely right. I will be back many times in the future. Thanks to Three Carrots for making it easy to spread that vegan love!

I walked in around 5 pm (love to be able to do that for massages) and they were able to give me a 40 minute back massage and foot reflexology at the simultaneously! Both were fantastic and reasonable priced

Good times! Outstanding selection of old school games. All the favorites! Only 25cents. They have a change machine in case you forgot to get a roll of quarters. 

Bar had a good selection of bottles, tap, and the friendly,  hilarious bartenders can work some mixology for you, too. 

Great music in the background, tables cleverly marked with player numbers for sitting and visiting or just to rest your drink while you game all add to the fun atmosphere. 

A very enjoyable night out!
Food is good but the non alcoholic drinks are a bit of a joke, small 8oz glass loaded to the brim with ice and then charge $3.50 for juice?

If I could give more stars, I would. 

This review is for a facial that received from Naomi. 
It was the most thorough facial I've ever had. I asked for the "Fix It All" and boy, did she. 
My lines cleared overnight. 
My skin was visibly lifted and tighter. The technology and product in the salon is not "cosmetic" but is dermal medicine. 
Absolutely fantastic service and salon - I'll be back over and over again.

I called and tried to ask Jose a question about the appointment I made and he could not answer my question, nor did he try to find the answer for me. He was very short with me. I asked if I could cancel my appointment and he said yes, and then hung up on me. Poor customer service. Won't be using this company for future projects.
It's 8pm I'm the only customer and it took 20 mins just to make my pizza and me receive it! The place was dirty and the employees were very unprofessional... good luck keeping your store open

A great long time Sparks institution that has a different daily special on most days. All you can eat taco Tuesday and $2 pints on Wednesday to name a couple. It takes a lot to get 5 stars from me, I'm kind of stingy with them, but 4 stars is an easy score here. Food is always good and fresh, drinks are stiff and staff is always nice. Parking can be an issue if it gets busy, but only if you expect front row. There is plenty to be had, you just have to walk a bit. Live bands on some weekends with a decent stage setup and dance space. Whitney Meyer started out here on the staff and on the stage. (Google her, she was a contestant on The Voice)

This is a memory/meditation garden. Plenty of benches along the trail, some of it is paved or you can walk through the trees. Parking lot behind the garden, but it seems that the locals park along the road.

I was in Philadelphia for my cousin's wedding and needed a room the night, I booked a room at a decent price and enjoyed my stay at The Windsor Suites. The staff was kind and helpful. The room was spacious, clean and comfortable. Check-in and out was a breeze. I would recommend and stay here again if I was in the area!

Very clean with lots of washers and dryers of various sizes. The staff is friendly and helpful. I was there on the Thomas Fire and this was the spot our crew used. Starbucks, CVS and Ralph's within walking distance.

Go. Just go. The sandwiches are heaven. The vibe is cool. You'll walk out full and happy after a visit. The Veno is a personal favorite. It's like St. Louis wrapped up in a sandwich. And, this is one of the only places I could find Old Vienna's Hot Diggity's. I love this place!  If you have time and don't mind a little wait on the weekend, get in line.

LOVE THIS STORE! It is so beautiful!!! It has so many things to offer and items to choose from. I came into the store particularly interested in purchasing Crystals and I was blown away with the variety of Crystals they had to choose from. Stacy is the one who helped me. She is so nice and took her time explaining everything even in the midst of the store getting crowded, she still took her time and made sure I was helped. The other workers, Bonnie, Eric, and Tessa helped me as well. Wonderful staff! I will definitely come back!

What a hidden gem!!! Giving them four stars BC of the limited seatings but I loved this place, cool vibe, great music and awesome drinks!! Saturday nite it was busy BC its not a very big space. Seating was limited its a first come first serve seating. It took awhile to order our drinks but once we put in the order it came super quick. I would definitely be back. Very cool little spot near plenty of restaurant and shopping as well.

The service was great and so was the food. The portions were just right and everything we ate was great. I had the meatloaf with mac and cheese and my husband has the catfish with fries and green beans. The meatloaf was seasoned just right with noting too over powerful in it and the catfish batter was cornmeal base that was light and flavorful. We will be back.

Go here occasionally and they are normally pretty good. Today I bought two white cream filled chocolate donuts and both donuts weren't very filled with cream like they normally are. Was very disappointed in the lack of cream. Other than that they were very fresh donuts. The employees were very patient with us while trying to decide what to get. Although digital menu was a little confusing.

Honored to have visited this church today to see the Indianapolis Children's Choir perform "White Christmas". I honestly had never noticed this church despite driving past it several times along 86th Street near Meridian en route to Trader Joe's. The church has a clean design with a brick exterior and some stunning peaceful areas thanks to a garden and skylight corridor. The main sanctuary features an upper level and gorgeous stained glass windows that allow the natural light to flood in to the stage. The sanctuary is fairly large which explains why the ICC would choose this location. Note that they also offer ample parking. I can't speak for the church services but it did appear that they offer five services during Christmas Eve and Christmas Day. The upper level of the sanctuary offers a beautiful view of the entire room.

I love the Starbucks in my neighbourhood. The are super friendly and the store is always clean. Coffee is great, you cam veganize your drink which is awesome. The only bad thing here is the lack on vegan food. They only offer a bagel with avocado spread (which is way too spicy) and a platter they never ever have. I hope they realize this and get
More savoury stuff for all the vegans in town.

Nice place. They have indoor and outdoor covered seating. If you have a large party (4+) then outdoor would be your only option. As another reviewer mentioned, you order at the counter and then must get all of your own silverware, straws, and sauces from a side table. No big deal, but some might find it annoying if they did not already know this. Food was good. People were nice. Atmosphere is great. My only issue (hence the 4 stars) is that the portion sizes were kinda small. Maybe it was just what I ordered, but I'm the end I was still hungry. Anyway, I will definitely be back. Gonna try their wings next time.
The best fried chicken in Edmonton. The soy garlic is the go-to for takeout. The pieces are sizeable, crispy, and consistent.

This place was pretty solid. It's not quite fast food but not really a restaurant. I had never been there before and the staff was super friendly to me. They gave me recommendations and they also give you a free sample if it's your first time. I ended up going with my own concoction which was a pulled chicken made super spicy. Everything was top notch and delicious. It was actually quite spicy especially with the gravy mixture they served with my sandwich I was dipping in. The potato salad was quite good as well as the fries. I sampled their seasonal sweet potato casserole which was solid as well. I'd definitely recommend this place if you're looking for a quick eat and especially if you like a good spicy pulled  meat sandwich.

Came here for dinner on a Tuesday evening.  Made a reservation and requested a tank side table and luckily we were able to sit a row away from the tank (they had a party of 17 coming in that already reserved the seating right next to the tank).  The service was okay and the food was tasty, however I got food poisoning from the lobster mac so I'm not sure I would recommend it.  Overall it was a nice experience in the restaurant due to the fish tank.

We had eaten here a couple  of times before  relocating from Nola. The food and service was really impressive.  I have to say that tonight's experience was less than good.  The hostess was not a great first impression.She seemed less than enthusiastic about greeting customers.  The food and service was just okay. Nothing to really talk about.  I am sorry that I suggested this restaurant and will not be returning.  There are so many other really great restaurants in Nola. Very disappointed.
Love the power bowl with extra granola on the bottom! Always order online and it's ready on time with no wait :)

This tour was amazing. Brian was entertaining, knowledgable, and filled to the brim with charm.
The stories we heard were chilling, and it was a great walking tour that unearthed some dark secrets of New Orleans. 
If you are into the paranormal and spiritual, this tour is a must.
Not just standard "ghost stories", this tour delves into architecture, religion, history, and has many fun put stops. 
Got recommended to this tour by friends, and I would definitely recommend to anyone!
Quaint Conor Bagel shop. Family Owned great coffee, good prices, and always a newspaper waiting.

Neil O'Donoghue was our sales rep! Super cool for a bunch of reasons, including being  ex NFL, but primarily because this was our first stop to look at vehicles and he respected this fact. He did not pressure in any way.  He worked to get us the vehicle we wanted in the color we wanted.  Even though it took us past closing time (we didn't actually intend to get a vehicle that night) Neil didn't seem to mind. 
Absolute professional in every way including follow up call/text.  Perhaps most importantly of all, they were just fine working with an insurance payoff that hadn't arrived when it was expected... 
great old fashioned business ethic here.  Go see Neil O'Donoghue for your next dodge/jeep!

This place is definitely a hit! First time here and it was absolutely amazing, the staff was very welcoming. Our server Nick T. was super helpful, patient and funny. Veggie tray with the green goddess dip was soooo delicious! My entree was the Lobster Spaghetti which was to die for! I'll definitely be back, very soon!
Wine was good, dealt with 3 staff members one of which was rude! Would be great if they had more outdoor seating to enjoy the view.

Just an overall great experience. Every visit we have had to Oakley's has been absolutely exceptional. The service is wonderful with some incredibly friendly people. The food is some of the best in town. This weekend I had a rigatoni special. It was exquisite from the first bite to the last. My wife had a steak that would rival any steakhouse in town.

Trendy, industrial decor in a small space with a good number of tables but if the word has gotten out this place must get packed.  We went for lunch and based on the waiter's recommendation, ordered the Char Sui Pork Ribs.  They were amazing!!!  Fall-off-the-bone tender, delicious sauce, a cilantro and mint salad to top, and a sweet/salty peanut crumble.  It it not something I would usually order but SO glad I did.  The Juicy Lucy lamb burger was good but I have had better lamb burgers--it was juicy, wasn't greasy, but just missing something maybe.  I'm definitely going back to check out dinner!

The food was absolutely amazing, but the service was very slow and I don't think the waitress really liked her job. After we ordered our drinks we didn't get them for 15 minutes which at that point they were watered down. That is the reason for 4 stars. But everything else was on point.

I had been avoiding this place for a while, but now I regret it! Don't know why but I had a misconception. Went here before a Roadrunners game at the TCC and had great food and great beer. Quick service was great, considering it was pretty busy! And the free chips and salsa (with warmed chips!) were a nice touch.

This is a very well maintained Civil War historical site. Be sure to take the tour of the inside of the Carter House - the guide is excellent and makes you feel what it was like to be in the middle of a major Civil War battle.
Paul

I have been going here for over 12 years. George is a great and honest mechanic, not to mention a very nice guy. I had previously gone to chain auto repair places such as Firestone and Pep Boys and I had nothing but problems. His prices are fair and even a little cheaper than dealers. I have had all kinds of work done here on various cars and everything was done quickly and correctly the first time.  George always calls and explains issues and prices before doing any work.

I highly recommend Carneys!

I was excited for another place to open up on Harbor Island and couldn't wait to try American Social after hearing some rave reviews around town.  We decided to come in the early afternoon to have some drinks and food before the Lady Gaga concert on a recent Friday.  Upon arriving, since we were early, it was pretty easy to get a table outside but the place got pretty packed around 6pm with fellow concert goers and the after work happy hour crowd.

Cocktails off their menu are very creative and sound tasty, but two cocktails can set you back about $30.  There is a weekday happy hour for apps and the pretzel bites off that menu were a bit of a disappointment.  They tasted like clumps of bread with large salt chunks on them.  It was served with a cherry mustard, which was an odd combo.  I ended up also having a quesadilla off the menu and it was dried out and felt as if it was prepared earlier in the day and just sat all day under a heat lamp.  The pricing of the food was also not indicative of the quality and overpriced in my opinion.  

It was nice seeing this location finally fill up with another tenant and the overall atmosphere is really nice and spacious, but I feel as if their food quality needs to improve if they want to charge the prices they do.

First cheese steak and I regret having it at the airport and not some famous place that claimed to have invented it. 

Still, wasn't bad. Price is not exaggerated, the bread was fresh and soft. Plenty of meat inside and I let them pick out Swiss cheese. Grilled onions and nothing more. I'll start with the basic and later on advance to more toppings inside. 

It's not 5 start because I wasn't overwhelmed. 
It's not 4 because throughout the sandwich I had a couple of bites that hit something hard. I figure it was bone or something but it wasn't meat, cheese, onions or bread. Didn't investigate too much.

We have eaten here several times for brunch, and I've had a great experience. We were here on Saturday, however, just to have a drink at the bar and the service was so poor, I had to let a manager know as well as write this review. I'm always amazed when people are rude because they're busy, isn't busy good? There were three girls behind the bar, one of them was relatively new, and the nicest of the three. The other two were visibly irritated either that they had to work or that they had customers I'm not sure which. It was so uncomfortable being there,We finally had to leave. I did let the manager at the front door no, not sure if she was interested or not.

This place is "a-ok". Nothing spectacular to add. Quick regular sandwich, and able to use the Wi-Fi from the place next door. Not much business when I was here, so I was able to chill at a booth for a while.

I've been searching for my favorite Chinese's place in the GNO area for years and I've finally found it. This place is a no frills, good price, good food gem.

People have strong and varying opinions on what makes "good" Chinese's food. Well, this place is the Americana version for sure, but it does it so much better than the other strip mall and take out places.
One of my favorite frozen custard places in St Louis (as it is an institution). Love the Hawaiian - it can't be beat!

Wonderful space, tons of character, great decor. Great staff. Helpful and inviting. 
Amy Johnson is a miracle worker. 
She took a bushy six month grow out and turned it into a smooth, sleek, chic pixie. 
From what I hear ALL stylists and colorists are just phenomenal. 
I FINALLY found my salon.

Really impressed by this little place. They need to put their menu on the site. The bratwurst was to die for. My group also ordered the black bean burger, grilled cheese and the Stool Pigeon chicken. No complaints. Choice of beers was very impressive. And our favorite musician was playing, Corey. We will definitely be back.
Excellent food. Great staff. Stopped here on our road trip from San Diego to San Francisco. As a Thai food aficionado I highly rate this restaurant!

Had an absolutely phenomenal dinner. Started with both the tuna tartar and carpaccio both A+. Followed with mussels in coconut curry - now on my top ten list of best things I've ever eaten. The 36 oz dry aged porterhouse was amazing both in taste and presentation. But if you don't save room for dessert you're out of your mind. You couldn't live with yourself for missing out on trying the apple fritters however the carrot cake was the best we've ever had by a mile.

I was staying nearby at the Faunbrook B&B and they recommended this restaurant. I had the shrimp and crab over spicy linguine as a carry-out order. My food was ready very quickly and pick up was pretty painless. I wish they had a reserved parking spot in front for quick pick ups. I'm not a local and wasn't sure where I could leave my car nearby easily. The serving size was enormous- enough for 2-3 portions. And they were GENEROUS with the seafood. The quality and freshness were great, and the value was good once you see how much food you get (including a whole bag of bread!). I will certainly return if I'm in the area and would recommend this for a date night, or to feed a small group with good taste.
Amazing experience at Tuna Bar tonight. The food was amazing and service was great, as well. I would definitely highly recommend.
They were so friendly from the moment I called, to walking in to picking up my order. The food was good and fresh. Ready in 10 minutes from the time I ordered. The price is good.

Fantastic customer service, did a great job on my screen and expert install of new screen protector.  I'd say, move over Apple Store! I really enjoyed my time here as they had snacks and drinks in the WeWork facility.  Get the manufacturers screen as opposed to the cheaper one.  

Mac helped me out and was very nice and thorough. They even stayed late to help me!
Best burger ever! The sauce makes it perfect! The French 75 cocktail is a must have ! ( cognac and apple cider)

Was not expecting much when my husband suggested we stop in here for breakfast as we were out walking on a Sunday morning. They had a very inexpensive, not fancy, but adequate "buffet ". Bacon, eggs, sausage, the basics. No wait! This is practically unheard of on a Sunday morning!

Wow wow wow wow. So good. They measure and use so much precision and care with each cup. Best coffee I've ever tried. Best fresh grapefruit juice (local) and best mocha. The cascara tea is really special too.
