I want to love this store - they are and right next door to my house, and they are open 24 hours. They have a nice selection of fruits and veggies, and alcohol. (Reasons for 2 stars.) 

However, the staff isn't that friendly: I had purchased three clusters of snow crab, drove the min and a half home to my house, and put them into the pot to cook for lunch. When I pulled them out of the pot, they stank of Ammonia / bleachy smell. I looked it up, everything I found said they were bad. I called the store and after be transferred from staff member to staff member, one finally told me to just come back for a refund. I asked if I needed to bring them back - ( that I totally would..it had only been a matter of 25 mins between buying and finding them rotten.) - and she told me, "no, just come back with your receipt".  So, I went in, only to be talked down too like I was (A.) lying. and (B.) like I was dumb for not bringing them back. 
I told the woman working customer service (not the one I spoke to on the phone.) that's I'd be happy to go get them and come back. I just wanted my $30 back.
Finally got a refund after 15 mins., and some eye rolls and huffing and puffing from the lady working. 
I told them twice they need to pull the snow crab off the shelf, because they may make someone ill. 
Came back the next day to find the same snow crab there. 

This afternoon I was eating some of their tomato basil soup you can get when you walk right into the store on the Starbucks side. 
Halfway through I found plastic in the soup, (picture attached.) 
I'm not even going to bother calling, because frankly, they probably won't do anything about it since they left the rotten snow crab on the shelf. And, I really don't think the $4.99 back is worth the attitude and 15 min ordeal. 

I recommend only buying fruits and veggies.
Buffalo mozzarella.   Actual Italian hoagies.  Fresh bread.  Cheeses.   Small Italian market feel.   Been there about a dozen times.   Highly recommended.

Took a 6 am flight to Philly. Landed it was snowing. Took the train and walk several blocks to the hotel. Check in friendly room ready wow early check in. Went to the room. First thing I notice a wine glass on floor outside the room. The room clean . I even pull the sheets and check the mattress. I did notice a dent in the wall and unfinished repair over the window. Gab a quick drink and some thing to eat . Nothing special. Later went to the bar at 11:30 pm for some drinks . Was told that the bar is closing. What on a Saturday night. I was able to order drinks to take to the room. Stay open longer.

We had the turkey leg which was enormous and perfectly cooked. The sides were exemplary especially the sweet potatoes. The marshmallow really made it seem more like a dessert than a side.
We had really attentive and friendly wait staff and enjoyed our night out.
I'll definitely be back!

Had the delight of trying this place thanks to the clueless people in Giorgio's who sat way too long! It's not okay! Especially in a place known to be booked & busy all the time. You're not only ruining the night for other diners but the poor servers who only make money if they can turn the tables (I was a server years ago & it's very frustrating!) The food was super yummy ((great meatballs) but our waiter was the standout! We were bummed but he cheered us up. Thank you Giorgio for sending us over. You saved my sisters birthday dinner. Giorgio's is still my favorite but this was a close second!

Craving some BBQ I stopped at this establishment for take out.  I ordered the pulled pork without the bread.  Two sides where baked beans and the mac n'cheese.  
The pork was so tender and went nicely with the sweeter version of there  BBQ sauce.  I would say you get a little over a cup of pulled pork.
The baked beans themselves were just as I like them.  Not overly mushy but, tasty just the same.
The mac-n-cheese was to me nothing really special.  
Overall I would come back and try different menu items.  Probably this time dine in.  Then when I get an uncomfortable looking at a  bag with too much grease on it.  I would not frown--as you must already know about me presentation is the king.  Nothing like an unclean takeout bag.  I want to look into the takeout bag just like I received the best present in the world.

Sam has become our go to spot, I only wish we'd found it sooner. We almost always can grab a seat at the bar, and the bartenders are always super friendly and attentive. Especially Monica, she's great and always recognizes us and says hi when we come in. She even remembers what beers were on tap last time we were in and can point out new ones to us. We get the county line wings every time...the sauce is some sort of combo of maybe bleu cheese and hot sauce and something else, and they're crispy,  or soggy like other places. The pizza is great too, we usually get the short rib or the upside down. Atmosphere is great for happy hours and dinner. We've been for an Eagles game before and there wasn't much of a crowd, which we prefer. We have yet to try their brunch or visit on a Wednesday night when there is live music, but hope to soon!  There's also a lot of regulars here, which shows you what kind of place this is. There's even an older gentleman who you can sometimes find at the bar doodling people he sees.
I love the marts Mac basic Mac n cheese. Cute, clean, polite, helpful staff. Just a few seats.YUM!! Almost as good as Smac in NYC! Next time I'll get the basil pesto chicken Mac!

This pizzeria was not bad, but it was really mediocre and the pizza wasn't remarkable. It was St. Louis style pizza, but it really lacked the robust flavor found at most of the St. Louis pizza places. It's not bad, but if you want St. Louis style pizza, there are other places close by that do a lot better.

Decided to do takeout pizza for a little get-together. Ordered large plain pie, large supreme pie, and a small special calzone. The pizza arrived still crispy, the cheese didn't slide in the box. The calzone was also still crispy and not soggy. The calzone was the best part! A great idea for pizza in the area!

Absolutely great customer service, our waitress was awesome and food delicious...to add very affordable first time there will become a regular customer 

Yelonda J

Nobody greeted me. I had to walk over to a waiter to ask for a drink. Naan wasn't good...I think they cooked too much ahead of time.  Good variety on the buffet. One guy left mad because they sat him back in an odd place by speaker and bathroom and they didn't seem too concerned that he left. They would do well if this was the only option - but there is a lot of competition now. Need to improve service and atmosphere if they want to stay open.  I may go back, but I think it's worth the extra drive to go to Cool Springs or Taj.

A fabulous shop!!! Eclectic finds! Unique, yet somehow something for everyone! I completed my holiday shopping in one visit! A shame I don't live nearby. Will definitely visit the next time I'm in town!

Vientiane Cafe - oh I love you dearly. Not only do you always provide an affordable meal that all seem to enjoy - you are consistent, every dish is made to order, and OMG can you accommodate all food preferences!


This visit is bitter-sweet, as I am departing the Philadelphia area for a new career opportunity.

While I know I will be back from time-to-time, as I do have family in the area, I still can't just pop on over to one of my favorites when I need a good friend's couch to sit on. Because of all realistic measures, that is exactly what Vientiane is - a good friend's couch that you can come hang out in a laid back and chilled BYOB atmosphere.


It's that friend that makes you that big bowl of comfort food to help you celebrate the highs or to crush to lows... and for all of the amazing experiences I have had here - I thank you! I thank you for making eating out and being social a possibility for a gal who has multiple food allergies, is a bit of a food snob, and living on a budget. You are amazing and I will continue to spread the word that all of Philadelphia needs to come check out Vientiane, if they have not already!


This evening, we were seated and handed the revamp menu - which, is visually much more appealing. It is also helpful that this menu consists of GF (gluten-free) codes so I know what is and is not safe for me.


I ordered a good classic for a table share - Lao Porridge (jow-piek) or congee. It is a smooth and comforting bowl of heaven - not too many more ways to explain it.  It is a subtle dish with simple flavors meant to heal. Good thing I planned on sharing and that I ordered the large because the entire table went nuts over it. P.S I order it with the soft tofu rather than fried - it is just a preference, but I think it makes a world of difference.


Then, despite having a huge list of things I wanted to try (aka the casserole, Laab, any of their fried rice dishes, Banh-Xeo, a dessert, and more.....) I had to go out with the first dish I ever ordered.......


Drum roll please..... the King Soup - or as I like to describe it as a Pho with coconut milk and much more spice! We all know I love coconut, love a creamy dish, and we LOVE spice - so win was always written all over this dish! Oh, and did I mention that they can make it gluten-free, vegan and it comes in a GIANT bowl for under 15!?


A friend of mine did order the new dish, Bamboo Stew (gang-naw-mai) which is bamboo shoots mixed with pumpkin and mushrooms (very earthy) and served with their famous sticky rice. Note, while this dish is not marked gluten-free, I am sure that if you ask, they are able to modify it for us gluten-free folks! 


In conclusion, it has been real Vientiane Cafe and I will certainly be back to visit! In the meantime, keep making some more awesome additions to your menu and oh, if any of my readers try the other dishes on my wish list, PLEASE SEND ME REVIEWS!


Until next time.


Oh, and check out all my other reviews of Vientiane Cafe below:
http://gf-flamingo.blogspot.com/

The Hispanic man with the glasses is the nastiest person I have encountered by far in a long time. I went to go grab some napkins and he made me ASK FOR HIS PERMISSION. I hope someone heals your rude soul. Will never be going near this place ever again

We were in town visiting and looking for something fun to do. Liveminds was our answer, and what an amazing adventure it was!

This was the second escape room type place I've been to. Liveminds goes above and beyond anything similar. It was comparable to being on a movie set. The experience was all immersive and each and every little detail was carefully thought out. From the decor to the sound effects- I was blown away! 

We chose to do Treasure of Pacari. We had a small group (4)  of varying ages and everyone had a blast. This specific room felt challenging but also doable (that just right level of difficulty). 

Each second we spent inside made us feel like we were indeed exploring ancient ruins in search for the item! 

If you are looking for a fun birthday plan or something new to do on a Friday night in the Nashville or Franklin area, I highly recommend Liveminds! I can't wait to go back and try one of the other rooms. Thank you for an awesome experience!

This review is for Parkallen pizza; we've been enraptured and haven't yet ventured to the other parts of the menu, even though they look great.

A quick shout out to the staff, who have always been sweet and understanding as we navigate the relationship straits that is the picking of the toppings. There are few dilemmas as great, and as meaningful.

I guess it goes without saying that pizza tastes much better when eating it right from the kitchen; delivery is foodie insult we inflict when we are lazy and hungry. Parkallen pizza is still very good when delivered, but in-house it was sublime! It has the most tasty crust I've long tasted in a pizza. The contributions of each ingredient (we shared a half Hawaiian and half meat-lover) could be noticed and appreciated.

The hunnybunny's place is near-by, enough so that we've eaten in and picked up pie for transport home. More than once it's been an open question whether we can survive the seductive pizza smell filling the car or should we just pull over and dig in. You've been warned :-)

My husband and I were passing through the city from a long road trip, and I have always wanted to try this place out. Well, I have no regrets! The place itself is super clean and chic. The ambience was very warming. And our waitress Laura was the best! She attended us instantly very friendly and with a smile on her face! The food, one word, AMAZING!!! The jambalaya had the perfect blend of flavor and the shrimp and grits were so creamy! I recommend going to Desire as soon as you get to the French quarter, and don't forget to ask for Laura; she will definitely make you feel at home!
Great place!  Cheers to more options in Donelson.  Only thing is... it seems like the product keeps changing.  Quesadilla was nice and stringy cheesy last week but cheese was like velveeta this week.

Great little bike shop with can do attitude. I found them to be very knowledgeable and accommodating in fixing the problems with my Trek Bicycle. Service and Parts pricing was reasonable and they did their best to handle all of my issues and get me back on the road even though it was shortly before closing. Thanks guys
Not good for delivery. Food was cold and soggy. I ordered the salmon bento and stir fry soft shell crab. Horrible. Threw most of it away. Now looking for something else for dinner.

I absolutely love this location. The cashier I spoke to was very friendly and energetic to everyone around and made the experience of shopping here that much better. I bought some eyeshadow here and although a little expensive it's very nice.

The food here was good. We came for a late breakfast and waited a little longer than they initially said. The food took a long time to come which made lunch last 2.5 hours, but everything tasted good. The City Grits were especially fantastic! The coffee mugs were adorable and are a great gift (albeit a little expensive at $18 each). Overall a long but enjoyable breakfast.

Terrible. I had to get to church with a colored print that had details of a child with a fatal disease and their printer took 30 minutes to print 4 pages properly! Three different machines and three people had to get involved. They didn't charge me but I obviously missed my appointment! What's more their ladies room at 10:30 am is absolutely disgusting and no paper towels even though have have so many on sale outside.

Came here while attending the Essence Festival food was so good we came 2 mornings in a row! I  would suggest getting the shrimp and grits. I Had that with the fried fish as well and asked for gravy on the side. The grits were nice and creamy, shrimp was tender and the fish was fried to perfection  with just the right amount of seasoning. The wait staff was also accommodating. The place is a bit small so get there early or there might be a wait.
Improvement is slow.  Food is same but at least they have a few friendlier people.  I wish they offered some specials.

Roger,
Seattle wins AGAIN!!!! You're an awful bartender with awful friends. I keep you in my spank bank, exactly where you belong. Let me know if you need some redecorating, because your front door looks like crap. Drizzle rain? Better grab your umbrella. 

Folks,
If anyone wants soda water in your 'Old Fashioned', this place is for you. Bad people making bad drinks. They would mess up a cup of coffee if you asked for it. It's Folgers btw. I would recommend the trek to Firkins Tavern in Ewing, NJ - the real deal! The further you can get from this trashy, low-class bar, the better.

Went on a Sunday. Very limited menu, much different than what is listed online. If you only serve brunch - let people know! Only one kids option. Food was just okay - we had migas and huevos rancheros. Eggs were over cooked in the huevos rancheros and it came with cilantro on top although that wasn't listed on the menu.

I stopped in and made a reservation, but I am horrified by the service I received. First of all, they took over an hour to seat us after telling us the wait was 30 minutes or so. Then, they seated us and it took over 20 minutes for a waiter to bring us water, let alone take our order. Food was far below similar restaurants (with better service). And I am disappointed.

Food is excellent!!! The grouper is ridiculously amazing!! Along with the crab cake!!!!!!! Delicious!!!! The service is not stellar and this place needs a serious update but if you want good food with a decent view... Sculleys is it!!!!
I know it's not fancy, but the food is fantastic! Best marinara sauce ever. I order eggplant parm via Uber Eats weekly!

Having my hair done at the same place in NJ for 8 years, I was super nervous to switch hair colorists when I moved to the area. Kadi, however, exceeded all my expectations and did an amazing job on my color. I am so happy I bit the bullet and tried someplace new!

Have been following American Social on social media and decided for the last day of 2017 to give it a try... and so glad we did!  Everything from the service, to the food, to the atmosphere is amazing!  The flatbread was to die for, the chicken was tender and juicy and the girls live the pancakes and sides (we live the bacon!).  Oh and I can't forget the cocktails.. my favorite is the Tijuana Social!
Two visits on my trip. Excellent food and service! Had the oyster Benedict and the seafood Benedict.  Awesome grits as well!
This neighborhood bar is amazing. The bar staff especially Sam is amazing. You always feel welcomed and at home. Great prices and great pours.

I went in with high hopes. A place that specializes in burgers and offers a $30 burger on the menu should blow me away. I left unimpressed and let down.  My burger was over cooked and dry. The size of burger not worth the price. I honestly would of preferred a double cheeseburger from Wendy's.  

There is nothing special about this place. Not worth the money.

I met family from out of town at Morning Call so we could catch up as I live out of state but grew up on the Westbank.  I wasn't impressed to be honest.  For starters I had to put my own powdered sugar on the beignets which I've never had to do and I eat beignets at least once a year when I'm in town.  Their beignets were a little fluffier than other places but I've had much better.  I'll only come here again if it's the only way to see family, otherwise I'll stick with Cafe du Monde.

SO GREAT!

From the drinks, to the bread, to the main course everything was great and seasoned perfectly.  I really enjoyed the filet mignon and parmesan risotto. The only thing I didn't care for was the garlic mash.. they seemed dry and the presentation was bad.. literally looked like it came out of an ice cream scoop.  But honestly this was super minor compared to how great everything else was.  I will definitely be back!

This was without a question, one of the best sales and delivery experience I have ever received in my life. Below I will explain why I say that and how it came to be.  What I want everyone who reads this review to understand is a few simple strategies. 1) Know what you want before you go to a RV dealership; 2) Do your due diligence on choosing Make, Model, Options and the Fair Price you will pay; 3) Order the coach so you have time to sell your own if possible; 4) Don't be in a rush; 5) Have all your communication in writing and if something is missing, take responsibility that you did not prepare prior to your commitment.  
All the above is what I did.  Why, because I read every blog I can find on the subject, watch every YouTube video I could and listen to folks who have been RVing for decades. Every single part of my requests to Tampa RV were fulfilled prior to me even setting foot in the dealership. My sales consultant, Stephen Weaver, communication with me consistently throughout the ordering process (three months).  Everyone from the General Manager to the PDI manager called me prior to delivery.  Even the dealer sent me an email after I took delivery.  
Folks, every aspect of my sale to delivery exceeded my expectation.  Thanks to the entire staff of Tampa RV for working so closely with me.  My hopes are everyone does their research and preparation prior to even thinking about the purchase of an RV from any dealership.  Bravo to all involved.  See my addition comments below for more information.
This not my first purchase of an RV/Coach.  Prior to every transaction, I do a level of due diligence that most people can't or are simply not willing to do. In the past I have been asked to speak on the subject at national conventions, pod casts, YouTube reviews including my own and my personal blog on the RV Industry.  My goal is to be a advocate for clients to have a seamless and transparent transition with most RV dealers in the United States. I am called the "RV Advocate".
On to my review. When I finally choose my brand (AirStream), model (Interstate Grand Tour) and option package (Tommy Bahama) it was time to choose my dealership.  Since I had purchased an AirStream Trailer prior, I had gone through this process before.  It seems my prior dealer did not communicate some critical facts to me on my potential new purchase, so we parted ways as friends. My money, so my choice. I knew every single Airstream dealer is a five-state radius.  I had visited most of them. I was referred to Tampa RV (A member of the RVone Group) by a trusted Airstream friend. Tampa RV's reviews were not stellar to say the least, but I studied them very closely.  It became clear to me the issues, not only with Tampa RV, all RV dealerships I dealt with was "professional communication" on both the client and the dealers side.  I created a process in writing to leave "no stone un-turn" and the result was OUTSTANDING.

3 words... donut bread pudding. OMG. Insane. Not too sweet, light fluffy goodness with coconut & fresh cream. It's a dream. Trust me, save room for it. Service was also divine. Servers who weren't even ours stopped to ask if we had what we needed, if we were liking things etc. Really an awesome experience. We will be back for a dinner! 

Update: we came back for dinner and the burger will change your life!!

I try to go here once a week, the food is amazing and the price is right. Food is freshly prepared and it shows. They have an amazing awards program, please don't change a thing! 

If Chipotle/QDoba could be more authentic, they still could not compare!

Their chicken al pastor quesadilla is my favorite.

In summary: Best quick service Mexican food around.

Cool ambiance, great food! Definitely order the Yakitori, we had chicken thigh, very tender and moist. The duck fried rice was yummy too.  The Japanese beer, Orion, was really good too, never had it before but good drinking beer.

The place looked interesting enough, the live music was pleasant enough, the food and drink were over priced and marginal at best, but the coupe de grace was delivered when I received the check. I had asked for an additional portion of herbed mayonaise that accompanied my Cuban sandwich, upon examination of the check, I found a $1 charge for a table spoon of mayo. Unbeliebvable. I said something to the manager who did nothing but say "that's how it is."
Don't be lured by the interesting exterior......this place is not worth your time or money and the management is completely tone deaf on customer perception of value; $8 for a 10oz glass of common IPA, $18 for lack luster fish tacos plus mayo for $1. There are much better options in that town or accross the river.

We are regulars. Its one of our places for sushi rolls. Very clean place. I think they need to change up the menu a little more often. I personally dont care for much of the hot foods. Just dont like the sauce. Soups are GREAT. I would tell you to go.

Visiting from San Antonio and I had researched some places to try while in Tucson. This was THE place at the top of my list and we were not disappointed!  We visited on a Tuesday for breakfast and when we arrived it was busy. I ordered the Breakfast Sammi and it was delicious. The English muffin and eggs were perfect and the Preps potatoes are amazing!  The Smoked Salmon Beni was served perfectly. The service  was friendly an on point!  We wanted to try one of their pastries but they sold of them before we could.  This place is a 'MUST' try!!

I really enjoyed eating here it is just the cutest place, we loved the decor. I came for breakfast and they have a great variety of coffee drinks, I really appreciated that. Their food was delicious. The staff was friendly but a little under trained on the menu and offerings but that can only get better the longer they work there. We were very pleased and will return. We parked in the parking lot underneath expecting to get a discounted rate with validation, like the sign stated, but they don't validate. Other than paying, parking is a mess- maybe try walking/Uber if you don't live too far.

Lovely beach spot opens in the Shoppes at Sand Key. Just south of the Sand Key Bridge to Clearwater Beach, this is a welcome addition to the local fare. All organic teas, coffees, juices, smoothies, breakfast and lunch. Splendid view of the intracoastal waterway. Open every day 8-4.
Excellent special veggie Pho with delicious vegan "fish" sauce broth served by the nicest people on this side of town! We will be back often.
Awesome atmosphere! Food was great! Had Gus's pretzels for appetizers, frittata for main course. Other folks had pizza and steak salad

Love this place! No need to go all the way to Philly for pho. We had house special pho, pork bbq summer roll and ground chicken lettuce wrap. All of them were delicious and satisfying. Their pho portion is pretty big!The service was great too. My mom was also very happy about this place.

Enjoyed a great brunch here on a Saturday with a friend of mine. We arrived around 9:30 AM and the dining room was full. There was a decent overflow of people waiting and I anticipated a much longer wait time than what we experienced which was about 20 minutes. This gave us time to engage in some observation of the clientele as well as the delicious breakfast items being pushed out by the kitchen. 

I loved the decor, clean, modern and welcoming! 
The breakfast menu can satisfy from savory to sweet. My friend and I shared a cinnamon roll before our main dish arrived. She had the eggs Benedict and I had a wonderful has. The food was seasoned really well, came out hot, and was ample in size for our post yoga consumption, I had to take some of my hash home. 

Overall I am for sure a fan of this place and look forward to dining on the patio when the weather is a bit warmer! 

My only criticism is for a refill of coffee they charge you .75 cents.  I don't know enough about the quality of coffee they serve but I can't imagine it's so extraordinary that you'll need to charge customers extra for a refill. Was just a tad put off by this!
Delectable aa bowls/pita and wonderful staff. Ambience was quaint and clean; only downside was lengthy wait time for food.

Closed down? I can't even believe it. It's only been two months since I was there, but I've been dreaming about it. The frybread with green chile was absolutely delicious, the best I've ever had. It was a giant portion, too. I hope the owners can bring it back. It was awesome!

Staying at the Ramada so I ordered a meal for myself to go. I go and pick it up, and it's $18 for the fried steak meal (with eggs, hash browns and pancakes) and a cup of coffee. That seems a little ridiculous to me for ihop. Also, hours after eating it, I got food poisoning. Save yourself the money and your health.
Excellent food at a great price. Old country charm and friendly service. A must-see if you're in the area!
I don't normally eat burgers and this place was sensational! Great food & great service! The beers were awesome! Highly recommend stoping here.

Excellent freshly cooked food. My chicken tacos, with avocado added, were perfect.  My husbands regular sized burrito was huge and delicious.  Great stop after buying Florida citrus across the street.

I went to the salon to get a Brazilian Wax + Stomach Strip and boy was this a pitch job and messy. My Waxer was Rebekah. She was very pleased to to talk to but she was just not careful. She didn't do small sections like the other waxers, instead she did huge sections. I had Wax all over me. Just strings all over my stomach. EVERYWHERE. I had to peel it off and hand it to her. Overall she is nice however, if I can save someone their money I would 100% not recommend for a Brazilian Wax. I usually just bounce around and take any waxer I can get but this was just horrible. I've gone there every month since Feb and I needed to say something about this one because it was horrible.

Great southern hospitality. The burger is delicious and the chicken and waffles is a-maz-ing! This cozy place is just off of Broadway so it's right by the action but is a great place to just relax. The staff is friendly and makes you feel right at home. It's kid/family friendly and it's open 24 hrs so you can pop in any time. Loved it!

This place is absolutely divine!!! We started off with the the whipped feta with bacon... great addition to any meal. The butternut squash soup was superb! The fire roasted carrots are always a family favorite. The sweet papas bravas stole the show!!! It was truly amazing!!! One of my all time favorites. As our main entree we got the crispy avocado rice with chicken. It was awesome! We ended the night with a the butternut squash ice cream cake. It was a beautiful dessert and tasted even better. Tonight was truly, delectably exquisite!!!!

Got there to find that you no longer need to put your name down for a table but to seat yourself. So we had a party of 6 squeezed into a booth made for 4. We were gonna accept it since the place was packed and you had to fight for a place to eat here. But then a miracle happened and a larger booth opened up. We already gotten out food but the waitress was really nice and let us move since it was still in her zone. No biggie. But then the service was not up to par. She only bought us one set of silverware. I figured she just put the one down to go and get 5 more. Nope. So we had to ask for plates and more silverware. She brings us the other half of our order and says she'll come back with the plates and silverware. Brings me my drink. By this time we almost done eating. No napkins. Ended up stealing a batch from the bar. No silverware. No plates. Finally she brings plates and silverware. But she only bought 4 silverware sets/napkins and 5 plates. We have a party of 6. You do the math. Then she disappears for the rest of our meal. We don't see her again. We ended up having to hunt her down to ask for our check. Also note that before all this we were almost given someone else's order. The people delivering it totally looked lost. 

This place is still running around with its head cut off. I noticed that there is an entire area in the back that they closed. Then you have people hoarding tables while their brats run around to play games. If they are not actively order a continuous food/drink I think they are done. Maybe give em a hint by giving them the check. Just saying. 

Also, if you parked in the garage they only have pay Stations on the first and 6th Floor. That's makes a whole lotta sense. People can either go down to the first floor pay for parking and then go back upstairs to whatever floor they parked on. That's not enough elevators for all that foot traffic. Or you can pay for parking before leaving the 6th floor where people are lined up to buy cards for the games and the foot traffic from the elevators. So now you adding to the foot traffic as well. Yippie. Have fun.

Best car buying experience we have ever been through.  We had a specific type of truck model in mind and price range that we wanted to stay within and saw a truck on their lot that fit the model.  We decided to stop by to ask about the price and found that it was out of our price range.  Harry Martell was the sales associate assisting us and asked specifically what we wanted and price range.  He said a vehicle matching our specifics had just been traded in and was still in the back.  We test drove the vehicle, loved it and without ANY hassle or annoying haggling that you normally experience at dealerships, Harry had us in our new truck and out the door in no time.  Richard, their finance manager had all of our paperwork ready to go and I have to say it was the easiest transaction we have ever experienced.  We appreciate the honesty, ethics and knowledge these two brought to the table.  We love our truck!  Thanks guys!

Ordered the chicken finger salad and a side of fries as takeout. It was ready in less than 15 mins and was directly across the street from the courtyard Marriott. The salad was good size. It has a House sauce on the chicken, which wasn't too bad, but a little spicy for my taste. The worst part of the salad was the croutons, which were greasy. I would get the salad again without the croutons. It came with a homemade ranch which I loved.

Easy 5 Star. Really nice ambiance, very relaxing with the low lights and plentiful candles. The service was very good and the prices really reasonable. We shared 5 rolls and had 2 miso soups and our bill was under 50 dollars. We had the dynamite, jazz, veggie, don taun, and Philly rolls. All were delicious and very fresh. They had a huge menu with many options. Everything sounded good. A must try!

Dee-lish food, good variety. German/Austrian twist offers different dishes from schnitzel to spaetzel to Lukelly.  If looking for American dishes of salmon and steak, they have that, too. Desserts were homemade with whipped cream made from scratch. Outstanding!  Cappuccino, iced Viennese coffee all winners. Service was superb. 
Plenty of parking. Cheerily and tastefully decorated for the holidays. Very comfortable seating. Serves beer and wine, too. Portions are so generous, everyone in our party of 6 took home leftovers. 
All around winner.

Amazing dive shop with top rated gear and staff!  I've been diving for years and recently moved to the area looking for a dive shop.  I couldn't be happier with infinite descent.  Connor, Maria, and Eric "Hollywood" are all extremely knowledgeable.  I had great dives in the gulf where I saw schools of fish, goliath groupers, and a large turtle.  They also do spearfishing.  It's also one of the only dive shops in the area that has their boats go straight out from behind the shop.  Extremely convenient!  I can't say enough great things about this shop.  Be sure to check it out!

Annamaria the GM is absolutely amazing! Her customer service is above and beyond, and we were thoroughly impressed!! We found this place by accident and stayed because the food, service and atmosphere was amazing!!!! What a gem!

Sat down with another group in front of us and was ignored for 25 minutes. The group in front and behind us were waited on and served immediately. At the 30 min point we were finally acknowledged and asked for our drink order. Here at the 45 minute mark waiting in our food as the the group in front and behind finish their meals. Here on vacation and will not be coming back or rendering anyone to your establishment.

I came here and almost all the tables are highly top,l. It's difficult when you have a short wife or even if you're drinking you could easily stumble. The food is over priced, pretzel are frozen from a box, lemon for my water had mold residue, and my glass was cracked. Not only that I can see how terrible the management is to the severs. I asked a server how much they had to tip out to bartenders and it's nearly ridiculous. It doesn't seem like a great place to work or eat. Way to over priced and terrible management.

This was a surprisingly great restaurant! It was across from our hotel so we wandered in to a short 20 minute wait during the holiday season and sat outside on their upstairs balcony. The service was great and the food was even better. The quality of the sea-food was top notch and the sides are cheap and yummy. The entrees are expensive for the environment of the restaurant but the quality makes up for it. A fun restaurant in a busy area!

First trip to Nectar, food and service was amazing. The owner visited many times. Group of six, shared the Queso and Chips with guacamole, salsa and Pepita Hummus. All great but the best was the hummus, very unique. Bowls, fish tacos and quesadillas excellent. Will be returning soon!

I went for a deep tissue massage.  I was greeted warmly and immediately.  The spa was clean, inviting and soothing.  The massage was amazing!  Stephanie worked wonders on my very tight neck and shoulder muscles.  The 80 minutes went by way too fast!! My checkout was seamless.  I'm scheduling another appointment with Stephanie before I leave town!!

This is just a lovely hotel! It feels so different than any other hotel I've stayed at. It's special and has a very thoughtful design that is all in the details! Our room feels like a place where we can really relax. It's contemporary style makes it very aesthetically pleasing but it also feels like home. They provide friendly service that is accessible but not overly so. This is a well conceived, very welcome addition to downtown Boise and I will seek out "boutique" hotels from now on for the unique experience it provides!

Service was slow to start, however, once the server approached us I was very pleased. He was very knowledgeable towards all aspects of the menu- very informative. I ordered the Creole Combination, which consisted of red beans and rice and a cup of gumbo. The red beans and rice was full of flavor, especially the beans. Sausage was a nice addition to the dish. The gumbo was delicious- it came served in a warm cup and had a bit of a kick to it. Key lime pie was OUT OF THIS WORLD. It was cold, creamy, and perfect. Would recommend if you are in the area!

First timer. Ordered their turkey chili which was great. Had flavor. Also ordered their turkey provolone panini which was the most unappealing in taste of any sandwich I have eaten out. The turkey had a gamey taste to it and the entire sandwich was hard to chew and bite off even. 
The price was more than I usually pay for lunch. Compared to other establishments in this neighborhood , not worth it. I will attach pictures of the sandwich. I only ate half. It was not worth the effort to chew. 
I wanted to like this place but it did not live up to the hype on the menu.

The best breakfast, lunch, brunch spot in Tucson hands down. The food is great. The staff are the best, even new hires prep and pastry knows how to pick who is right for the job. Chefs at both locations are spot on. I love the food there. I've nearly tried the entire menu, and always up for what chef Hannah has to offer with the French toast. I love both locations central and east
My mom, daughter and I stumbled across this place and we loved it!! Everything was great!! Great sandwiches, soups and salads.  Homemade breads and desserts!! We will be back!

I placed a delivery order for chicken chow mein, broccoli with garlic sauce, and chicken with garlic sauce. They only sent ONE correct order to us, the chicken with garlic sauce. The other two orders were beef with garlic sauce and chicken and cabbage with no noodles. When I called back to ask if they could resend the order and I would give them the incorrect orders back, she yelled and stated that chicken chow mein DOES NOT include noodles, only lo mein does. I'm not Chinese, but I'm pretty sure that "chow mein" translates to "fried noodles." I would recommend never ordering from this restaurant if you want a correct order.. or chow mein WITH noodles. They said the only way they would correct the order was if we brought it back to them.. which doesn't make sense because we ordered delivery and they messed up. The only good thing was how quickly we received the incorrect order.

I worked for the Service Manager many years ago at their Toyota store. He used to call me "youngster." Great manager who taught me a lot about life. I was talking to a friend, who also was an advisor and the one who introduced me to the manager, and I was reflecting on how the current Service Manager was the most honest manager I ever worked for. I can guarantee you that if you go to Conicelli for service, you will be given a fair and honest price.

Excellent food. 

The place wasn't  as clean as one should expect. Every table had crumbles and left overs. Had to engage two staff members to do the job right since the first one  couldn't do nuts. 
Thank you staff member #2 who was apparently on her break but still did the job and in the right way and spirit 

Excellent food is a combination of great prep + clean ambiance + friendly staff

In regards to the museum, it was great.  In regards to one particular staff member...  She was horrible.  My family came to visit from Columbus.  We have a three year old and a 20 month old.  When we came in, we were politely informed by three separate people in the space of 60 seconds that our kiddie 2 seater wagon was not allowed in the museum.  In case we didn't hear it the first two times in the space of ten seconds.  Even though I was trying to get my kids unbundled and out of the wagon so I could get my husband to return it to the car.
That's fine.  I understand the concern.  But what got me was the woman who was standing 8 feet away from me as we were waiting for him to return complaining to the security guard in a very audible voice about how she couldn't understand WHY anyone would bring a wagon instead of a stroller.  And how she wanted to make sure we got rid of it.  And why kids would need a wagon anyway?  And on and on.  

Incredibly rude.  I followed the rules.  I put up no argument.  And you're still going to be snide?

 The museum is nice.  The kids area was nice.  The trains were cool. I sincerely hope they do well and spread understanding and better knowledge of Native American culture.   But I'm not coming back.

I'd say this was five stars except for the fact that the adjoining bar/ restaurant was ridiculous- the staff was so in the weeds it was a twenty minute wait at the bar on a Friday night.  On an up note, hotel staff and accommodations were absolutely perfect .

New to Philly and glad to find such a great place like this! All great experiences from scheduling an appointment to the finished product. Great cuts, great convos. Excited to make this my new go to barber shop!

Wow, what a disappointment. It's a pretty building in a pretty place, hence the 2 stars. The service was terrible. I very rarely leave a bad review but this place deserves it. When I booked the room it was for 2 people and their "bay breeze package" but when I got here I was told the reservation was only for 1 person. This resulted in an additional charge of over $50 to add my daughter back onto the package. Since it was my first time at the hotel and it was their error, I asked if there was a comp- 1 front desk person and 2 supervisors later I was able to get 1 free drink at the bar for a house brand drink. Really? All that work for a $4 glass of wine? When my daughter's cold got worse and then she couldn't use the additional service I just paid for, neither the hotel or the spa would work with us to rebook the service, issue a gift certificate or anything else. The room was ok, nothing special. The hot tub and pool were ok, but creepy later in the evening due to poor lighting and minimal staff. Save yourself money and stay some other place that is more customer oriented.

I have to agree with majority of other Yelpers here - the quality of both the food & customer service are way off. I ordered a buffalo chicken wrap & sweet potato fries & the delivery man practically threw it onto my porch like a newspaper. The flour wrap was stiff & tasted kind of stale & the sweet potato fries were way undercooked. I have had their lasagna before & really liked it so maybe I'll stop in & try that to see if redemption is possible.

This was my first visit so I went with the steak teriyaki. It was so good but I was jealous when I saw my boyfriend's dish. He ordered the Bibimap which is pictured in the large stainless bowl. Both dishes were fantastic. Note: it gets pretty busy at lunchtime during the week so plan ahead.

After a big lunch, we decided to swing by District Donuts and give the donuts here a try. Being in the middle of the afternoon, there wasn't a long line, and getting seating inside wasn't too hard either. The vibe is pretty relaxed, with a spacious feel, some industrial finishes, and spacious booths, bar seating, and some outdoor spots as well if you want to sit down. Most of the attention was focused on the donuts, but as the name suggests, they also serve sandwiches and coffee here - so a little bit of everything for everyone. We ended up sticking with donuts, trying out the chocolate glaze, spicy maple praline, and cookies and cream.

How'd it shake out? To be honest, I was a bit underwhelmed given the hype that I had seen on here (and other places on the Internet). The donuts are very much on the thicker and denser side, and outside of the maple praline, I didn't think the frosting really stood out relative to other donuts I have had. I do have a soft spot in my heart (and belly) for maple donuts, which explains why I liked that the best flavor-wise - but it also didn't have any hint of spiciness at all, which makes me wonder why the description even bothered. The chocolate glazed donut was very average to me, and the cookies and cream was also pretty generic...there was only a small sprinkling of cookies on top.

Overall, the donuts are different from what you'd pick up at a Krispy Kreme or Dunkin' Donuts, but it didn't measure up to the uniqueness (and tastiness) of other donut-centric shops that I have been to. I would like to come back and try the sandwiches, which looked tasty, but from a donut standpoint, I came away full but a bit disappointed relative to expectations.

I really wanted to like this place! I was looking forward to eating here for a long time. Finally decided to pull the trigger. When I had seen the menu, I was super excited. We ordered a few items from each category, we really wanted to get the full experience. Nothing really wow'd us at all. The concept, menu and food items are fantastic. The execution on the other hand was very weak. The food and flavors needs some work. I hope much success to them!

Stopped in for breakfast on a rainy Sunday afternoon.  We didn't have to wait but a minute for our table for two. It was the smallest table for two I've ever sat. Despite that, we had an amazing meal. You don't come here for atmosphere or experience....just amazing food. I had the shrimp and grits. I'm not a southern so grits is not often in the top of my list but it's one of the things out waitress recommended and I am so glad that she did. It was out of this world. Warm, creamy, cheesy and savory with ample and flavorful shrimp.  My partner had a more traditional breakfast with eggs bacon toast hash browns and pancakes. It was good. But he admitted he chose poorly once has tasted mine. The pancakes were excellent btw. Cake like.
Good pizza and great delivery.  Right on time.  I liked the eggplant parm pizza a lot.  The pepperoni was OK.  I'll definitely order from there again.

What a gem! My husband and I were staying in the Treme, and Lil' Dizzy's Caf was recommended by our Airbnb host. It was a quick walk and we are so glad we made the trip! We were there for breakfast (their lunch does not start until 11, so if you want fried chicken you have to go after that time!) That said, breakfast was incredible! I had the shrimp grillade, their version of shrimp and grits, with a homemade biscuit, and my husband had a jambalaya omelette. So tasty! Exactly the comfort food we needed on a chilly winter NOLA day. The service was incredible; everyone made us feel very welcome and we saw three or four folks during our dining experience, including the owner, all helping to make our experience positive. The music station they play is pretty great too. We truly loved it and will definitely be back! Best breakfast in the Treme for sure!

Ox tail pho made for a great meal and the crepe appetizer was a hit with the table. My gf got the crab and garlic noodles, but they were out of crab so they upgraded to the lobster at no extra cost. Turned out the lobster was fantastic! Only down sides were the duck was dry and touch and the taps were not yet installed, the taps will be up and running soon. Hopefully the duck prep will improve or change to something else...

Nice but expensive! I live in the Chicago area so I know that goceris can be costly but this place was more than I normally pay. I had to stop in while visiting family to get some salad fixings since I that was my potluck dish to bring.

Everything cost more than at home - lettuce, tomatoes, vinegar and herbs!

The store is big and has lots of food to go options with sushi and a salad bar but the layout seems a bit awkward as I kept having grocery cart traffic jams I need many areas.

It's nice but not worth the price!

The place is very nice & if your a sports fan they have TVs placed so you won't miss the game every seat here is placed so u can see the tv, ordered the 1/2 plate chicken & fri-tip pretty good & the servers are very friendly & great selection of libations

Cracker Barrel rarely disappoints. Wish there was one on Long Island. Went with a party of 4 and ordered the special cinnamon French toast special. It was as good as advertised. The wait for a table was a bit long but the food was fast and the waitress attentive.

We were slow to try Pica's....our loss. Quality is outstanding, portions generous. Grilled chicken Alfredo, chicken Parmesan sandwich and seared scallops. Yum, yum and yum! Warm bread and sauted peppers to table at start. Reasonable pricing for quality food! We'll be back. And, staff is friendly and professional. An all around win.
The Classic Roast Beef sandwich was excellent!! The baked Mac and cheese was ok and the Chai latte was low key! :/

This place has went down hill to me. At first, when it was just the owner at the one store on linbergh, the food was amazing. It seems since he started branching out, the service and food has not been up to par. I think they lost my service.
This is a really cute place!!! We love the customer service and the food is really good! We also had coffee and tea. Would totally recommend this place!!!

This is the best lunch spot in the area. Everything is made fresh, so it's easier for them to customize dishes for dietary restrictions. I became vegan in July 2017, and they've been so accommodating! My favorite dish is the tofu teriyaki and yaki udon. You can't go wrong with the Traditional or tacos or hot chicken if that's your thing.

Well, lots to say. Managers were busy makin coffee drinks and totally ignoring the business. Tables were ready and set but empty. The "15 minute wait" became 30. People that work there appear to be miserable and in slllloooowwww motion. Waiter brought table next to us their food holding a dirty rag and said "this is a really hot plate. The heat is coming through this rag."  Ummm. After seeing and hearing that we were kinda disgusted. Our meal was fair. My skillet was hot but the food was not. Sad- the menu is great but will not return unless a major re-do happens.

Went with a group of 8 people during brunch on a Sunday. Staff was friendly and accommodating! Food was delicious - not a single person at our table had a complaint. Speedy service, yet we didn't feel rushed to get out. Definitely a lovely experience and we're looking forward to our next brunch date here!
Great local brewery!!! I was lucky enough to taste every beer they had on tap ( thanks Shawna) and even took a growler back home with me. Ignore the fake reviews that you see below.

I enjoyed a good dinner here. It is a small restaurant, but has a nice selection of Peruvian dishes. I had an excellent Chicken Causa for an appetizer followed by Palta a la Reinga salad. My Lomo Saltado was well seasoned, but the beef was tough and a little over cooked.   They also had Cusquea and Crystal Peruvian beers. 

For a Friday night, the place was pretty quiet. Given my love of Peruvian food, it is a sure bet I will be back.

I always love chick fil a. The food is consistently delicious and service is always wonderful. This location is no different. In fact, I think the service was even better than normal. They handled the lunch rush with efficiency. The playground area is clean. I love how the bathrooms have extra wipes and diapers just in case. Staff was courteous and very helpful. I would definitely come back.

My girlfriend and I were in the mood for Mexican and saw that this place had really great Google reviews. Our GPS seemed to have a really hard time finding it. When we finally did find it, we realized it was attached to the Bayside Inn Hotel on US19. We almost didn't go inside as we drove around the building and noticed that the hotel seemed to house less than savory folk. We were starving though, and just figured we'd go inside to take a look. We were instantly pleased with the service we received upon entering. The waitress was very pleasant and the establishment was clean. We ordered the house margaritas, which were delicious. We ordered the Vallarta fajitas for 2, which was a combination meat fajita platter. It arrived fast, was seasoned perfectly, and actually probably could have served 3-4 people. We spent $44 for 4 margaritas and the $23.99 fajita platter, which we felt was fair. I believe we now have a new favorite Mexican spot. It's a shame it's attached to the hotel, and isn't easily identifiable. It deserves its own building. We will be back. Thanks for the great food and service!

I found this awesome place while playing Pokemon Go (2 gyms in the parking lot). The workers there are very cool and friendly. I was offered help and samples of their different brews immediately upon entering. The guy who helped me was very knowledgeable about how the beers were brewed and what went into each batch.

I ended up buying a custom 6-pack of three of their beers: Tripel Horse, Belgian Freeze, and Oatmeal Milk Stout. All the brews were very smooth and had no lingering after taste like Heineken, bleh.

I'm not a beer lover (I only love vodka), but the River Horse brews are TASTY, creamy, and rich. It's nice to savor my drink instead of drinking to get drunk. I definitely need to get my air fryer so I can enjoy more River Horse brews with some fish n chips!

Overall, I'm very pleased with their product and I'm happy that a local, family run NJ brewery is doing very well!

St. Louis is always little slow on food trends, but I was super excited to hear poke was finally starting to arrive!

This place has been on my radar even before it opened, thank you social media. My spouse and I checked out PokeDoke for dinner one night. Parking was pretty difficult to find, but it's to be expected as this restaurant is located in CWE.

I was having trouble figuring out which of the three sizes to choose. Small, regular, or large. I decided to go with the small which came with two scoops of protein. I had two scoops of the salmon with a base of white rice. I went with the medium poke sauce, but I think I'm going to go with the spicy next time. Toppings: mango, seaweed salad, masago, green onion, friend onion, and wasabi, all topped with a drizzle of wasabi mayo.

I'm not sure I can say it's the best poke I've ever had in my life, but it sure was tasty. The salmon was pretty good, I liked the poke sauce that was used. The toppings went really well with the meat and the rice. I really just see poke as a deconstructed sushi roll, which I already love. I was really surprised as to how full I was at the end of the meal. Though I chose the smallest size, I was pretty stuffed. If I had chosen the regular size, I would've been very uncomfortable.

I thought prices were fair. A small bowl is $10, while a sushi burrito from Blk Mkt Eats was $9 or $10. Not a big difference.

It is unfortunate that with such a unique location and such a brand and product offering this specific store offers such lousy service. The wait is endless, no one is available to help and at Christmas time getting a gift wrap is act of God that requires endless wait. I bought gifts and knew that the wait for wrapping would be long SO I even left my items at the store to be gift wrapped at their leisure. They were not even moved from the counter where I bought them when I returned almost two hours later ready for pick up. This was a gift that needed to be given and The staff COMPLETELY "dropped the ball" on my time constraints! 

I love their stuff, but today was my last shopping experience at this location: couldn't get a gift wrapped after being assured that it could be done in a timely fashion???  I'll  cancel my card, do everything online and try not to go there if I can. It's really a shame!

Found there to be a good variety of food for a late night dinner with young kids. Wish we had one this good near us in upper PA. Person that rang us in was friendly and helpful. Two things  made our experience top notch. First was out waiter Eric, who was friendly, observant, went out of his way to get odd requests, and quick to getting back to us.  Eric is the type of waiter you would find a quality sit down restaurant.  The other were the 2 people at the grill house station. When I asked to have shrimp not basted due to a pepper allergy that offered to get different tings to remove them from the grill. I appreciated their thoughtfulness.

Awesome place and good food. Had the cheesesteaks with mushroom cheese whiz (first time having cheese whiz) and the fries with old bay seasoning. It was awesome. The staff was on point and the place was comfortable. Barely got a sit even on a Sunday. Good place to eat in Philly.

We came in and were quickly greeted and seated with friendly service.  After a quick perusal of the menu and a few questions, we ordered.  Antipasto first.  Pasta special, wild boar over home made pappardelle as a first/pasta course, and a rib eye for her and the rabbit for him.

Antipasto:  diverse and excellent.  A+

Pasta/first course: (one or two which were home made but all fresh), the  special, wild boar over home made pappardelle was savory with some wine noticeable, would have liked more texture from the boar, but delicious.  A

After a bit of a wait, we moved on to our entres. Not long enough to knock points off, but long enough to start throwing the pacing off.

Her rib eye had a good char and was cooked nicely. Tough and dry, though; an insult to a rib eye.  C-

His rabbit: fork off the bone tender; something in the sauce I want crazy about. Something almost sickly about it.  C

Service was slow but very good. A

Atmosphere: noisy and tight. Warm inside, enough where we were getting antsy.  C-

Appetizers and first course pasta were very good, entrees were disappointing; a mixed bag for us. Pre dinner: A, Entrees: C-. Might have been better off with the boar as an entre. Pasta as a regular course seems a safer bet than their regular entres.

One of the best in Collingswood?  Not for us.

I ordered via Eat24 on Yelp for pick-up and it was very fast.  The food was good for American Chinese food and the quality was good as well.  I enjoyed the combination dinners and the portions were in line with other similar restaurants.  I would not recommend the hot and sour soup.  The General Tso's chicken and Beef with Garlic Sauce were both good.  Bubble tea was pretty good as well.  Solid choice for a quick and tasty meal.

We had a wonderful experience with this company. The owner was conscientious--he kept an eye on things, and made sure we were completely satisfied. But the workers themselves made sure they did a good job! They could not have been more clean and careful, inside and out. We had star bolts put in, which meant they had to cut holes in the living room ceiling. They hung plastic and put down drop-cloths, and since they had to work over three days, the plastic had to be taken down and then put back in place every single day, so we could use our front door. They were always cheerful, polite, and terribly pleasant. The ceiling looked as good as new when they were done. The outside work involved repointing and repairing and recoating the stucco. The job was done impeccably. Our neighbours were very impressed. So are we. We'd use them again in a heartbeat.

Incredible.

We ordered the pastrami poutine as an app, my bf got the pork fried rice and I got the curried cauliflower. The poutine came with a house-made hot sauce that was like a mix between buffalo sauce and sweet BBQ. The fried rice came with two sauces and the dish tasted nice and nutty, almost like a peanut sauce, and the cauliflower came with a harissa sauce. Portion sizes were perfect and not skimpy

The food was all super fresh and really flavorful - you could tell they care about the quality of their ingredients.

Whole bill came to $48. Not too bad for really awesome food. We didn't order any drinks. 

Our awesome server, Amanda, let us know that we could sample the gelato even without getting any. We didn't plan to, but I noticed they had a few fun sorbet options aside from the traditional orange and strawberry - super refreshing find being dairy free! I tried the pineapple + habanero, apple cider and grapefruit sea salt. Cider was definitely my favorite!

Burger restaurant in the hotel. Good burgers but you have a choice of single or double ( 1/3 lb) patty's. Two sounded like too much sine a half pounder is all I would want to eat. However the single was too small for a hungry person so get the double. Not as large after cooking. I ordered s bourbon and was asked if I wanted a single or double!! Switched the order to a bottle of wine when I heard that. I'm not a fan of measured pours at a bar.

I am not sure why this restaurant has such high reviews.  The quality of food is okay and the prices are high.  They do not have a lunch menu and most Thai restaurants serve soup and egg roll with lunch.  I will not go back because there's too many Thai restaurants with lower prices and better quality food as well as a nice lunch menu with lots of options.
Decent atmosphere to watch sports, and is on the water. However, the food is expensive and not good. Would go back for drinks and a game. But do not go here hungry.
They did an amazing job the other day! My car was a wreck and they made it look brand new. I'll will be going back.

Very disappointing.  We ordered 2 appetizers and 2 pizzas and after an hour sitting and waiting nothing came out.  When we asked about appetizers they said they were really busy with take out orders. Young male manager on duty was really rude with my wife. Obviously has no managerial experience.  I suggest they downsize and do strictly carry out. Regardless I will never be back.

A bit pricey but worth it.  There are not many authentic Korean restaurants in Reno. This new place is hip - trendy and very delicious. I prefer the Korean fried rice and Korean chicken wings over the bab bowls All the ingredients are very fresh and flavorful. Staff is very nice and helpful. They have a reward card which gives you a free menu item after 10 purchases.

We eat here regularly. I ordered takeout for the first time last night. I wasn't sure how takeout would compare to dining in. Silly, but I've had bad experiences elsewhere. Order was correct and just as good as dining in. The location is sketchy, but I say this is hands down the best Indian food in Tucson. The staff/owners are super friendly and very accommodating. Masala is phenomenal!
The aesthetics of the place is amazing and the food is pretty bomb too. I love it, I would highly recommend

Super yummy macarons! My favorite was the vietnamese coffee! I would love to try other flavors such as green tea, lavender, and earl grey! But I'm aware their macarons are made randomly. I have to say the macarons here are better than la bonne bouchee I can eat more than one macaron here without having a belly ache. Usually when I am working on my second macaron at la bonne bouchee, my belly is hurting, thinking I'm just consuming too much sweets lol. My nephew had a cake made here which was the artwork was amazing!! The kids in the family killed all the fondant. I wasn't a fan of the cake, it was too sweet for my liking and that's just the cake itself with no fondant. I'm up to try their other pastries next time!
Super fresh! They made me spicy crab for me, which was awesome! We will so be going back!
We called AAA this morning and they sent a K&S tow truck, driven by Rob. He was very personable, respectful, knowledgable, and helpful. We're very appreciative!

delicious food
lots of parking
kind staff
cool atmosphere
appropriate pricing

quick heads up- there are two dining options

Chinese and a la carte sushi
or
all you can eat sushi

you cannot have a mixed group because all you can eat sushi diners have a separate place to eat.

Nice looking brewery/bar. Wanted to go here for a while, it's super close to my apt... first thing ordered was a Flight of beers (picture) for $7 you can choose 4 beers. I really like malted beers so I enjoyed a lot the Smoke porter and House Amber (Not malted) from those 4. Also got the King Louie (full size) which was really good! If you like that kind of beers. Get it! Won't regret it!.

Food... got the prime burger (per serve recs) was good, the meat was juicy and tasty! Nothing to die for, but a good solid burger. (It came with fries, which were well... regular and nothing exciting fries fries. Last but not least, the service was good, our server was attentive and nice. 

I see myself going back and getting some drinks here but won't go just for food. It wasn't bad but not super good either so...

Seriously it doesn't get any better than this. I had the chili dog and fries and it was delicious. It's so great to finally find a place that is authentic! Best dogs in town! Paulie is very personable and remembers your order is you're a regular!

I am here once every couple months and it is always a hit for the lunch specials. Soup or salad, app and main dish for under $12. Sold.
Very friendly service. You can be in and out in 40 minutes if you know what you want fairly quick. Very nice portions and they will cater to the level of spicy you prefer (1 thru 4 I believe). Go with a 2 if you want some spice, but not enough to distract you from your meal.
My favorite dish currently is the Vegetarian Pad Thai. Tons of colorful veggies and tofu to boot. I'm drooling just thinking about it now. I find the Drunken Noodles to be a bit on the oily side, so I don't typically order this one there, even though I it is one of my go to dishes for thai food. 
They are closed Mondays. Chicken Satay special for app. on Tues. and Thursdays only. BYO as well.

Of all the ears of I've gone there , I finally got a friendly attentive waiter (I wish I could recall his name ). The food is just ok , but my whole family races that they have the best Clam
Chowder anywhere . The drinks are just ok . The bar service is slow . It's always full because the restaurant is all outdoors and have a great view (The Gulf). They have live music on certain nights and the local love it . I only go there if someone's asks me to.

Tried them twice , first time got lasagna and sent it back cause every bite was crunching cause it was over cocked , second time tried the pizza , and had to send it back as well , they do have have good cocktails to be fair

I found records I forgot about a long time ago. So wonderful to browse through the LPs and take a trip down memory lane. This is a fantastic store to pick up gifts for friends! I even found a bunch of foreign language LPs and CDs that I had to have.
FALSE ADVERTISEMENT!!! That hot sign is always on & I rarely get hot donuts. Turn off the light sometimes

A tragic facedown fall yesterday left my iPhone 6S screen shattered. After thorough research, I found this location to be both the most reasonably priced and best-rated option. I got almost a dozen quotes within a 15 miles radius and Experimac was the only one that cost under $70, provided both the glass and LCD replacement, and didn't require an appointment.

I decided to bring my phone in at lunch and pick it up in the afternoon. I had never been before, but when I went in, the store was very clean, well organized and pleasant to be in! Justin said he'd get started on my phone right away so I decided to wait for it. It was repaired in about 20 minutes and they even threw in a glass protector screen for free.

Their products come with warranties and are clearly high quality. The people at the store are pleasant and helpful! If you find a lower price for the same repair service, I have a feeling they'd be willing to match it.

So glad I got my phone fixed instead of paying an exorbitant amount for a replacement!

I came here for a work dinner and we all enjoyed ourselves. Our service was pretty good! He was really nice and answered our questions but he did offer to go over the specials. I mean the specials were listed at the table but I thought It was weird he didn't say anything about them. The waiter said the rigatoni was their most popular dish, so naturally I ordered It. I thought It was good but safe, It wasn't busting with flavor. My coworker ordered the octopus ink pasta and said he felt like It was undercooked. Overall, I enjoyed the restaurant and I would go back!
Always a pleasure to come here. Relaxing and such a great pedicure. They make you feel so relaxed while pampering you.
Simply amazing!!! I could eat here everyday. The spot there before was mediocre so I wasn't to keen on trying now I'm addicted... chorizo queso is the best!!!
We love the rolled ice cream here! The choice of toppings is also a big hit with the kids. A nice change from those other ice cream shops.

Top notch food. I ordered the 3 course meal and everything was beyond super deliciousness!!! Our waiter Jenna was amazing, knowledgeable and fun. She made our experience sheer perfection. I can't thank the staff enough for making my birthday dinner heaven on my taste buds.

I had the popcorn chicken, wontons in spicy chili oil, pig stomach and mustard green soup, and beef chow fun.

Popcorn chicken: Mediocre. The breading was too thick and a little bland. I tasted some sweetness, which I found unusual for popcorn chicken. Definitely could have done without.

Wontons in spicy chili oil: Flavorful with a good spicy kick. They actually give you a decent amount considering it is an appetizer. I'd recommend if you like spicy!

Pig stomach and mustard green soup: I've actually never had the soup prior to my visit here, but was up to try something new. It has a pickled/sour taste from the mustard greens,the pig stomach has a slightly chewy texture, and there is a white peppery taste in the broth. I was actually surprised that I liked the soup.

Beef chow fun: The noodles were a little too al dente for my liking and I think it could have used a little more soy sauce or flavoring.

Overall, reasonably priced food, good variety, and food is pretty decent. Very casual ambiance and only had to wait a few minutes for a party of two. Next time i'm in Reno, i'd probably return.

There's a Yelp deal- 10% off your bill of $45+ and the restaurant also has an app (101 Taiwanese) which sometimes has coupons, but when I went I didn't find any current coupons.
This is an amazing place. I had Beauty and the beast and it was fantastic. The was barely a line which made it even better. I will difiniity be going back.

This place is definitely up there with the good Pho places in the area. It's major advantage is the design your own Pho soup. I definitely never was able to order a tofu, flank, and brisket combo anywhere until I came here. Fried spring rolls were considered good at the table (I couldn't eat due to shrimp allergies). Eating area is spacious and staff is good. I definitely recommend.

Unprofessional manager, that manager I spoke to was not
listening to me at all.
 He would talk as fast as he could and would not let me say what I call for, every time I say something he would start talking and keep talking just running all over my words, neither of us listening to each other, only escalated voice tones.
It was not worth the 10% which was about $20.00, I would save by using my government issued veterans id card but because of some verbiage that was not on the ID, Home Depot decline the discount.  The cashier interrogated me took my ID looked at it then at me and said I could not use the Id, I never had a problem before.  She stop talking and stood there waiting for my money.  The manager did not want to hear me out and the check out person were  both very disrespectful and rude.

I went with about 11 of my girlfriends. The server did a great job handling all of our orders and attitudes. The oysters were great. But a few of my girls had the shrimp and grits, it was cold. Someone had the power boy which she said was great. I had the gumbo which was ok. All in all the atmosphere is great. I would go again.

This place is a gem!! Almost a hidden one, as I walked past many times since I moved to the area couple of months ago bbt never noticed it. Through yelp, I saw it, and when I saw the pictures of the gelato, I jumped out of bed and went there as fast as possible. Capofitto did not disappoint. The gelato (I had pistachio and bacci chocolate) and the espresso were to die for!! I spent a summer in Italy where I ate gelato everyday, and ever since I came back to the US, I was not able to find a place that satisfied my tastes and love for gelato--except for the Italian chain Grom in NYC. I'm so happy and the same time sad that it took me two months to find this place in Philly. On top of that, the guy that served me, Craig, was super friendly and nice. Would definitely be returning there many times, and only if the prices were lower, I'd probably go there many times a day! Can't wait to also try their pizza, as I'm sure as everything I tried so far, it will be amazing.

Needed a battery for my Lexus.  Drove over to AutoZone in Roxborough at 9 am Sunday morning.  Easy transaction, had the new battery installed within minutes!  Thank you for getting my car back on the road again!
Cashier was very rude fat Hispanic girl at the airport location. Very very rude. Half the menu wasn't even available.

In total agreement that this is just like a Las Vegas Strip hotel...HUGE, EXPENSIVE, but it is also clean, beautiful, and lots to see and do.  I recommend packing a big, rolling suitcase full of food and beverage to take to your hotel room, (and it will be a HIKE!) but it will save you mega bucks.  You will pay $8.00 for a Bud Light here.) I wish I had paid extra for a room with a balcony, and had smuggled in some food, and could people watch while pre-gaming!
I enjoyed the sushi and service at Wasabi. I had a TERRIBLE $7 breakfast biscuit from Conservatory Cafe. Also I was not impressed with Sheldon, the front desk manager who made my check in more difficult and lengthy than it had to be. 
Place was decked out for the Holidays, glad I visited  in December.

Reno has a lot of great AYCES places. THIS IS NOT ONE OF THEM. 

Horribly let down by other reviewers who rated this place 4+ stars. Fish tastes like catfood. The kind of sushi you expect from the little teriyaki/sushi places in Sacramento. Perhaps other guests missed this because every roll has either jalapenos or hot sauce to cover up the flavor. 
If Reno has any taste at all, this place will fail within a year.  

The gyoza and miso are delicious, load up. 

Edit: I let them know it wasn't great and they only charged me for one roll. Otherwise this would be a 1-star rating.

Really nice family owned jump center. Great selection of bouncers, nice secluded toddler area. Love the giant air bag, great attraction! No outside food or drinks allowed, but they have a stocked snack bar and a large area to sit and eat. My only complaint is that the air conditioning could be better. Other than that, great indoor play area with LOTS of room to grow!

This place is terrible. They wouldn't serve me because of the color of my skin. We ended up waiting for our shitball ass food for 2 hours and one 8 oz drink took us 45 minutes. Very polite and courteous waiter though

One of my favorites to take out of town guests to, or for any special occasion. Intimate setting that it great for conversation and the food is exceptional. Friendly, family-oriented restaurant that you can tell has stood the test of time for a reason. This place is an experience! Be sure to wear stretchy pants because you will be FULL when you leave. :)

The beer is good!! They have tables to sit. They have board games to play. It was fun to just sit and have a few drinks. My wife is pregnant and she can't drink(the only reason she beat me in trivia Pursuit). They have popcorn you can buy there(cheddar and cheddar and Carmel mix). You can earn rewards for visiting there. I paid with a card and everything was easy and receipt was sent to my phone. 

Food***You can order from cluster truck they deliver to the parking lot. 1st time ordering you get 10% off Cluster truck has a ton of food options. And the food is Fantastic. You order from an app and they accept Apple Pay too. The reason I focus on the food is because good beer is good beer, but having food too is rare. They also have a stage area for small concerts. I will go back!! Oh and the bathroom has to be one of the cleanest public bathrooms I've used.(just saying)
Love this place! First time going and I will def be back. Got gel manicure and eyebrow wax. Staff was friendly, store was quiet & professional. Def a little hidden gem.
This place is amazing. Staff is friendly. Food is great. Don't miss out on the chorizo and cheese empanada! Chips and guacamole are also amazing. Make sure you check in to get a free empanada.

Being a Missouri girl, I was raised on BBQ. Eli knows how to bbq. It's all about the meat and the smoke. The ribs are my favorite. They are tender, pulling off the bone just right. The chicken, sides and bbq sauce are great but the meat is the KING.

Always worth the wait. Filling this review out after I've gone a few times (5-6 times). Immaculate baked goods, inspiring latte combinations, creative soulful brunch food. I recommend grabbing a latte and a baked good to munch on while you wait. 

I've had few dishes I haven't loved.  I normally find it hard to narrow down the options, I normally ask the wait staff bc there always seems to be a few dishes that rise above the others. The sorghum bacon is always pretty impressive and a crowd pleaser and I've definitely ordered a few different versions of the Dutch baby. Happy brunching!

The husband had a hankering for Asian food so we decided to check out this new Thai restaurant based on the reviews. We were not disappointed. We started of with their pork & shrimp dumplings. They looked more like Shu mai which was different than what we expected but very delicious. They have 4 spice levels; mild, medium, hot, & Thai hot.
