They are not kidding around with how spicy their food is. Normally I order the Pad Thai the first time I visit a Thai restaurant but decided to try the spicier Garlic Beef at their medium spice level. It was delicious & perfectly spicy. The hubby got the Panang curry chicken, medium spice, & it was delicious & perfectly spiced too. The portion sizes were just right. We finished off our meal with their sweet, sticky rice with mango. OMG, it was the best I've ever had! They use the black rice & it was warm & drizzled with hot sweetened, condensed milk. The mango was perfectly ripe & there was more than 2-3 slices. We will definitely go back. The hubby wants to try something hot.
Attention Vegans - they have a separate menu of dishes just for you!

My sister discovered this restaurant and our family is so happy to have some authentic Salvadoran food. Food is great but the service is sometimes slow, so don't be in a rush when you go. Pupusas and the Bistec Salvadoreano -- yum!

The atmosphere is very nice. I always am leery of "hipster" spots but this place is legit. Super friendly and not pretentious staff. Female bartender made one of the best Bulleit neat Old Fashioned's I've had out. Other mixed drinks were also prepared well (well balanced without being boozy). I ordered Korean beef tacos. They were not bad but not one of my favorites either. They were still good. The table over got nachos that looked delicious. I also think if a place has a clean bathroom, their kitchen is usually clean too. This place is spotless. I also was impressed to see the bartenders cleaning bottles and the bar in their down time. Overall, I would definitely visit again when I am in town. I'd actually rate this place a 4.5 stars if I could.

Love coming here to get a fully stuffed bagel.....lox is fresh and cream cheese is full of flavor. Ordered an everything bagel with lox & scallion bacon cream cheese and an iced coffee. Everyone is nice that works here and It is truly the perfect Sunday brunch food!

Local brewery with good food and great customer service. The french bread pizza I ordered was cooked in a smoker, which I thought was unique. Although we didn't sit outside, the environment seemed welcoming with a outside fire, string lighting, and a live band (this was on a Thursday).

My wife and 5 kids and I really enjoy the experience... we go quite often... they do a great job accommodating our group of seven... service is predictable and great... they take care of our kids... food comes fast... and is standard Mexican fare... I really enjoy the tacos al pastor!.  It's a rare place where all 5 kids ask to return often... and that's a lot of picky kids to accommodate!

So glad to find this place! The food is simply delicious! Apple salad is the bomb! Honestly, I tried almost everything on the menu and was not disappointed once. Except for the one time when I tried to order lunch and, they could not place my order because they were extremely busy. Which is NOT a bad thing - the food is just this good!

Our Friday night party of eight could not have had a better time. Alexa our server was very attentive. The food was spectacular. Started with the sausage and figs appetizer as well as the fried meatballs both of which were perfectly prepared. Our entrees ranged from the special stuffed veal chop (that was excellent), the always good veal parmigiana, the filet with crab meat and a very well prepared gluten free halibut. Every one enjoyed the food and atmosphere. Topped off the evening with limoncello cake and sorbeto. I look forward to returning to this special treasure in South Philly.
Loved their rooms,  they are beautiful and they have comfortable beds. They have great restaurants, nice bars to hang out at and cute shopping stores. We are definitely coming back.
If you're contemplating on going over there because the wait at breakfast & Burger is too long think again. Just wait your turn and get a table at breakfast & Burger that's all I can say.
No more Maine Root???? No more Pimento cheese??? It's these items that made this place a go to for us. No longer.

Well ordered our food over phone says 25 min. Get here not ready. Taking care of others first. Food still not here. Taking care of others. Than they can't find the order. Person says good food. I look at customer service first. This stinks. Lucky we had what we called in, with us. 20 min later on a call in for food. Finally ready

The good is that these were seriously good burgers--the meat was fresh and the buns were soft and tasty

The only issues were that I called the order in and it took more than 30 minutes for it to be done--when I got it home, the bacon cheeseburger that I ordered "plain" as "only meat, bread and cheese--no condiments or veggies" had the mustard spread in the bread.

So next time I will give them more time to cook and double check the order before I leave--it was really good other than that.
Great bar food, the Cuban is the sh@t.  Awesome Saturday bartender!!  All in all, a great experience.

The best of the best! Great outfitters with great employees. This business cares about its customers,even to the point of closing if conditions are unsafe on the river. That costs them revenue but they put safety first!

This place is great. The staff is friendly and fun. My son wanted to try and they got him set and and learning quickly and safely. Will be coming back! Recommend to anyone in the reno area looking for a fun way to spend the afternoon.
Coffeebar is awesome.  The service is ALWAYS friendly, and my beverage is always tasty.

Bailey's Chocolate Bar moved upstairs and Dave Bailey transformed this space into an entirely new experience. Having recently been to New Orleans, I can tell you the decor is very similar to the trendy & chic little restaurants in the French Quarter. I cannot wait till spring to enjoy the outside dining. 

My dining partner and I started off sharing, a Lump Crab Cake, Blackened Shrimp and a Cornmeal Waffle. My favorite was the Blackened Shrimp that came with a Cucumber Ranch. I tried it, it was cool and refreshing, but I ate my shrimp without it. The spicy flavor, was reminiscent of the cajun seasoning I experienced in NOLA. My DP, favored the Crab Cake. It was topped with slices of grapefruit and avocado. Make sure you get a mixture of all three in every bite. It makes for an interesting combination on your palate. 

Our Cornmeal Waffle was a tad cold, so we sent it back. The second one was warm and served with a large scoop of soft whipped butter. I enjoyed the texture of the cornmeal and the taste, but would have preferred some other type of topping in addition to the butter. Perhaps, a little cup of syrup. After all, it is a waffle. 

We went in different directions on our entrees so we could each sample each others. Being a fan of catfish, I choose the Crab Stuffed Missouri Catfish. It was served on a bed of poblano grits and topped with a garlic dressing. You can not go wrong with crab and catfish in the same dish. 
It's amazing how the older I get, the more I am developing an appreciation for grits. These were some of the best I have had. 

The DP went with the Shrimp and Grits. The shrimp were the same as the Blackened Shrimp we enjoyed as an appetizer. She liked them. They were hard to photograph in a dimly light bar, so trust us when we say they tasted better then they photographed. 

Being a bar diner, I was highly impressed with the comfort and style of the barstools. The back was low, giving good back support and they had armrest for extra comfort. Only thing lacking at the bar was hooks underneath for ladies to secure their purses and outlets to allow social media junkies to keep charged up. 

Nathan was a great bar host and mixologist. He's a transplant from Tulsa and is adjusting to new city very well. Stop by and welcome him to STL. 

Will I return? - I hang out in Lafayette Square - so, YES!

When: December 28, 2017
Why: It's new, hot and trendy. You should go, too.

This place is great! It's a very cozy atmosphere, with around 10-12 tables.  The food was delicious - we had the Melanzane (eggplant parm) appetizer, as well as the Poleptta, which is basically a large meatball. The eggplant was huge, definitely enough to share. Same with the meatball, you only get one - but it's large. For the main course, I had the special of the night, which was fettucini, tomatoes, arugula, and shrimp mixed together with olive oil. Pretty basic, but delicious. My boyfriend had the gnocchi, which he also said was delicious.  Service was good, and the staff (basically one person) was super friendly and attentive. This spot is definitely worth checking out!
Ordered the Korean tacos made from naa bread and meat was very cheap. More than half the meat was fat. Also very little meat overall. Unfortunately did not like my experience.

I saw the 4+ stars and hoped for a serving of good Pad Thai. I was disappointed. The noodles were a lump. They were a funky red color. Overall lacked flavor. My quest for good Pad Thai in South Tampa continues.
My server Janessa was so friendly and polite. We came for brunch and our experience was phenomenal the food was great and Janessa made sure our drinks were always full

Not really worth the price or your time. Took the combined Laura/Oak Alley plantation tour and was gone from 11:45am until after 7pm. That time made so much longer by the fact that we were stuck forever doing drop offs in the French quarter. Those staying there who were lucky enough to jump off the bus and walk after sitting in traffic and not moving were luckier than those of us in the garden district. As the first ones picked up in the morning it would have been nice to not then be dropped off last. The tour at Laura was good, but the tour at Oak Alley was really lacking. And the bus exhaust was so bad during our drive that you could barely stand it. Not worth how much we paid and not worth an entire day/evening if you ask me.

Last Monday I came to TJ's for half of appetizers and discounted burgers. I have been here before multiple times for the same things, so I have never tried anything else on the menu, but I must say that TJ's is definitely worth it during discounted burger night. When I looked at the menu, I realized that there were many burgers that were previously offered that were taken off of the menu (like the TJ's house burger with blue cheese and caramelized onions which was my favorite), but there were new creations added aswell. The burgers were also priced differently, and discounted a little differently than they were before. I got the guacamole bacon burger, it was originally 13.99, but the discount brought it down to 7.75 (so not exactly half off, but close enough). Since their menu got redone, I don't think that the waitress knew exactly how the discounts worked, which is something that my financially aware family would like to know, but she was able to communicated that they were indeed discounted. Appetizers are half off, so there is no confusion with the pricing. I enjoyed my burger, and there was tons of bacon on it, but I'm not a huge guac fan. I'll come back this winter and have their steakhouse burger, which may have been a better choice.

Tried out this place for lunch with my SO. We ordered the tried eggplant, a bowl of their gumbo, and the jumbo Louisiana shrimp "en cocotte."

The waiter brought us bread and butter. Normal baguette and nothing special.

The fried eggplant is served with a marinara sauce. I would have personally wanted more cheese in the eggplant and a thicker sauce, but this was not too bad. The presentation of the dish is also exquisite. The eggplant was served in a small fryer basket on top of a thick cutting board. The sauce was served in a creme brulee sort of cup and also on the same board. I probably won't order the fried eggplant again since I didn't love it, but my SO loved it a lot.

The gumbo has fantastic flavor. The portion is quite small, but the flavors make up for it. It's served with a bit of white rice.

The shrimp and grits is fantastic. Jumbo shrimp was slightly overcooked, but shrimp tastes good regardless. The grits were cooked perfectly with a sauce and served with sausage. This is a delicious Southern staple.

The portions are okay and prices are not too bad for food in Louisiana.

Dont let the buildings past keep you away. The interior and food have undergone a complete remodel. The menu is a great version of modern American fare.
Service was pleasant as well as the flavors in the food. Be sure to order pepper jack cheese sticks with sriracha dipping sauce for a nice departure from the old mozzarella sticks.
We plan to return for dinner soon. You should plan to stop in and try a new Reno spot that's worth the gamble!

I really think the sewing skills are wonderful. I'm a sewer. I don't have room in my house now for the sewing machine I used to have in my previous home. It's an industrial sewing machine. Anyway, the owner's sewing skills are excellent!
She can have my son's school shirts finished in 1/2 a day and the cleaning never smells of that strong solution. The clothes are always impeccably clean!
Don't hesitate to use them.

Anyone upset about this Company should know that the Owner tragically passed a few weeks ago. So - no, your calls will not be answered or returned. No - no one is controlling the emails, notices, etc. So if you continue to get notifications.... please, give the poor woman & her mourning family a break! She. Is. Dead! So save your crappy Yelp reviews for a business owner that can actually reply to you, fight back, make it up to you or just straight up has a Goddam heartbeat!  No need to tarnish anyone's reputation.

Ate here last night and boy was it good! The staff was great, very informative and knowledgeable of the menu. I had the seasonal chicken- it's buttermilk fried chicken and it was served with grits and collards. Having lived in the south, I have a very strong opinion about grits, chicken, and collards and what I was served at The Love is some of the best I've ever had. My mom got the salmon poke and she said it was amazing as well. 

The decor is also great, the cork ceilings absorb some of the noise and it feels very cozy yet chic. 

Only reason it's missing a star is because the dessert menu was a little meh - as someone who's lactose intolerant I couldn't eat 3/5 of what was on the menu.

Their dishes are authentic but with the fair prices. Really satisfied after eating here, highly recommend family to come here to have their dinners! If you are a fan of Taiwanese cuisines, this is a good option :)

After a beautiful autumn walk through the Botanical Gardens I stopped in for lunch. It is basically a old service station turned restaurant, but don't let that throw you off. Trust me - you will love this place. 

Think vintage oil cans and crystal decanters with silver trays and copper tagines. Add to the mix a variety of artisanal gin, rye and Japanese whiskey served over an upbeat but chill background music (Like ARE & BE on Spotify).

I ordered the Ugni blanc with some baba ganoush and the autumn root vegetable tagine. Homemade bread was amazing and everything was delicious. I'll let the photo do the talking.

I'll be back!
Love this place. Come in sit in the back,  relax and have some me time.  They have all types of spiritual  items for sale. Really nice gifts too.

I bought 3 pair of shoes at Marti and Liz Franklin store yesterday. I came back today with one pair that did not fit correctly. The arch was not on right place in shoes. Clearly damaged from beginning. Shoes did have some wear. But as it's used shoes some have more wear than others. When I returned the employee said no we can't take those back in that condition. They are in the condition I bought them. So I asked for a manager. Who was rude and said nope sorry we are taking them back. The hostile attitude of the employees and arrogance is none matched by any store I have ever been too. There was no customer service. I was denied to use their return policy even though I had not had the shoes 24 hours. They said call the main office if I don't like it. This is a Christian company. Which mAkes it even more shocking. They sell used shoes! They are not in new condition. Yet then say they are not in return condition. SHOP AT YOUR OWN RISK! Do not count on their return policy. They are not honest.

Great location but parking an issue. They have 6 assigned spots a block and a half away. No happy hour on Sundays to watch the football games in two very nice bars they have there.

The rooms are not updated. Old TV that did not turn on nor off with the remote. Had to manually do so. They came to fix only to turn on the TV manually. No remote fix.

The sheets were not of fine quality and the shower situation was not ideal. 

I suggest having management sleep in each room every quarter of the year and make. List of improvements. 


Staff knew we were not thrilled and an irritated  sorry was there response to our complaints or suggestions. 

I won't be back...

You need to try this place. I saw the reviews here and thought I would give it a try for a pedicure. I was not disappointed. I got the Spa pedicure and loved every minute of it. My next service is going to be a dipping powder manicure.
We have lost count but think this might be our 7th or 8th Peppermill stay.

It was my first time eating here and it won't be my last! Had an early lunch on a Saturday and they were just starting to get busy. Waitress was friendly and extremely attentive to our needs. Food came out fast and hot. Cheesesteak egg rolls were delicious, even though $10 for 3 egg rolls seemed a bit overpriced. Wings were large and pork sandwich was really good. Only complaint is we were seated in the outdoor/covered patio. Great ambiance, but the sun started shining right in on us. Wish there were some kind of shades they could have pulled down.
VEGAN JUNKFOOD DELICIOUS!!!!!! Who knew you could get a cinnamon roll that taste so good, just so good and it's cruelty free, total WIN WIN! #stayWOKE

Awesome community. Beautiful, clean and well maintained... staff is quick..units are clean and free from bugs and roaches... we have a great time living here at preserve.. would definitely recommend this community
Awesome Pizza! Large pie,wings,and a 2 liter very reasonable , delivered to our hotel . Had the Neopolitan. Fast delivery even on NYE
Prices aren't bad there at all...only prob i have is picking what toppings i want being that there's sooo much to choose from!

I've been here twice and it already feels like I'm visiting a favorite family member when I go in. I had the tres tacos, tomato soup and the lime tarte (like my personality) made me a converted dessert lover. Sabrina and her staff are authentic, gracious people. I can't wait to go back.

Super amazing breakfast spot. Food is amazing, service is amazing, and you don't have to wait in lone at 7am to get a table. I live downtown and this is my go to spot when I don't want to make breakfast.

I've had better. They're new so I'll give them a pass this time. Bowl was poorly put together and the staff lack professionalism. There should be some adult supervision and someone who can train them in customer service.

They do all the little things right (and the big things too). I've taken my family 3 or 4 times recently and I've tried a different sandwich each time. They've all been awesome. My kids always get pizza and it's some of the best (maybe THE best) St. Louis style that I've had. The salads are good. The steak fries are tremendous. They source nearly everything locally (bread, coffee, soda). They make their own ketchup - and it's good. And the owner is engaging, friendly and is very honestly committed to ensuring you have a good experience. Give it a shot, you won't be disappointed.

Brandon is the best electrician in Santa Barbara! I've worked with 2 or 3 others here in town. We've used Brandon for small jobs, medium jobs, and now adding a bathroom to our home. He's working with our Contractor. He shows up when he says he will and he does great work consistently! I tried to send him home one summer, he was working in our attic in unbearable temperatures (we were uncomfortable being in the house), but he stayed and finished the job. I have multiple jobs coming up during our remodel and he's the only guy I'lll use. He'll offer educated opinions and help you make the best decisions. Kind. Professional. Courteous. Smart! I can't say enough!!!!

I have been to Luxury Nails twice now.  Each time I've gone, I've been treated with the utmost kindness from all of the employees there.  It is a clean, calming environment.  Lots of colors to choose from.  I get acrylic fills with gel polish; each time their work has been consistent, and they give a lot of attention to detail.  I have had both Amy and Anne do my nails; both are lovely women.  I arrived without an appointment today, and I was greeted immediately and told there would be a brief wait; it was about 15 minutes, which I find completely acceptable.  I will continue to patronize this business, and I highly recommend it to others!

Never disappointed, great selections excellent customer service.  Food quality is excellent it's always a great time.
Excellent can't say enough about this place.

Great pina coolata, really good tuna bowl and very good shrimp Po boy! Had sausage on it FYI.
Nice and warm on patio because they had additional ceiling heaters not just the stand alone ones.

We love Chase!  The food was wonderful and the service even more so. The atmosphere is warm, fun, inviting, cool! We came while in SB holiday shopping and were wowed by the amazing decorations; everywhere, hanging from the ceiling, atop the bar, and every other place one could be squeezed in. A complete delight. I had the grilled salmon which was excellent, and my husband loved his chicken piccata.  Terrific experience!

I recently graduated from being a short sprinter in college in May and was looking for the perfect fitness facility to give me a hard cardio and resistance training workout. I also studied exercise science and therefore have a very picky attitude towards fitness facilities. However Barry's Boot Camp is the best around! The instructors are amazing and the workouts will kick your butt. Not to mention that the shower facilities are amazing and that there is a protein smoothie bar there as well. I'm extremely happy and pleased to be a member of Barrys Boot Camp and wish that everyone could give it a try. Antonio is amazing

I want this to be a four-star or more place, I really do. Alas, it wasn't in the cards. Let me lay it out real simple like:

Pros:
- excellent ambience
- central location
- easy (car) parking when I visited 
- line is infinitely shorter than Biscuit Love (no line vs. 25 deep)

Cons:
- no apparent bike parking
- coffee took 10 minutes from order to first sip
- portions were small for the price
- eggs benny were amazingly bland, and this is how I judge a breakfast location

There you have it. A solid 3 stars. If my tab for a mediocre small breakfast and slow coffee hadn't been $20, I'd maybe think about 4 stars. Maybe.

You better have lots of time to burn.  We were on vacation so we didn't.  Food was okay, bacon was under cooked, hash browns were over cooked.  We were there for and hour and half, that's a long breakfast.  They did take our drinks off for the delay.

I went here for brunch during my birthday. The service was good and attentive. The food was nothing to rave about. A few of us got the Timpano breakfast, the sausage was good but the eggs were burnt and potatoes not fully cooked. The others who got lunch items made the better choice. Their food came out hot. I would come back here for drinks only. The plus was that if you got the unlimited mimosas there was a bar where you could choose your juices.

Great food in an area that most tourists will visit during their time in New Orleans. We visited for lunch while exploring and found that dress is more casual at lunch. Don't shy away at lunch if you are dressed casually! 

The dill bread to start was delicious and interesting since dill is fairly underused at restaurants. I started with the House Salad that was a bit of a flop, but helped me meet my vegetable requirements. There was plenty of greens with onions and manchego, but the delicious dressing wasn't mixed in properly. The salad tasted like it had been drenched in salt too. My husband started with the Crab Cake and that was delicious! It had nice pieces of crab and a definite creole flavor with the seasoning. 

I ordered the Shrimp & Grits which was delicious. The shrimp were good and the sauce and grits were tasty. The flavors of this dish were spot on. My husband ordered the Etouffee Pasta and that was probably the best food of our entire trip. The flavor of this dish was outstanding. Despite liking my meal I would definitely order this next time. 

Our waiter was friendly and professional. The restaurant was busy, but we were still taken good care of for our dining experience.

I can't tell you how exciting it is to find a restaurant that not only has gluten-free options, but is entirely gluten-free. Everything on the menu is safe and delicious. 
I had the Italian sandwich on garlic bread (a little slim on the meats), and a lemon cupcake. Everything was so good that people who are not gluten-free would enjoy it as well. 
I finished my meal and I feel great! It's been a rarity to be able to say that these days, and I will absolutely return if I am back in the city again!!

Wow! The manager Brian is the worst! I'm sorry but what manager cusses at customers and refuses to fix a sandwich? Don't come here if you want your order to be right. Sorry there are other Bully's locations that can get things right.

What a poor excuse for a restaurant, and I already expect hotel restaurants to be expensive and mediocre but the prices here were ridiculous and not posted on the menu. 

I asked if there were any other options on the breakfast menu for kids and he said they do things a la carte, like eggs, bacon, fruit....one of the a la carte things we ordered was three eggs....we paid $5 for the first two and then $3 for the 3rd. What's that about? And $5 for a drip coffee? The most overpriced coffee chain doesn't charge that for a venti. 
In the end we paid over $50 for 1 order of croissants (2), 2 miniature danishes, a small bowl of cold oatmeal and 3 slices of bacon and 3 scrambled eggs. 

We should have just braved the cold like we did for every other meal when we were staying at Hotel Monaco.

Delicious. There was a huge crowd when I went and it's the middle of December, but the lines always move quickly. Plus you always get to see dogs there. Chocolate ice cream with hot fudge and cookie dough  never disappoints.
Food was so amazing! Andy made the best Guacamole... his food and drink  recommendations were spot on! We will definitely be back... hopefully we will be lucky enough to have Andy make our guac!

First of all what a beautiful salon it  has a very elegant feel. I had gotten a gift card for microblading which I never had and wasnt sure I even wanted it.  For some reason I was losing a lot of eyebrow hair for some time.  I had my proceedure with Annie Morris, she was recommended.  She took her time explained the procedure, was very gentle, and accommodated my schedule I went in on a Sunday.  My eyebrows make me look years younger I love them.  I will definitely be back Annie.  I love the freedom of being able to run out the door without any make up and still feel pretty.  That gift is priceless.
Great place, caring and compassionate staff. They have always taken great care of our pets, I wouldn't go anywhere else,  & Dr.  Haskell is the best!

This chipotle is absolute garbage!!  The staff at this location is absolutely incompetent.  They under stuff your burritos, forget items in your order, ask unbelievably stupid questions, do not clean up the mess they make after each burrito and then proceed to drag your food through it.  

By the time you make it to the check out, they top it off by incorrectly charging you for your order, and because of the idiocy at large, they ask you to just accept their mistakes and move along because they can't figure out how to fix it.  

Horrible, this is all over several visits.
We have come here two days in a row now. Great food both times and a great atmosphere. Definitely give it a try.

Awesome awesome awesome!
Don't think twice. Long lasting. Covered every inch. So surprised and happy. 
I was skeptical about an airbrush tan from a random place. Not only being from South Florida where a tan is accessible but an airbrush is even easier.. Awesome chick. Awesome tan.

Not bad just not the same.
The service was good and the Pizza was not bad,
the restaurant itself had seen better days.
Part of enjoying a good meal also includes
the vibe or general feel of my surroundings.
Godfathers was a fun place to eat 10+ years ago
and while re visiting Reno we thought we would pay a visit.
Thank you Godfathers for the memories, but unless time and money is put in
 it may be time  to move on.

Easily the closest hotel to Independence Hall. 20 yards to the IH security checkpoint. 100 yards from the Liberty Bell. Easy to walk almost everywhere. Scores of great restaurants and bars close by.
Perfect service. Had a king room over looking the "park" - which really means your room looks right at Independence Hall and the Liberty Bell. Definitely pick that option! Xmas week prices under $200/night?? Easily worth double!
Best sushi. Highly recommend. The sushi rolls were very good especially the crunch roll and the service was fast..one of the waiter looks like Jared Leto too!

This place was great. It's hipster af and that can be annoying but I brought a couple friends and that made a big difference. The food and drink is sooo good. The cocktails are one of a kind and delicious. Spicy Louisiana spins on a few classic dishes. Brunch here is where it's at. So many places to eat in NEw Orleans that it's always a challenge to choose but you won't go wrong with a visit here.
If u need a little history on IPA etc. Frank is your guy! Great food & one of the largest variety of cold brews I've ever seen in a local spot.

Exquisite. We went here for the second time this fall since they started the chef's menu. We'd been to Vetri a few times in the past, when it was a fabulous, traditional Italian restaurant and it was great then. This is food, wine and service taken to a new level. On both occasions we had the wine pairing and it was spot on perfect with the courses. We started both times with a palate teaser from the chef which promised the joys of what was to come. Unlike most multi course chef's offerings (such as Alinea in Chicago) Vetri actually gives you a choice of dishes within a limited range of beautifully prepared courses. We opted to have the chef choose for us both times so that we could taste what he thought was interesting and so that we could share each other's plates. When I say that this rivals the best restaurants that I've ever been to, it is not an exaggeration. The blend of flavors in each course and plate was magnificent.
In addition, we had the same wait person both times and he paid meticulous attention to us and was friendly and understated. Such a pleasure. Finally, one could actually have a lovely conversation here. It had a pleasant low level vibe without intruding on conversation. For those of us who hate loud restaurants, it was heaven. Vetri is pricey, so it's not an everyday, casual kind of place. But you get what you pay for.

The ambiance was lovely. So nice to be able to have a conversation in a restaurant. Having said this ---- Terrible service. We were sitting for 25 minutes before the waiter came to get drink orders. I had to ask the hostess to light a fire under him. Not that the young man wasn't nice. He just was poorly trained and slow. Looking around it seemed as if all the servers were away from the tables and out of the dining room most of the time. Back in the kitchen perhaps? Certainly not attending to our needs. At this price point I expect more and have gotten better service almost anywhere else in Philly. 
The food was just OK. My husband and I had the prime rib. I've had it elsewhere in Philly for a lot less and it's been comparable flavor wise. My friend had salmon which, again, was OK. The sides were OK. Nothing special. When it came time for coffee it was not presented with cream or sugar and when the sugar came, there was no teaspoon with which to stir it into the coffee. Don't know what the rave reviews are all about because we won't be back.

Everything we had was great, filet, truffle fries, bbq shrimp and redfish.  Len was our server and was so personable or and friendly.  Even if the food had only been ok, I would go back for his service.  Brought our kids balloons and was just so attentive to our table and others.  Highly recommend!!

Awesome food! Get extra gravy for the chicken and waffles cuz it's awesome! Wife had the three tacos! Had to box one, she is a lil one so three huge awesome tacos did her in! Lol, place is a cool atmosphere waitress was fun friendly and fast! Thx for a great dining exsperience!

I placed an order through DoorDash and when it was brought to me, the fries I ordered weren't there. The driver told me to call Cheesecake Factory for a refund (which didn't make sense since I paid doordash and the driver wasn't about to go and pick them up for me which was the sole purpose of his job anyway) POINT IS, I called CF anyway and the manager Justin was so nice, he offered up one of his employees to bring me my fries. I didn't want to inconvenience them in anyway because that seems ludicrous for just some fries. But he mentioned he just wants his customer to be happy and I mean, duh, I got my fries. I'm totally happy. And happy with good management. 10/10
Boyfriend and I were in Tampa for New Year's Eve weekend and had a great experience. Fun conversation and delicious food. Would deff come again.
Nice bakery, with plenty of goodies to choose from. I bought the Paleo Pumpkin pie, which was deliciously amazing. The staff and service is great, place is clean and inviting.

The food was fresh and wonderful! The staff was friendly and accommodating. You can tell everything is made from scratch and the flavors shine though:) 

Great find and happy we stumbled upon this restaurant.
Not impressive at all, I ordered turkey hummus wraps, turned out that half of my wraps barely contained any turkey! Only green and hummus. What a surprise!

First time at this local restaurant. The meats were tasty but served cold. Collard greens were unusual but not in a good way. Garlic bread and cole slaw lack flavor. The fried green tomatoes were good. The waitress brought our food out, already cold but did not bring us plates or utensils. Had to ask for sauces too. She didn't bring straws with the drinks. She forgot my wine altogether. Food and service need work!

Best Chicago Dog and Italian Beef in town! Order the "Beat of Both Worlds!" They can get busy and everything is cooked fresh to order so call ahead!  Paulie knows the meaning of how to treat people too...We will return!

Absolutely ridiculous. There needs to be a staff change or an actual manager needs to be placed on duty at all times. This place is so unorganized. Ordered bagels on the phone at 9am. I asked if they had a certain bagel they said yes they had it. & to come in 30 min arrived at 9:37. Line so long. Went up to ask if I could just pick up my bagels that I already ordered. I didn't want it getting cold. They said no I have to wait in line. WHAT!!!!! So my bagels could be cold. The wait in line was another 20 min almost. So my bagels sat for almost an hour. So I decided I was going to reorder them then when I got to the front of the line. They wouldn't let me. So now I have hour long made food. Gross and Luke warm. On top of that I ordered a milk to go it's frozen I can't even drink it. Absolutely ridiculous. Reporting this company as well because the staff is absolutely rude. All college kids. Have no respect. Never coming back and I'll make sure none of my family or friends do either. Waste of time and money.


Update Foods cold & a long blonde hair in it

Worst , Worst , absolutely the worst , ordered around 6pm received order at 8:24pm then I'm thinking ok going to enjoy my pizza the pizza wasn't cooked I been calling the store and no ones answering so pissed never again will I order from this place !!!!

I stopped in here after reading multiple reviews about how great it was. My dad was in the mood for chicken and I remembered this place, so I headed over.

I was here on a Sunday afternoon and the place was packed. I'm talking line out the door, people inside waiting on their order packed. I took this as a good sign, so I hopped in line and got ready to order at the window. I got the 14 piece chicken combo which comes with fries and a salad. It was a little over $10 which was perfect because there's a $10 minimum on cards. After you order they give you a number and you sit and wait. On this day the wait was about 15 minutes, because of the crowd, but that wasn't a problem. When my number was called I got my food and I was on my way.

The chicken itself is tasty and really generous. There was an even mix of wings and legs and I enjoyed it. The fries weren't anything spectacular and the salad was just lettuce, so next time I might skip the combo and get the 14 piece for $8 deal. While Golden Wings isn't on the level of Popeyes, you can't beat the price and the food is enjoyable. I'll be back.

Wow, first time stopping in and definitely impressed. The restaurant itself is very nicely set up and decorated. We were seated right away at noon for the lunch buffet.

The buffet was amazing. I've only been to another Indian lunch buffet before and this one definitely surpassed it. The amount of vegetarian options was awesome- I went back for seconds! Make sure to come hungry because you will leave stuffed!

Not terrible, just not good.  Steak was pretty skinny cut, ordered medium, came super well-done (roadkill), and was over-seasoned, albeit acceptable.  Potato (baked) was standard fare and pretty hard to screw up.  Salad was not fresh, and mostly-all iceberg, with a sad little bit of tomato.  Glad I tried it (seen this place for years and curious about it).  Will not order from again.

Best cappuccino served at any of the drive thru merchants in town. Orders are always right. Service is friendly. Dark chocolate espresso bark bar is killer good and no linger available 
Strange layout to the lot from all driveways. Accessible from 39th and 38th. 
Walkup window and casual outdoor seating available

I'm running errands at Walmart and Home Depot and as my tummy gurgles, I look out onto the horizon I see the qdoba sign, like a beacon of hope. I was greeted happily by the staff and they prepared my big yet affordable burrito. I even thanked Manager Marcus as I left. I appreciate it y'all. Keep it up!

Ordered a burger and salmon. The bill came out to $27.00 not complaining about that, but the salmon was over cooked and a very chewy. Plus not the most pleasant of experience with customer service. I got a very unpleasant stare. I probably won't be back.

Came here for drinks and a little dinner before a show a few weeks back. The atmosphere is perfect for a cozy evening: booths tucked away, arm chairs, a fireplace-- all great! We were, however, really disappointed in the food. My husband got the fish and chips and I got the lamb sliders after reading good reviews about them on here. Fish and chips looked like larger versions of fish nuggets and the lamb, although cooked well, was really underwhelming. It was listed as having "a variety of toppings" but in reality, one had half a piece of bacon, the other some melted and congealed cheese, and the last had absolutely nothing. I had to dip them in ketchup to get any flavor other than meat. For that, I would've just gotten a cheeseburger. Would come back here for a drink but not for food.

TERRIBLE SERVICE
I had out of town guests and took them to Bareburger. We were a party of 4. When we entered, we were behind a party of 2. The party of 2 was immediately seated at a 4-person booth, while there were multiple tables for 2 available. Host told us they were just clearing another booth (and pointed to it) and said we would be seated there shortly. In the meantime a party of 5 came in after us. It took 10 minutes to clear the table and then another hostess came up to the original host to ask who was waiting for a table. He told her our party of 4 and a party of 5. She proceeded to seat the party of 5 at the booth, adding a chair to the end of the table. There were no other tables, let alone booths, available for 4. When we told her we were supposed to be seated first, she said there was no other place for the party of 5 and it was just logical to seat them there!?? In what world is that logical?  We walked out and will not go back. Went down the block to Barra Rossa, seated within 5 minutes, had excellent service!

Another annoyance at Bareburger, while we were waiting to not be seated, a hostess came and shouted at the several groups of people waiting to MOVE TO THE BACK OF THE RESTAURANT SO PEOPLE CAN GET THROUGH! Has management never heard of customer service training?

It is always nice to have a local restaurant real close to where you work! This place is in a little shopping mall which would give you a little pause on if this place is going to be the pizza restaurant experience you are looking for. However, do not be fooled, this place is a legit pizza place! Their calzones are by far the best for local faire and their "The Krewe" cheese sticks are the whole reason why I would walk through that door.

The food is good, the price is pretty cheap and it definitely beats out your local fast food pizza delivery spots. If you find yourself in Belle Chasse, come check out this funky little spot. This is the most convenient place to get your Rotolo's on!

Really nice coffee shop! Loved the place as soon as I walked in...

Their coffee was very nice, very balanced. They also have some pastries, though I didn't try those. 

The atmosphere is pretty chill, and the decor was nice and creative. 

There's also a cowork space adjoining the coffee shop.

They overcharged my friend and I by over 15 dollars. The bill only shows the total amount so when we asked the waitress to see each item she said she couldn't change it because there was no manager on. (It was a Saturday night). She proceeded to give us cash - but not enough. We both lost money. I will never go back because the good and drinks were not even that good. I can't stand businesses that just take your money and give no explanation. DO NOT GO HERE BECAUSE THEY OVERCHARGE YOU.
A nice change and a good taste of home. I think I was the only person to let the barista show their talents and got my usual double espresso. Well worth it.

This a review of the kids haircut. Both my little guys needed a haircut and this place was recommended by a friend of ours. 

If you're not familiar with this place, it is a sports oriented haircut establishment. A TV showing ESPN or a sporting event. Sports magazines on the rack for your reading pleasure. The process of getting a haircut is to check in on the tablet. Type in your number if you've already registered and wait. You can also request a certain stylist if you wanted.

We didn't have to wait long and there is about 16 chairs you can sit on. The stylist was very professional and made our kids feel comfortable. There were lollipops to help them pass the time too. Since it was our first time there, they upgraded the cut to the MVP.  Your kids will get a shampoo , dry, and a massage if needed. They also have hair color which my kids wanted. Blue for one and red for the other.

The haircut was good. My kids were happy and the staff was great. We will be back again.  

The Kids MVP cut is 23 dollars.

Another brunch gem for Midtown! We went here to try a local place before we headed home and we were not disappointed! We started out with the White Trash Hash- holy smokes. They're basically cheesy potatoes but way better. I had the Pretzel Pancakes for my meal and they were the perfect flavor. They were drizzled with dulce de leche and served with a side of white chocolate mousse and they were so good! I also had a side of Texas toast (hello carb day). Ask for the coconut jam with it... UNREAL. My boyfriend had the biscuits with chorizo gravy and he said they were really good. He also asked for a hot chocolate. Our server (I can't remember what her name was but we were in the room that looks out onto the patio on Sunday 12/17) went to the back to check if they had it and it turns out she made it by heating up milk and melting chocolate.. they didn't have packets so she went above and beyond. Incredible food, incredible service, and definitely one of our new regular spots when we visit!

One of the best pizzas i have ever had. Went here mid week mid day and sat at the pizza bar. The pizza is not cheap $32 for a large with pepperoni, but again it was great pizza. Thin lite crust with great flavor and char. Good draft beer list with a large list of bottles. Service was just ok this could have been because we sat at the pizza oven bar. Was cool to see the pizzas made and cooked in the open wood/ gas fired oven .

Walking into Burger Study was reminiscent of a Harvard Law Library. Dim lighting, rich woods, and a bit of a cozy feel. Not what I would typically expect from a burger spot, but hey- it works! Perhaps what sets this spot apart from other burger spots in the city. 

I think Burger Study also finally hit their stride. When they first opened there wasn't a ton of consistency among their dishes, but I recently returned and was pleasantly surprised. Burgers were cooked to perfection and topped with only the highest  quality ingredients. My fianc pointed out that this was the best bacon he had ever had on a burger! 

A great alternative to some of the other chains along GA Street and a must try for any out of towners.

Great customer service and repair! 
Recently our 2003 Winstar broke down due to a bad transmission. AAA towed us to a local shop near the breakdown that we weren't familiar with. We had it towed to InTown Auto Care for a second opinion.  A transmission isn't cheap, the Winstar ran fine otherwise, and Intown Auto Care was recommended by friends.  The new owners Suzanne & Mike took great care of us. The diagnosis was done quickly and a replacement transmission was ordered. 

Unfortunately the first transmission ordered didn't meet their standards. We received a call from Mike. He stated he didn't like the looks of the transmission and ordered another one. He apologized for the delay. We were happy he was looking out for us ! Just as happy to have an Enterprise rent a car arranged with their help.

The Winstar is running great, good for another 14 years!

My first time coming in today.  First impression was that it was very empty, so I was very surprised that the sushi chef asked me to seat myself.  Sushi was good for the most part but I hate when they put a lot of rice. So when I got salmon nigiri, I pick off a little bit of the rice. I had 3 tiny bits of rice on my plate and the server rudely stated "next time finish your rice, ok?"   I eat sushi at least once a week, this was the first time a server has commented on a little bit of rice left on the plate.  Inside one of the salmon was some black stringy substance so I did not eat that piece and he didn't like the fact I left one piece of nigiri on the plate as well. Price is on the high side. They didn't not refill my drink at all.  The sushi was pretty good though beside having too much rice on the nigiri.

Wonderful food in a quiet atmosphere (hard to find when visiting Mew Orleans). Had the stuffed crab, collard greens and Mac & Cheese.  Loved it! Greens were perfect!! Husband ordered red beans and rice with a side of sausage.  Yum!!

Ya know when you are so full, but you keep eating because the food is so delicious?!? Yup there is your warning! Visited on a Monday around 1pm. There was a line, but it moves quick. I ordered the Chicken Shack Ranch. So Good! 
Seating is limited, but it is worth visiting!

Pretty good preparation on the salads BUT the lady that runs it can be very moody at times almost to the point of being rude. Her husband is a sweet heart. One time the women was extremely rude and had the nerve to charge for an extra butter. So when you go inside you pick the size of your salad and then either you can get bread or a banana but this time I ordered the bread and I must say they're bread rolls are really good but the little tub of butter they give you is not even enough to butter the whole bread so when she charged me I was a little taken back surprised to say the least. Love their salads that's why I rated them them a 3. But their customer service I would definitely give them 2. Size of place is nice.

So, I just moved back to Florida from Northern Virginia.  Felt the need for something different for lunch today and popped in to Zio's and am I glad I did!  What to order, what to order . . . homemade Italian sausage (sweet, not hot the first time around) with peppers and onions.  First of all, half a sub is still HUGE and I could only eat half of it; secondly, it was absolutely delicious.  Sadly, this place is too close to my new house - my hips and thighs thank you.
Sometimes they'll deliver to my job, sometimes they won't. I'd rather just not deal with them anymore and give my business to someone else.

Prices are extremely fair, portions are generous, quality is high, and the food is delicious! Whether you order the delicious Baja burger or a portion of rotisserie chicken, your meal will be extremely flavorful, and filling. They are well worth a try!

It's very hard to get me upset about rude people especially those in the service industry; However, I can say that the service desk employees here are a lost cause.  They are rude every single time come here, never make eye contact, and symbolically and sometimes literally roll their eyes every time you ask for some assistance. It's a real bummer.

Being that poke is my favorite food group, I am ecstatic that this place exists within 5 minutes of my home. So delicious and fresh and quick! The drive through factor is just a bonus. Please everyone support them!!

This was my first time at Burger Study and I was very impressed with the food. I did a build-your-own burger and went with a classic bacon cheeseburger. It was cooked to a great temperature and the meat was delicious. It was a little sloppy to eat with a decent amount of grease and I had hoped that their special sauce tasted a little better but overall a fantastic tasting burger with plenty of other substitute options if angus meat isn't for you (turkey burger, garden burger, lamb patty, etc.). I would definitely come back to try another burger.

Being born and raised in NY, I consider myself a pizza elitist/snob.  I've gone to Barros three times and the pizza is good, but what brings me back are the wings (big and full of meat) Two dozen for little over 20 bucks. The mango habanero wings are fantastic! Nice to have a place to get wings close to home now!

Wonderful dining experience!  The NOLA bites were  great!  The fish and oyster platter were some of the best on the planet!  My husband loved the red beans and rice with a side of cole slaw.  We definitely will be back!
I love this place...Colin and Sarah (ph) are the best and always friendly!!

I've now been to PokeDoke three times, at various times of day. Initially they were working out some kinks (ran out of fish, 15 min wait for rice) but I have had an excellent meal there every time! I feel like even the small is plenty filling. You get two scoops of fish for the small, which isn't a ton but is enough. You can chose whatever toppings you want, which is awesome! The flavors are great, they are pretty efficient, and the people working there are very nice and friendly. Great addition to the CWE dining scene! Get out of that shake shack line and try Poke Doke instead!

First time trying this place out! The food is amazing and the serving size is large enough for 2 people if your order a large! I ordered the taso and diri kole! I'm very satisfied and would definitely go back if it wasn't an hour away from home!!
Burgers are decent, not fantastic but you can customize them which is cool. Their french fries alone are worth the visit at least. Super good. Had great service last night too!

I didn't care for the bar look in the place because I went Sunday morning and the food was so good!!
Why not come here instead of waiting outside in front of the other brunch place down the block.
I loved the waffle burger and it was very fulfilling.
They have tons of vegan or veggie options.
But one thing I didn't like were the tiny tables and the sticky floors.
We will come back for the food if in the area!

Only giving two stars because the decor was nice. We were there for Sunday brunch and it was literally the worst brunch I have ever had in my entire life. I will recommend to go to a diner for more quality food. I got the 8th st egg Benedict and it was came with two very small pieces of eggs on English muffin plus a weird green salad and bland meshed potato on the side. Boy, their cook couldn't even poach eggs. The Egg was hard and solid inside, not runny at all. The ham was dark and over cooked. Too much acidity in their bearaise. Overall worst egg Benedict I ve ever had. They can't even do it better than a causal diner. My husband ordered the chicken and waffle. The chicken was in pale color and has no flavor. KFC chicken is much better than that! The waffle has the same pale color as the chicken with minimum flavor and very soggy. I think it's easy to surpass that with just your home waffle maker. Overall, save your money and go to a diner instead!!

My daughter and I drove to Tampa just for the night. We walked to Besito. The food was amazing, but the service was even better. If you go, ask for Andy and give him an awesome tip. He gave exceptional service!! Tell him Ananda from Tennessee sent you. :)

Over cooked burnt chicken just what I always wanted! thank again for your great food! Arby's definitely isn't what it used to be. Used to be when you do Arby's you knew you were getting good food now it's the same as McDonald's except for you pay twice as much. Arby's you lost another patronage!

Ooh yum. This is the place to go when you have a group who can never agree on pizza toppings! The pizzas are brick oven fired to perfection, neither soggy or dry, and always what you're in the mood for because you pick all the ingredients. 

If you're like me, you have big ideas about ingredient combinations but hold back because adding toppings is criminally expensive at most pizza joints. 

Not so at MOD. Everything is one price, so you can afford to get all gourmet and creative. And if your creation, like mine, involves a dozen or more ingredients, you'll find they add the ingredients judiciously instead of overloading the pizza to the point of soggy crust. 

I also appreciate the online ordering.

DO NOT USE THIS COMPANY! First off they were hours behind. My daughters ipad had a small crack on her screen. It was still fully functional. No issues whatsoever. The technician, Naseeb, came out and was watching YouTube videos on how to perform an ipad repair. He then stacked 5 heavy books on top of it and stated to leave it. I did not get a chance to look at his work. He stated to leave the books on for 24 hours. The next day the screen was lifting and halfway hanging off. The company then sent another technician out and he stated the first technician took my frame with the screen. Which they are not supposed to do. No one could get ahold of him. Now my screen is only half lit. I was told when that happens there is no fixing it. I have reached out to this company. No response. They said they are going to have management call. No response. I have no issues getting my lawyer involved. Do not waste your time or money with this company. They will send you around in circles. My daughter us devastated that she lost all of her contents on her ipad. These technicians are NOT certified. If they are, they are definitely not tested to make sure they really know what they are doing. Save yourself the headache and find another company!!!

This was the worst brunch I've ever had. Ordered the Buttermilk Fried Chicken Sandwhich; chicken was pale white, soggy with oil, definitely not fried and drained well, and might have even been slightly undercooked. The side green salad was just leaves, no dressing, no veggies, bland and neglected. The sandwich had absolutely no flavor, no taste, undercooked chicken, and strong pickles. Overall just a terrible experience and it took 25min to get the check back. Never coming back; you're better off going to a local diner or fast food restaurant for higher quality/edible food.

We decided on Milk and Honey for brunch after a long morning of flights in Nashville. Our original plan was to visit Biscuit Love, but the line was long and Milk and Honey had only a short wait. 

The sausage and pepper omelette was a perfect size for a hungry guy and was cooked perfectly. Fresh peppers and delicious breakfast sausage.  My girlfriend had scrambled eggs, caramelized onions and arugula on a biscuit which looked amazing. She said it was quite good!  


Update: upon further review of their wood fired pizza oven we decided to return for dinner. Excellent choice. The braised short rib and gnocchi was phenomenal and the pie was a perfect Neapolitan style margherita. Would definitely come back again and I recommend you try it! 

Pro Tip: save room for their cookies

These guys killed it on all counts!
Super friendly!
Amazing selection!
Amazing food!
Great prices!
Just good people who know good food...
If I lived anywhere nearby I would eat here 
all the time!

YOU WILL NOT BE DISAPPOINTED

WOW!! This place is not your ordinary fast food restaurant. You can come in and sit down to dine in, order take out or enjoy yourself during happy hour at the bar. Well I decided to order takeout and sit at the bar during happy hour while I wait for my food. The happy hour beers are a good value, I got a nice cheap beer for $2.20 from a very friendly bartender/server. As for the burger I ordered the 'Fire Quacker' it's made of duck, added to pepper jack cheese, pickled jalapenos on a brioche bun. This 'burger' was juicy, tender and bursting with flavor. No it's not your traditional burger but if you are adventurous you should take a shot. I also ordered the onion rings, nothing to really speak of here. If they're 'homemade' they should rethink the recipe as the taste is bland and overly breaded.

Chef-made barbecue. Bold flavors and unique sides. They use premium meats, and cook everything precisely and brilliantly. These are not attributes of a typical barbecue place. 

You get what you pay for, and therefore their prices are higher than typical places. For about $15 you get a reasonable meal. I'm not a huge eater but never seem to have leftovers.

This is barbecue for foodies, not cheap eats like most bbq places. 

I definitely recommend it and prefer it, but my wife likes more traditional and generous bbq. 

Treat yourself and give it a shot!

Super friendly staff. They brew a variety of really good craft beer. The menu is a bit limited, but has something for everyone. The food was very tasty and used some high end ingredients for affordable prices.
Aesthetically beautiful, delicious and tasteful in many ways. The place exudes class and good taste - and things that taste good. i'm a fan.

I have been looking for a good French Napoleon for a long time after Wegmans discontinued to bake Napoleon.  When I saw my FB showing a photo of Napoleon from J'aime, I can't wait to give it a try. 

We went J'aime on Christmas Eve but they ran out of Napoleon so we ordered Chouquette which is very surprising good. The cream of Chouquette is very light without heavy sweet and last time I had such silky smooth cream with good/right puff is from beard papa(Japanese bakery).  

So, I decided to come back today in order to get in line for Napoleon. Like Chouquette, Napoleon also has a very velvet moisture cream and because J'aime doesn't glazed sugar or fondant on the top layer, it won't too sweet which I can even eat a whole without coffee or tea. We also ordered Quich and I like pie crust of Quich at J'aime is thinner than Le Pain Quotidien.

I went on the free lunch buffet day, the food was amazing but it was crazy packed inside. This was my first experience at this location, I'm not sure if it's like this daily. The line to the buffet was confusing because it bottle necked in the corner. The one good thing about the day was you could dine in or take out.
Fish eggs is crab bisque= fail. Duck fries are just fries with parsley. We ordered 3 sandwiches none were overly impressive. Service was very well attended but can't make up for the lackluster food.

Deserves zero stars.  Their staff can't handle basic requests, they never deliver on what they promise (download codes, freebies, merc, etc), and yet have attitude like no others.  Really CID, time to reassess why your "product" keeps getting worse - otherwise you're just the fraud you appear to be.

I've been meaning to come here for the longest time and I'm so glad I finally did! It's a hole in the wall and the menu is very minimal, so you know that they've perfected every item. I got the beef bap and the sauce is so good, they have a bottle of sauce if you'd like to add more. You can dine in or take out. The inside is a cute little spot and the man taking orders was very sweet. As you can see I killed the bowl.

I am embarrassed at how many times I have walked by this little boutique and haven't walked in to shop. Thank goodness, I discovered them at their outside booth during the Lafayette Holiday House tour. 

My cousin and are the family shoppers and after browsing the items at the outdoor booth, we headed up the street to check out the store. We weren't the only ones with this brilliant idea, the store was packed. After finding several gifts for different people on our Santa list, we opted to return later to make our purchases and avoid the crowd. 

Without giving away details, because a recipient may be reading this review. We found several unique and STL themed gifts for local sports fans and bar items for the boozers. We do not discriminate, we shop for the naughty and nice. 

The staff was friendly and very helpful with our selections. This little shop will now be one of my go to stores for unique gifts and I'll be shopping local. 

Will I return? - YES!

When: December 10, 2017
Why: Naughty or Nice List

What a fun place to come and walk around.  We were staying in downtown but took at 15 min Uber ride over to check it out.  The decorations for the holidays and great and fun.  This place goes on and on and on. Lots of tour buses and tour groups but it didn't feel to crowded.  This is a money making machine so you'll see bars every 100 ft, gift shops and they have things designed for you to spend.  We took 15 min boat ride which was kinda funny and it let us rest our legs - it was $10.50.  We walked over to the Grand Ole Opry and went by a christmas gift store - again designed to make you spend money, when we got to the Opry - it was $26 for a 45 min tour - we decided that was too much - we would have paid $5 for a peek!!.  This was a great spot to get in some steps, look at the beautiful gardens inside the hotel and check off the bucket list.  We did not stay on site so have no idea what the rooms are like.
This place is dead. We saw too many empty store fronts that we got back in the car and went back home.

Fun, funky, and fresh all around. The food was standard poke bowl fare. I was impressed by the vareity of toppings and their quality. Every bowl will pack a lot of flavor with the amount of sauce and toppings they use. Portions were to be expected for upscale fast casual places. 

It may be a little confusing for someone first walking in. There's no sign about where to order so go the end of the bar. And if you are not familiar with poke, the build your own style might be confusing. Feel free to ask them for guidance. The staff is friendly and helpful. The venue is clean and modern. Great local staple!

I would not recommend the bubble tea. The quantity of boba was really high for the little amount of milk tea and ice. It's perfect if you really like a lot of boba.

We came here for a family outing/belated birthday celebration. The owners are knowledgeable, patient, and fun. Our family of 5 had a really great time and look forward to coming back with more friends...did I mention BYOB? Great place!

Fantastic Tucson food truck!!...Pablo Diablo is one of the best sandwiches I've put in my mouth!..Patty melt on Texas toast grilled with America cheese, avocado, sauted jalapeos & onion!..Add the hatch green chile sauce and this sandwich will blow your mind!!..Don't wait!..Find out where they are and go get some awesome food!!

The whole shabang is legit (all 3 flavors) I get it medium spice b/c I like a little kick. I usually get a pound of shrimp and a pound of clams. As an appetizer I get 6 blue point oysters which are amazing!!

Overall great experience, vibe, location and atmosphere. 
Great service and food
Bread should be included - not extra
Poke was very good - but should be tuna. 
Cheese plate was great
Fried chicken - very good- but not the best I've ever had, moist and delicious though, jalapeno grits tasty, collard greens very good
Strogranoff was good- meet a little dry, could have been a little more flavorful
Overall deserts were a let down- mousse was ok, cookie tray average- only saving grace was the caramel/toffee, carrot cake sunday- meh. 
Lastly - everytime they brought a course they gave the plates and drinks to the wrong person- I'm sure this will improve with time
Wine list decent - but way over priced.
We will return- and I'm sure some of these things will improve.
I have been here a couple times now with some great friends and the service is always amazing and the food is even better. Its is totally worth the wait to get seated!

Didn't feel like cooking so i ordered the crabs from uber eats. I guess they were having a bad day yesterday because when I ate their crabs I got food poisoning. Threw up all night. My suggestion is if you want a near death experience get the crabs.
I had the shrimp and grits ($20) and it was delicious! Good portion size and no wait. Decent amount of seating on 2 floors. Service seemed to be fine. They had a good selection of cocktails too.

Eunasia, Deedra, and Maxwell was incredible. A great refreshing way to start my morning. They gave me good recommended drinks as well as a pretty good go to iced machiatto to try. Parking sucks though. But they make up for this in service. I enjoyed the way they made me feel.I enjoyed the conversation. There are also food I will get that later and tell yah how it went.

I love stopping by Street Tacos before and after shows at the Fox Theater. The meats are too yummy, all of them. I like that you get your choice of corn or flour tortillas. It does get busy but that's because it's so good.

The customer service manager contacted me and we discussed the charges during the plumbers visit. After explaining that I showed the plumber where the leak was I got reimbursed for the leak search charges.
I give it one more star since the work was done professionally but also that they care about they customer and listen to their complains. Thanks to social media like Yelp you can make your voice heard.

Came in town for a friends wedding had been here a very long time ago and i hadnt realized how good this place waa until i tried it again this morning! You are going to have a wait so be prepared to wait or get there super early. I got there about 930 on saturday morning and had to wait about 15-20 mins to get seated. After having a hard time deciding between the sweet potato pancakes and the cinnamon spice i decided to go with the sweet potatoe and lets just say hands down you have to try those! Even if you aren't a big sweet potatoe fan you will love these!! I cant wait to come back to Nashville just to try these. My girl had the blueberry pancake it was still great just no as good as mine! Def worth the hype and give it a try if you are in town

The Bridgestone Arena is where the Preds play, big name concerts are held and I'm sure the occasional Monster Truck rally. But the review is really about the fans rated number one by ESPN. While I am not sure of the formula the "mother ship" used, I'm pretty sure they got it right.
Everyone seems to be dressed in team colors, the anthem is often sung by some recording star, a veteran is recognized for their service all before the puck drops.
The fans taunt the opposing goalie with a verse that questions his ability. Loud music is played when the Preds need a lift. Live bands play between periods. It must all work as they often have the best home record in hockey.

I love the look and feel about this cute place!

Workers were very helpful to guide me to which coffee would fit me. 

I got the lemon blueberry donut which really tangy but good! Too bad they ran out of the cinnamon roll brle. I'll be back for you!

I also got the cold brew with condense milk. I forgot what he called it but he recommended that one since I wanted an over iced sweet coffee. And it was just that! Perfectly sweet coffee! 

Totally recommended and definitely coming back to try the food

This is the WORST D&B I have ever visited. The restaurant was filthy, with napkins, food and other trash all over the floor. The food was cold. The waitress ignored us while she cleaned liquor bottles for 10 minutes and we had to ask for assistance. When we asked for the manager, he was rude and dismissive. Don't waste your time!

My first time here.  Service was good, and the sushi was good quality.  But I'm giving it three stars because of the Wasabi.  It was terrible.  Not spicy.  No flavor.  Like pured potatoes with green food coloring in it.  Sorry but if your specialty is Sushi, you need to have at least decent/passable wasabi.  Everything else was good.
Incredible incredible food. Atmosphere is quiet and comfortable. Definitely recommend.

I've been coming to this restaurant for 25 years. The nostalgic layout is appealing. Waitresses are friendly and familiar. Unfortunately due to its size gets too busy on Saturday and Sunday mornings. You have to pick a good time or prepare to stand. Raised prices a few years ago. Taking it from a really good bargain to a moderate one. 

My first bad experience was today otherwise I would rate it higher. 8:30 AM on a Monday in December and the restaurant was almost empty because I was by myself I was not allowed to sit at one of the eight open tables. I was not interested in sitting at the counter and there were plenty of seats and no one at the door. That's just bad business. I left embarrassed because I happen to be alone this time.

Amazing! Great food! Great ambiance! Great service! I got the bacon cheeseburger on a gluten free bun. The best burger I have ever had. I love finding great places that offer gluten free options. I'm definitely going to come back here! Prices are not to high. My burger was $10.39. The price is great for how big the burger was!

I love love love the Teriyaki Burrito tonight it was all burrito and no teriyaki. This is something special so when it is ordered someone ought to take great care to make it what ii is supposed to be. Maybe next time.

Stopped by the Sun diner for a lunch as suggested by a person from the area. Walking in you will know that this place has been here awhile.  Very well worn and lived in feel. Taking a chance I, for the first time ever, ordered the chicken and waffles with sausage gravy. I was surprised by the fact that the meal was not heavy and tasted very good. The waiter was very helpful with suggestions and friendly. 
Stop by Goo Goos across the street after lunch

I loved my server, she was very good. This place has a nice atmosphere, love the decorations and the bathroom is adorable. The meal was my least favorite part. My turkey sandwhich came with fresh avocade which was good but with light sourdough. What exactly is light sourdough bread? It takes like white bread. The side salad was iceburg lettuce, which has no nutrition but I did enjoy the dressing. Last a terrible cookie that tastes as though it was made with splenda. I would probably come back here for the pastries or breakfast, but not for lunch.

Ordered the mahi tacos and it was great! All the food here was delicious! I would definitely go back. The outside seating was decorated nicely, very comfortable classy setting. The service was spectacular as well!

The gym is better since they renovated it. However, the gym is always too warm for working out. Many of the members have complained 
about the temperature but nothing has improved. They say it is set at 72 degrees but at times it feels much warmer. 72 degrees is too warm for a gym. Also, they have no fans in the equipment area to help with the circulation. I think they are trying to save money on their electric bills.
Amazing BBQ. Humble people. Calm atmosphere. Get the sweet and spicy sauce. To die for! We will be back soon

After a fun night out, my friends and I were in need of some serious brunch the next morning. I stop in to Ants Pants every so often for coffee but have gotten brunch here twice. I thought it would be the perfect place for us to get our fix!

We arrived around 11 am on a Friday morning, trying to beat the afternoon rush and were seated right away. Our server was great, explained the menu and what they're most known for, and immediately brought us over coffee, water, and OJ (the fresh squeezed juices here are amazing!). We were all craving something savory, although I've had the pancakes here in the past and as a brunch enthusiast, I can assure you they are some of the best in the city. 

I ended up ordering the Eggs Benedict. The hollandaise sauce was rich and tasty but not too overwhelming and the eggs were poached to perfection! My friends thoroughly enjoyed their maple bacon and croissant sandwiches as well. Ants Pants has easily become one of my go-to brunch places: reasonably priced, wonderful service, amazing food and coffee...what else do you need?!

Visiting area and looking for a causal dinner place. This fit the bill. Ate at bar on a busy Saturday evening. Wife had Mango-Thai tini that was really nice! I had a great old fashion. Then we had fish tacos and thai beef noodle salad. Great service and really enjoyed the lively atmosphere at the bar. Would definitely recommend this place
Had an awesome dinner. Tried the Greek salad, meatballs, and appetizer plate. All were great. Nice ambiance, great food, and reasonable prices. BYOB.

It was a nice experience, we took our two young boys, and since they could get up and walk around it was nice. On the down side, after we were done eating they gave our table away to the next dinner time, and we had nowhere to go! It was FREEZING out and we were more or less expected to sit outside for the next two hours!! Once we walked around and saw everything, we had an hour left to sit and freeze!

Let me start by saying that I'm not really a massage person. I've gotten maybe 10 solo massages in my lifetime. This is probably my best one. My husband and I did a couples massage for the first time on our trip to New Orleans .  I was able to book  over the phone and wasn't asked to give credit card information over the phone which I liked 

Arrival

Both therapists were there when we arrived both were friendly and nice. We were offered a glass of red or white wine  and asked what genre of music we preferred.  They were already playing reggae which we found suitable. 

The Massage

We were shown to a candle lit room and asked to undress and get under the sheets. The massage bed was really comfy and warm. Both therapist begin our massages with warm oil. They massaged from top to bottom. Very relaxing and the right amount of pressure. All the way from my finger tips to my toes. My husband fell asleep and was snoring (loud) but it did not disturb the tranquility of my massage. The price was right and the service was spectacular. Will see them again when I return in March.

4 is being pretty generous. 

We ordered delivery and it came a little bit earlier than stated so that was a plus. 

Poboy with cheese curds-my husband likes it but it looks really heavy and a normal person can eat half and be full. It came with a salad that has seen better days that had no dressing on it whatsoever. The chips included were homemade and were crispy and lightly salted. That was pretty good. 

Gumbo with andouille sausage-it was on the slightly salty side but wasn't too bad with the bread that was included. It was pretty spicy for me but perfect for my husband. I think this was the best dish we ordered


Mashed potatoes with debris-eh.

I ordered the steak bowl with some flour tortillas, the meal was okay. The tortillas was small, the bowl will be enough for you to get full for lunch. This spot would be ideal if you want to grab something on the go for lunch but you don't really care how good it taste. The steak itself is thinly cut and little or no seasoning on it. If you dine in they have complimentary tortilla chips but when I was there it wasn't refilled. It can get packed during lunch hours so if you're planning to dine in with more than four people, I suggest you come a bit early to grab some tables. Would I come back? Most likely not, I rather go elsewhere.

Wow. So I emailed a request for 18 powdered jelly filled donuts. I spoke with Ellen  and confirmed 6 raspberry, 6 strawberry, and 6 lemon to be picked up Saturday at 10:30. I drive in and lo and behold, NO DONUTS!!! Yes, apologies, but this is embarrassing! Thanks for nothing. This is no way to run a business. This is inexcusable. If I could give less than 1 star I would.

Ho. Ly. Crap. This is place is unlike any place I've ever been in my life. It's huge. It's got everything you need. W didn't even spend the night. We just walked around the place for hours. So much stuff to see and do. And it's a great location in relation to other attractions in Nashville, if you ever get bored here, which is unlikely. We will definitely be back to spend a few nights.
The food is very good but the prices seem too high unless you get their lunch special.  Service can be a little slow too but the food is great so just order take out.
Your standard variety Target. Plenty of parking, and the store wasn't crowded. Closer than the one in Metairie if you live downtown. One of the nicest grocery sections I've ever seen in a Target.

I don't do five star rating often, but this place is great if you are a cigar smoker. I treated a few friends to a cigar and then enjoyed the lounge for an hour while we smoked. It was a perfect experience. 

The staff knows everything about cigars and helped my friends make some great selections. 

We stayed past closing... they did not care. What a great shop.
