And since their location is the intersection of Himes and Gandy, trying to enter their driveway during afternoon peak traffic hours can be challenging, to say the least. Overall, they have room for growth and improvement, but this is an excellent start, especially for south Tampa!
Old school NOLA restaurant. Had drinks and gumbo and tomato soup combo appetizer. Delicious. Good Pimms Cup, but a better one across the street at Hotel Monteleon.
Stopped here and got an order of the chicken and sausage jambalaya. It was perfectly balanced and seasoned! Very impressed with the quality from a small shop inside the French quarter.

Oh my goodness. The remodel is GORGEOUS. This place is so soothing, so clean and lovely!  I went for the first time in years recently, and was blown away by the new tank rooms-- high ceilings, music if that floats your boat, lights if you want them.  

I prefer the darkest of dark silent tanks and the room offered that too.  Amazing.

The various Tria locations are all great, and this one - perhaps the original Tria? - is perhaps my favorite, being a bit more roomy compared to the Tria West. Seating upstairs provides a somewhat quieter area. I recommend getting in a bit early, as the place does fill up. Incredible wines and beers, as well as the food (tapas size) selections. On a recent visit, our server, Jill, confidently recommended the Avec les bons Vux de la brasserie Dupont - she was right! I'll try to get back while they still have it. For snacks, we enjoyed the white bean spread and a cheese selection. The very attentive staff brought more bread as we worked through what was first served. On a more recent visit, the mushroom with Fontina toast was excellent, very simple, yet really satisfying. And may I say that NOT having a TV was an excellent decision by the owners.
This is my favorite breakfast spot in Tucson! Expect to probably wait for a table, but worth every minute! My favorite is the Beni or the Steak & Egg Sandwich. Everything is amazing!
The menu is great but unfortunately they are inconsistent with food prep. I've had great food, then cold food, then undercooked food all for the exact same dish.

This place is great. Service brought us extra cherries for baby without asking. The fried seafood and drinks are the best. I love norleans! It's like Vegas with great food everywhere here hoooraaaaye.

Checked out this new sushi spot after hearing good things and I'm glad I did! The fish was clearly very fresh and the portion sizes were generous. The seasoning was excellent on the dishes. The J&J Specialty Roll was really good and I highly recommend it.  All in all, a great experience with delectable food and lovely ambiance. Will definitely be coming back!

To be honest I really struggle with this brewery. I love multiple levels of their establishment, but the beer is not one of them. And let's face it, it's a brewery. Isn't that kind of important? 

Let's start with the heart eyes emoji provoking assets. Their food is great. Their fried chicken sandwich melts in your mouth (I didn't order this but I always get a taste of my buddies palate ). Their bao buns were not the best I've ever had, but still tasty. I actually prefer mine more on the airy, fluffy side, but they choose to sear theirs so it's a little crispy on the outside. I'd also prefer. More crisp than fatty piece of belly inside but hey look who's being contradictory now (make up ya mind, Tone). Anyways, I was surprised at how much I loved the fried rice in my salmon taco. I actually enjoyed a few forkfuls on its own throughout the course. But even still, almost all of the portions are a little small for the price. Quality is important though here, and I feel they nail it. 

The atmosphere is definitely another pro. If you don't like noise, go away. People are having fun and drinking merrily. It's gonna be loud. So talk a little louder, look at your guests when they speak, and laugh at the kids next to you trying to steal their dad's wings. I'm Italian. I'm loud. I love noise. It makes me feel at home. So the tremendously open layout of this building is much preferred over their cafe location. 

So the con here. Guys. Whyyy are your saisons sour? No where else do I experience this, and saisons are my favorites. And guess what.. I hate sours. Don't get me wrong, I've had a few of their beers that I have really enjoyed, but overall I think this place is over hyped. My thought is they just try to get too eccentric, and just get a little nutty with their concoctions. Like I said, I don't hate it, but I rarely love it. I'll still keep going though. The atmosphere, food, and occasional slam dunk brew still reels me in.

Look no further! This is where you want to get your alterations done! I have been here twice and both experiences have been so quick and easy. Not to mention, the people that work here are extremely friendly and understand exactly what you're looking to get done. I just brought an item in today and didn't realize they were going to be closed until after New Years and I had an outfit I needed for NYE. Without hesitation, she told me she would have it done the same day and she wouldn't charge me any extra for rush alterations. Boom- outfit done in LESS THAN THREE HOURS! I can't say enough good things. Just go see them if you need alterations done in the Nashville area!

Ordinary sports bar with typical American bar eats. It does have a decent happy hour, which lasts til 7pm (at least add of the date of my visit) so it is reasonably priced. Brick offers one of many very similarly themed pubs in this area of Tampa. There was nothing extraordinary about this place compared to many others in this area.

Stopped by to try their "Food Network approved" creole seafood gumbo. Don't do it - it's extremely fishy and flavorless. Also tried the Cajun Dirty Rice which had almost no flavor despite being a nice shade of dark brown. Walk past here and go to one of the many other shops in the French Market.
This place is just plain good. You can taste the fresh! I will be back and I'm just in town for a couple days! If you enjoy food that actually came from the earth than you will definitely enjoy.

This restaurant is located inside of a beautiful Hyatt property. Once I stepped inside of this restaurant I wasn't impressed...I couldn't find a clean table. I get it the restaurant was busy. I moved outside to the area with live music only to find out food wasn't being served. I moved back inside to a seat at the bar. Sergio was our bartender he is a true gem to the hotel. The bar was busy but took the time to answer questions and not rush us. He recommend the catch of the day and the jalapeno burger. The food took a while well 45 minutes which was extremely long. Once the food arrived the burger was amazing but the fish was not good and that's giving it credit. The rice was cold and was sent back. The fish had no taste. The portion was VERY small. The manager Teresa came over and was extremely helpful she's a true asset to the Hyatt. She listen to our issues and handled it really professionally. We left the property to get the car from valet and encountered another issue that is when I met another manager Ajyey (so?) she walked me to the valet and took care of the issues. Even thought there were some issues with the food I will say the staff at this restaurant was AMAZING!

This ACME is not much different from many of the other establishments in Philly. The one advantage is that the overall store is larger, but the amount of fresh fruits and vegetables (with emphasis on fresh) is a little bit of the disappointment side. The staff are a little bit more friendly than the center-philly location and the large parking lot makes it a bit more tolerable for lugging large quantities of heavy groceries. Overall, it's not bad and it does have some cheap sales from time to time.

Probably the worst casino in the nation. No free drinks when you sit at the tables, I was playing at a table for almost 2 hours, I was down a lot and asked for comps to use for a drink. They took my card and came back after 20 minutes just to tell me I couldn't get anything and to try again in an hour. Long lines at the cashier on weekends, and bad service. I wish there was another casino on this area.

Extremely helpful with ideas regarding design and DIY installation.  Figured accurate quantity of tiles , grout, adhesive and Ditra.  Took additional time explaining use of Ditra in application.

We were looking for a specific tile which they did not carry or could not order.  The looked high and low, eventually locating a distributor out of state.  Presented ideas regarding a total gut of my kitchen and needed backsplash.  Would most definitely recommend them.

Two stars because the food is good. They lost three stars because the delivery guy is a greedy, entitled bastard who begged for a tip and refused to leave our doorstep, claiming he works off of tips. Yeah okay buddy. I refuse to believe that the restaurant isn't paying this dude for delivering food. When restaurants have delivery fees that usually goes toward the driver. Well that's not true for this restaurant. When I called there to complain the woman who answered the phone told me that the delivery fee goes to the restaurant. Sheisty af. I may order pick up from them again but for someone to complain about not getting tipped for driving less than a mile down the street (literally) makes me question the integrity of Pikpon Thai.
Always a treat, drinks, service and food tops. Trip is the best leader since they opened. He's hands on and very professional make it feel like a private high end club.

First of all, I enjoy Zaxby's, but not at this location. Up until now, every Zaxby's has been clean and the food was good. And maybe a Wednesday night after 7pm was not their best crew. Lets start with the counter. Two groups walked in at the same time and there was nobody at the counter. After a period of time the manager (from the cooking area) had to yell out to an employee that there were people up front that needed their orders taken. I then heard the manager say "I'm not yelling at you" to the person. After placing the order, the counter person handed my wife a number to be placed at the table for food delivery. The card with the number on it was covered in some sort of sauce or ketchup. (At least clean it first) We then went to the serve yourself soda and ketchup machine. The ketchup was empty and the soda machine nozzle must have been dirty as it sprayed inside and outside of the cup. Was there a napkin nearby to clean up? No, those containers were empty too. Lastly, my wife's grilled chicken sandwich was not completely cooked. The one good thing that happened was they replaced her sandwich with another (without an apology). So in conclusion, this is not an indictment of all Zaxby's, just this location and it's staff.

Walked in to get food to go. Hostess said to sit at the bar and we said we'd like a drink while we waited. My husband used the bathroom and no one ever came to me while I sat there. I used the bathroom afterward and walked out expecting to have a glass of wine at the table but my husband said they never even acknowledge him or asked what we wanted. So since we'd given them 15 min and the waitstaff was talking to each other instead of customers (it was dead BTW, Tuesday at 7 pm) we got up and left. Wouldn't waste your time.

This Starbucks took 25 minutes and 4 tries to give me and my wife a grande iced caramel macchiato and venti skim chai. The drive thru line is a closed line so we were held hostage and could not drive away. They kept handing us drinks that were the wrong size, which is annoying but forgiveable, or the complete wrong drink (like, why did you hand me a tall latte and try to tell me it was a grande caramel macchiato?!). 

Stay away!

The worst. Server was new and didn't know the menu and the manager didn't help the guy. The bar didn't have the ingredients to make several drinks. The sushi was just terrible. Food took forever to be served. The bathroom was nasty and my daughter almost fell in the only working toilet because the seat was completely broken. Will never go back.
Great food. Practically licked the bowls clean. Great service and inexpensive prices. I would recommend this to anyone. You will like it I promise just give it a shot.
Best authentic Mexican food in the area! Quesadillas are a must try and the queso is perfection. If you're in the area, go here!

A hidden gem for sure. The food is absolutely amazing! My husband is quite a foodie and was so impressed we ate there 2 nights in a row. The sopes are delicious as are the tortas,tostados and tacos! Can't wait to try everything else!

We were spending the night in Reno and wanted to try Chick-fil-A. I don't know if it was just this drive in but our chicken sandwiches were not very good. 

However the milkshakes were good.

Don't know if we will try it again.

Very friendly staff! I like that I get to stay in my car the whole time and be walked through the process of what they are doing to my car and when. Was in and out in 15 minutes. A bit on the expensive side, but they offered an online coupon I didn't even know about. I thought that was excellent customer service!

Had a good time with friends catching up before the holidays. Tthe food was decent. The drink that I had which was the Santa Rita was a bit salty due to the wine. I ordered it with the naked rim, meaning no salt or sugar on the rim of the glass. 
The server we had was nice and very expedient she had  10 different orders to keep up with and was very successful at it. I noticed that The restaurant will automatically add a a gratuity okn each bill for party's of 6 or more. 
Over all not a bad experience. If ever in that area I would visit again.

Recently my wife and I have been looking for a new mid size pickup truck.  On a recommendation from a friend we went into Santa Barbara Toyota and took a Tacoma out for a test drive.  The first day we dealt with Armando and Frank.  Both were great guys!  They were personable and very easy going.  We went over our options, talked some pricing and my wife and walked out with a good feeling about working with them.  Our initial plan was to go visit a few other dealers and see what else was out there, however, after sleeping on it for a night we were both in agreement that that was the best experience we have had at a dealer to date.  At home that night I shopped pricing and found that I was getting about the best deal available in the state.  I went in the next day and purchased the truck.  I worked with Derek to iron out all the details and Hector in finance to get my loan squared away.  Both were very personable, professional, and it was honestly the easiest car buying experience I have ever had.  I will be a customer here for the long haul as I really feel that buying a car can't get any better than going to Santa Barbara Toyota.  Thanks to everyone I really appreciate all the help and advice plus I'm loving my new truck!

I am so pleased with the results from Dr. Berg. And the whole staff is very friendly and they remember you when you come in which gives my visit a warm and personal experience. I came in a week after I had delivered my
Second daughter via c-section, and I had so much tension in my head and neck it was cause serious migraines. My first visit they figured out my problem and they began to correct my alignment, and I noticed immediate relief in my neck. After my second visit my headaches were gone and I finally felt normal. I'm so glad I decided to come here!
Had the coffee ice cream here and it was fabulous! It has little chunks of coffee beans in it as well. The staff was very kind and attentive. Definitely look forward to visiting again.

Isn't there a professional manicurist in the  City of Philadelphia??????
I had a very disappointing mani pedi on Spruce Street and went to Rescue Spa to have it corrected.  I wound up with the same poorly filed nails, so that they catch on everything and polish is peeling the next day.
Still the same dry heels and calous, because sanding them is just a formality, not to correct something.
I have had some excellent services at Rescue but the mani pedi department is sorely lacking. 
  Here's a thought, how about getting the polish on the WHOLE nail.  Not here.  "Partial coverage."  Alternate facts.
If I can't get my nails done, better than I can do them, why go?
Best Thai food I've had in Philadelphia, definitely recommend anyone who loves spicy food to check this place out!
This McDonald's is always slow and very poorly run. Please hire better management for this location.

Hey guys, thanks for slamming down the corrected plate of my friend's food on our table. We couldn't tell you were pissed at us for actually speaking up about the crappy service  Umm, some of the food was ok, but all in all it was inconsistent. Things came out at different times. Some food was hot, other food wasn't. One person's entree was spicy when we speciFically asked for it not to be spicy. They forgot my fries. Guacamole was not fresh. Margaritas were just... not good, not fresh. Like the bottom of the barrel. Manager didn't seem to care and acted sarcastic. That is the ethos of this restaurant. Save your time--save your money. Go somewhere else if you can

By far, this is the slowest DD in the area. Even if you're the only one in the drive thru, it'll take about 10 mins for 1 coffee. I waited 25 minutes last Friday with only 2 cars in line. The inside is not busy enough to warrant the long wait in the drive thru. I don't know who owns this location but it needs some serious work with speed & training. They also often get coffee orders wrong or don't add the flavor. I'm constantly checking before I pull away to make sure it's correct. There are a few gals who work the window that are very friendly, so I will give them that.

OMG. If you love #matcha or green tea, then DEFINITELY get the matcha galore!! It was so delicious!! I don't usually like matcha anything because they taste so strong but this was perfect and mild. I think it's so cute they add the little koala cookie as their logo, brings back childhood memories! I loved the atmosphere and various options for you to choose! Come here when you are done with your day bc the line goes out the door!

The server was eating at the same time she was waiting on our table. The salsa was just tomato paste very bland. Not worth the money 4th has better places than here. Food was cold and will never eat here again.

My family and I had probably the weirdest/worst dining experience here. It seemed as if they weren't prepared to handle customers and the waitresses seemed stressed to the max. I guess the best way to describe it would be unprofessional. The food is also overpriced for the small portions that are served. Everyone in our group left hungry. One person got their pizza just as everyone else finished eating their meals. Although the food itself was good, I wouldn't recommend this restaurant or return. There are many other places to choose from on Main Street.

I've been a loyal customer since 2009, there was a period where I didn't come as much when I moved to South Philly but I returned to dining here when I moved back to Fishtown in 2016. I've always had a decent experience, good margaritas and good food, the wait was never good but tolerable. 

Well tonight, 12/29/17, we asked for a table of 6, we were told 40 minutes wait time which was fine, we get it people probably had cabin fever and they were busy. We scurried to the bar area, congregated at the corner ordered drinks, even got a pitcher of margaritas. The bar servers were great. 70 minutes lates, we were finally seated. 

We got our appetizers, they were great then we ordered our entrees. Three of us got fajitas, 2 out of 3 were cold. One of three that was hot. But the hot fajitas had such a tiny steak on it. 2 of us did not want to complain, we weren't there to get free food but eventually one of our friend did say something. Our server, Ashley, was great and she got the manager. He solved the situation by getting me a fajitas that was hotter, the way it's supposed to be. He brought out another steak for my friend. The food runner with the pink hair dropped off my hot fajitas but the literally dropped the plate of tortillas, sour cream and guacamole as if she was bothered by our complaint in front of my friend. The Diva in me wanted to snatch her hair and scold her for her behavior but in the real world I had to keep it cool. I was so angry that I lost my appetite. I don't expect to be worshipped, that's not what I wanted but a good customer service would have been great. As a frequent diner, that's all you want. Good food and hot meal with decent service. 

Look, I'm not here to get free crap, I literally eat out almost every single meal. I know what's it's like to deal with customer complaints, I respect everyone and do my best to fix the situation since I've had a job dealing with food and people at age 16. The food runner with the pink hair could have remedied the situation by acknowledging the situation and not taking things personally or even the manager could have tried to understand but none of that was done. I felt bad for Ashley, the server but she literally did her best and try to make things better. 

It just sucks because I don't think I could ever get my friends to come back here again and I think I am done as well.

They can take the reservation...they just can't keep the reservation.  We had reservations Dec 29 for 7pm and were seated at 7:35pm.  When I followed up with the hostess at 7:20 she said "well we can't go around encouraging people to leave".  I didn't appreciate the flippant response  but she was young so I'm guessing she hasn't had much experience and/or training on customer relations.  And I certainly don't expect a restaurant to do something like that, but what I DO expect is a restaurant to know how many reservations they can take at one time and to save tables...just some basic restaurant management.  To make matters worse, my entre (ribs) were black/burnt and tough.  I had them once before and they were very good.  Perhaps they had an off night with less seasoned employees running the show?
Love coming here with friends with the weekend. The atmosphere, food and wine are all excellent and perfect. Great place to hang out.

You ask the community to support you.. And we do.. I come here ALL.. I spend more time waiting in line than I do actually shopping it's very frustrating to see ALL the closed lanes.. Hire some more people from the community and fix this problem. You're not only more expensive than Wal-Mart, but you're becoming more inconvenient as well
Nice staff and clean little restaurant. Authentic and tasty. One of very few places that offers pozole.
Great beer selection, food is really good although the menu is skewed a bit nontraditional. Very lively environment, expect to wait a little even with reservations.

So disappointed today. First it took a while for the bartender to take our drink order, which was understandable because she was busy taking another order, but why the assistant manager didn't even acknowledge us while standing directly in front of us blows my mind. The attitude the bartender had, however was not understandable. I mean every chance that she had to make a snarky remark, she took and not only to me, but to my husband and every other customer in there. I have never met a bartender or server who had more excuses for their poor service.  
  When our food did arrive, I teasingly asked if they had "gone out back to catch the chicken for our wings" her reply was " Well they have to be cooked. You don't want to eat raw chicken do you?" No I thought, but I also know that chicken wings and chicken tenders (which we ordered) don't take 35-40 minutes to cook. What was really funny (well not) is that my chicken wings were overcooked and I mean, dry and dark. I did let her know and she took them off the bill, but honestly the attitude that she had throughout the meal was a complete turnoff.
  I don't know if we'll return to this specific location again, but I know I can't let this bad experience ruin Bullys for us. We'll try again, but with doubts.

It took me passing this place at least 30 times to finally forget about my paleo nutritional habits and try this place out. I was disappointed by the variety of frozen yogurt flavors, and I was grossed out by the stale ingredients on the bar. Who wants to break a filling trying to eat old marshmallows? Not me. I'll save my froyo cravings for somewhere else.

Robbed the bank! Excellent, well thought out puzzles. With every clue you got a great rush of excitement, and the whole thing seemed to build and build. Solved it with about a minute left on the clock! Would love to try another one. Super pleasant folks behind the desk made us feel right at home--it was our first time going to one of these puzzle rooms.

This is a very solid Chinese food take out spot.  Do not go in expecting anything amazing/life changing; however, their General Tso and lo mein are very good, especially if you are swinging in to pick something up after work.  There is an added bonus of a very strong beer selection so you can pick up a six pack on your way out.

Wow. What outstanding service by Kim. The place is spotless and I appreciate that they use the sanitary liners in their tubs. It is thrown away between each client. That is very important to not get a fungus from someone else. I feel like they take their time and do not rush like other salons in the area. I can highly recommend.  Great leg massage too!

Next to the new Publix on 41. I have finally found a place that I can have my nails and eyebrows done in the area. I have been looking for almost 2 years. I am thoroughly satisfied!
This is by far my favorite breakfast spot in all Tucson.  The food is fresh, local, and delicious!  I've never been disappointed by a dish.
I can't think of a better place to drink at in Philly when the sun's at its peak than Dirty Frank's. Aretha and the flying hot dog will always live in my mind's eye.

I've used ANCO for 28 years. Not often, thank goodness.

But they've always been reliable, trustworthy and knowledgeable.

I called yesterday, December 1, kinda late in the afternoon. It wasn't an emergency, so I didn't need overnight or weekend service. But they said I could get service Saturday, which is today. Wowee!

The battery in my garage-door opener was depleted and making insipid yet piercing BEEPS. This is continual. It happened before -- in 2012.

This is IN THE GARAGE. I can hear the beeps in the house. You can only go so far with this situation without pulling a Jack Nicholson.

IMO, you need the battery. It's there so you can use your garage door when the electricity's out. I went through this conversation in 2012 with Greg.

Today, Greg came again.

I got a call ~8 a.m. giving me an 11 a.m.-1 p.m. window. Very tight. Very good and very much appreciated.

And Greg called after his previous appointment to say he was on his way.

Greg arrived ~11:15 a.m., and we had the same conversation about the need for the battery. I opted to get a new battery . . . my luck being the electricity would go out tonight right when I want to go to the grocery.

He totally understood and proceeded to replace the battery.

THEN I mentioned how the two light bulbs quit working after a few ups and downs of the garage door. I'm thinking it's vibration that loosens them, and then they don't come on. And Greg confirmed that is the problem.

Greg had tips on this conundrum. He asked me how tightly I tighten them. I said loosely. He said tighten them as tightly as you can. Wear a glove, in case the bulb breaks. THAT'S how tightly to screw in the bulbs.

He took out my bulbs, filed them (to get back down to the core), used a screwdriver in the socket -- yes, electricity was turned off -- to reduce debris and then blew into the sockets to get rid of the detritus.

BINGO!!!!! Both lights worked.

Greg knows of what he speaks.

I got a new battery. I got big tips from Greg re the lightbulbs. $199. Check this one off the list, and I don't have to pull a Jack Nicholson.

Please go here. Everything was incredible. The bartenders were amazing. Lee waited on us and made our Anniversary Celebration. He was so attentive, entertaining, and knowledgeable. The food was spectacular. We will be back. I wish I could give them 6 stars and Lee 7

Good eatery.  Very crowded but the food was filling and delicious.  We went to Sabrinas with family on a Sunday for brunch and it did not disappoint.
Fast, friendly service.  Decent prices.
I love this store and will go out of my way to shop here.  The cakes from their bakery are the best!

Thanks so much for the help in finding a last minute rental! Love that it wasn't just the dress but I got the pearls and headband to go with it and for a reasonable price. Beats having to buy everything separately.  The ladies were so friendly and helpful too. Can't wait to come back for the next theme party :)
GREAT BRUNCH!!  Service on point. We are always in search of a great place for Sun brunch. Did a search and this place came up. Looking forward to having a D-n-D there soon.

Went into the store in Thursday morning. Immediately greeted by Gerry, the man that was working there that day. Very pleasant experience. Explained I had a budget of 1k and he worked to get my exact mattress that I wanted (was $1,800) for the outlet price of $800. The mattress was delivered the next day. Old mattress/boxspring out -- new ones in. All in less than 10 minutes. The delivery men wore shoe protectors in the house which is perfect. Received a courtesy call the day before delivery for time window and again that day of delivery and about 20 minutes before delivery. Overall great experience.
Next time I'll skip the Monte cristo and the madam....they were delicious, but the others were to die for. I should have bought more doughnuts. Next time, I'll buy so e to bring home.
Pizza...too small too much had better way better especially for the $$. Like wood fired pizza but not into cremated crust.

This is one of my favorite places to eat in New Orleans. I make it a point to get the combination plate with gumbo and Red Beans and rice. They are as good as you will find anywhere in NOLA. The atmosphere is great. We the doors open you can hear the sounds of Jackson Square. I highly recommend this to everyone.
Awesome your!  mike is one of the best story tellers we've come across!  So worth it!
Totally recommend this place. If I lived here I would probably stop in once a week. The Bloody Mary was one of the best I've had and the sandwiches were killer!!
Good coffee, lovely space, friendly employees and open at 7 am on a Sunday!  Couldn't have asked for more.

This is one of my favorite places to get coffee so I finally decided to come for breakfast after hearing great reviews and I was not impressed. I got the open egg sandwich with avocado and after a long wait it finally came out barely warm. The avocado, which I paid extra for, was unripe and completely inedible. The breakfast potatoes were good, but overall it was definitely not worth what I paid for it and I definitely would not get it again.

We had a great experience here. Nkechi, our waitress was great! & her recommendation to start with a cinnamon roll or biscuit sounded so good. We had both.  We plan on coming back the next time we are in Nashville.

Having purchased our home "used" and living here 3 years, we have encountered numerous problems (roof leaking, plumbing issues, water heater dying, etc) so we decided to do an inspection before other issues could arise.  Our search for an inspector began with suggestions from neighbors and many suggested Waypoint. After reviewing their background with the BBB, (which was an A+ rating) I contacted them for a basic 4 point inspection. Wilmer was the gentleman who came out and he was amazing (and very personable)!  Not only did he complete the inspection, but he offered very helpful hints that would be beneficial for lower insurance rates and help preserve the longevity of home.  We would highly recommend this company (and Wilmer) for either a basic inspection or if you are moving to a new home.
The food is excellent the price is kind of high but it's worth it!!! I tried the Philly cheesesteak as well as the sweet potato fries both excellent!!!! I will be back

This is a great urgent care clinic with caring staff and built to last. I need to keep writing this review it's the thing I have to do. Why go anywhere else? Expect the best and leave a thing on Yelp.

If I could give zero stars I would. Huge disappointment. 
Terrible service all around. Front desk attendant upon my arrival was rude, couldn't find a luggage cart for me to use. I asked to be away from the elevator four times and was given a room that faced the elevator. The couch had a stain as did the walls. Could hear music and people talking from the lobby all night. I love Hilton hotels and always stay at one - this was a huge let down and I will be sure to never stay at this location again. For the price go somewhere else.

The food was good (definitely on the pricier side), but the service was terrible. Probably the most hipster restaurant I've been to in Reno, but I would not recommend this place if you're trying to have an intimate date night. The music in the restaurant is super loud. 

Service: After my boyfriend and I were seated, it took the waiter at least 15 minutes to get us water. The food took a long time to come out and our main dishes came out at different times. After finishing dinner, we asked for the check and I think the waiters completely forgot about us because we had to wait another 10-15 minutes. I would expect restaurants to want to turn tables over quickly, but for some reason service was super slow. For the poor customer service and overall dining experience, three stars.

Food: Tried the crab croquet. Pretty tasty, but I don't think it warrants the high price tag. Three crab croquets for $13 is a little steep.

Also had the spicy miso ramen ($16) and the wicked fried rice with duck cracklings ($14). I'd say the ramen here is probably better than other places I've been to in Reno, but nearly double the price. The broth wasn't super rich, but presentation and little vegetables were nice. The wicked fried rice was pretty good. The cracklings definitely add texture and the duck on top was cooked well.

I went to this McDonald's for a family birthday party. My grandson wanted his 5th birthday party to be here and he loved it! We brought a cake and many family and friends and it was just great. I even brought some of my hip hop students and we preformed a routine. The only thing that made me rate my experience 4 stars was while I was doing my hip hop routine some of the employees proceeded to laugh at me and my dancers. Some even video taped me! Like can't you youngsters just let a 56 year old pop and lock with her crew?
Second time coming and it won't be the last! Everything is super delicious @stephsequeirafit

Tuna Bar is a new sushi digs in Old City, a relatively upscale neighborhood in a city flooded with mediocre sushi restaurants. I frequent laban's favorites, bubblefish being one of them and the last visit left something to be desired. The fork in the road left me with two options, Royal Izakaya or Tuna Bar, and boy am I glad I chose the latter.

The ambiance is on point, and the service is friendly and welcoming. The menu is curated beautifully, from my understanding they narrowed it down quite a bit from the other location. This means everything on the menu is guaranteed to be fantastic and FRESH.

We started with the steamed chicken dumplings which were light and steamed to perfection. The ginger salad followed with slices of avocado and wonderfully balanced ginger dressing that wasn't too sweet. And they even do spring mix, which was great considering romaine isn't the best these days. 

For our sushi selections we went with the classic dragon roll, the east roll, the j & j roll, and 4 pieces of the tasmanian salmon, which is a fattier cut of wild caught alaskan salmon. The fish absolutely melted in your mouth and highlighted the night beautifully. The dragon roll was crafted wonderfully and the rice on every selection seemed to highlight the delicate subtleties of genuinely fresh fish. The wasabi was even a notch above. I don't know what else I can say besides try it for yourself. The preparation of everything was so wonderfully thought out and you can tell they care about what they do here. Ken was also present and very humble about my compliments.

6/5

Absolutely amazing!! We made reservations but it wasn't overly crowded on a Sunday, it was a perfect chill spot. The decor is awesome and a very stylish but warm vibe. The food was phenomenal and service was great. We got the dumplings, lobster fried rice, Rick shrimp, Sindy roll, and fishtown roll. The Sindy Roll and dumplings were our favorite. Highly recommend !!!
Everything was great!!I had the fish and grits cooked perfectly,the art and ambiance was wonderful!!!The owner stopped by our table and made sure everything was perfect!!!!Loved it!!!
Their massaman beef and coconut rice are great, flavourful dishes. The beef is tender. Service is fast and friendly.
I have been coming to this salon for years. Every stylist is super qualified and fun to talk with. Rodney the owner is always around and remembers all clients names

The restaurant is located in the corner of a strip mall. I ordered fajitas steak and what I was served was the cheapest meat they could pass as steak, by no means was it close to skirt steak. One thing I didn't like for the price was the cheese selection. Mexican Restaurant should serve Mexican cheese, such as fresco or cotija. Instead they serve fajitas with kraft shredded cheddar mix ( I wouldn't even say kraft... best value brand). This food was not authentic and at best mediocre. I wouldn't recommend, but if you end up there it's not torture. I think they need to pay attention to the value of ingredients!

Great transportation company. Easy to work with. Prompt, polite, thorough, competitive pricing. My family has used every year and even when I have called last minute, they politely handle and if I have cancelled and not used, they still are extremely courteous. 
I've never met a bad driver either. Always early to pick up, cars are clean and water provided.

We came across this place as my family and I were visiting New Orleans and we were taking a walk from the hotel to the French Quarter around 11am on a Saturday. We were seated immediately and the staff were all absolutely friendly. I was not familiar with Louisiana food so I appreciated the thorough explanation given when I asked what's bayou etc. Since we were there for brunch, we had two omelettes which were both good, friend alligator, shrimp po-boy, and a bayou bowl. Everything was great except I'm a little disappointed with the alligator meat - because it was fried it tasted like chicken to me, I can't really tell I was eating alligator. I wish there were options to choose from in terms of how you want the meat cooked.

So happy my husband did some research and I didn't go somewhere else. I had a 2 chips in my windshield, 1 small but the other was rather big and when I took it to Safelite they told me there was absolutely no way it could be repaired and I would have to replace my entire windshield.  Shawn repaired my windshield that I was told would be impossible and it was about 4x cheaper than my quote from Safelite.  Very prompt on responding to my request and setting up the appointment and the whole repair took about 30 minutes or so.  Great business, trust all the 5 star reviews!

The Looking Glass is great local boutique. The majority of the store focuses on engraving and etching vases, cutting boards, wine glasses and various household items. The great thing is the engraving is more than just a monogram. The other part of the store hosts local crafts, jewelry and children's clothing.

Ate here a couple of weeks before Christmas after receiving a gift card.  I've been here a couple of times before.  Free pie Wednesday is good.  There's just a lot of restaurant choices so I don't eat here often.  We happened to be here on all you can eat chicken tenders night.  I didn't know they had that.  Anyway, my wife, son and I all got the tenders.  My wife ordered the regular, my son got chipotle and I requested the Nashville hot.  My son loved the taste of the chipotle.  My Nashville hot was okay, I just didn't like how it was soaked in sauce.  It made the breading soggy.  I should have asked for it on the side, but I didn't expect it to be like that.  I prefer Nashville hot to be more of a seasoning in the breading and not a wet sauce poured over the tenders.  I ate most of it, but some was just too soggy so I scrapped off the breading and ate the meat.  If you like very hot then O'Charley's Nashville hot really won't satisfy you.  It was spicy and had some heat but not really hot.  If you're familiar with Buffalo Wild Wings the heat level of O'Charley's "hot" would be in the range of BWW's Caribbean jerk.  The all you can eat tenders meal is a great deal.  With all of their specials throughout the week, and great coupons they mail, O'Charley's is a really good deal.  Good rolls and butter, good pie and a good deal.

We visited Johnson's Corner Farm when we were in New Jersey for Christmas 2016.  It was super cute and festive during the holiday season and tons of cute little knick knacks like Christmas signs, pillows, and dolls.  We bought a blueberry pie to take for my in laws when we were there.  That pie was DELICIOUS!  I LOVE blueberry pies generally and really enjoyed how fresh and berry-licious that pie was.  I think this farm would be a fun place to go berry picking in the summer (I went berry picking in central Jersey with friends back during summer 2012).  I would definitely visit again if I happened to be in that area.  Their pies are delish, their service was very nice, and it's just very quintessentially Jersey.

Fresh looking modern accommodations with great style. My favorite style of Marriott bar-none. Love the layout of the rooms, the desk with the privacy partition that allows for some late night work without bothering the family or simply a comfortable spot to work during the day.

Color scheme is calming, peaceful. Everything is planned out from the faucets to the drapes to be a "paring" of the style. The end result is a well coordinated modern theme with plenty of visual interest from the lobby all the way to the commode.

Now, to top it off, Lauren is just about the most friendly, accommodating person there who treats you like a "guest" rather than a "customer". Her voice actually "smiles" on the phone.

Whether I am coming to Tampa on business or to visit my daughter at USF, I stay here. Thank you for being such a great host to my travels.

I got the Stuffed Pepper, Shrimp Pasta & green beans. There was NO stuffing in the pepper. Only heavily seasoned ground beef. No shrimp in the pasta, just 3 on top. Green beans were too salty. I'll just stick to the Turkey necks. Been here several times and have only had 1 good plate.

So glad we opted for Burger Study instead of Hooters!  DELICIOUS, well planned hamburgers. We had the Prime Degree and Southern Classic. Roasted garlic-black pepper aioli with my zucchini straws could be eaten plain with a spoon. My son's chicken fingers were the best we've ever had. Caramel milkshake for dessert, we stopped back in for two more for the ride home. AJ the waiter was excellent. So friendly and knowledge. We will definitely be back again and again until we try everything on the menu. All ready recommended to friends and family. Good job, Burger Study and Thank you!

Heard about this place on a previous trip and for a dinner recommendation but didn't get around to it. Just happened to be in the area again and decided to stop in for lunch... Definitely did not disappoint! The shrimp and grits breakfast entree was spectacular! My wife had an avocado chicken wrap and they were accommodating to make it into a salad for her as well. Service was also excellent. If you've not tried this place, I would highly recommend it!

Best Apple Cider ever!
Why can nobody else make it this good? I grew up on Adrian cider, then moved to Michigan as an adult. Michigan folks are rightfully proud of their apple orchards, but their cider barely passes for apple juice! I've never found the perfect sweet/tart balance that Adrian has maintained forever. And if you can see through the cider then I don't want to drink it!
Super cool tasting room in the Funk Zone in SB. Staff is friendly, and it's a nice setting with the fireplace and some comfy chairs.

I had high hopes for this place but coming from a southern family I've been spoiled. The chicken tenders were dry, the mac & cheese was good, the herb beef was excellent, the cauliflower side was good, the green bean casserole was OK, and the cornbread was just OK. Positive: extremely fast service!

Very cute atmosphere, I thought it was a little expensive but the food was very good and the fruit seemed very fresh so it was worth it. Clean and quite comfy place. Enjoyed everything but it took a while to get food even though they weren't that busy. Staff were nice and friendly but didn't act like they had anything to do.

Oh man, where to start! The Garden Brunch Cafe is in an adorable house, with diverse art placed in each room. The service was wonderful and attentive. We had coffee, fruit tea, a salmon Benedict, and the bananas foster pancakes. Everything was superb! My husband couldn't stop talking about the coffee, and I always enjoy southern fruit tea. The salmon Benedict was comparable to any good Benedict dish, but the real star of the show was the pancakes. I'm neither a pancake person nor a banana person but we ordered this on the recommendation of a friend. I am so glad we did! The serving was huge, and I think just splitting the pancakes alone between two people would have been plenty. They were delicious! The best specialty pancakes I've ever had, for sure. We will be coming back, and bringing friends!

First time ordering from here. And we were wowed. Great pizza--the crust was excellent--wings were delicious, and a freebie order of jalapeno poppers came with. Looking forward to the next time we get delivery to try more of the pizzas.

Such a cute concept! 

Mini cupcakes with great flavor! I absolutely loved these mini cupcakes! They are prefect size, you do not feel guilty after enjoying a couple! 

Flavor variety is awesome! I loved the lemon raspberry and the espresso!

I look forward to taking some friends and our fur babies to enjoy more!

Yoon catered a dinner party for 20 people for my husband's 50th birthday. The food was fantastic, and she and her team were easy to work with. And I got to actually enjoy the party!  I would highly recommend her.
The service here is terrible. 4 rude ladies at the counter.  Simply wanted to add a driver.  Wow. What a terrible adventure

Great little coffee and healthy breakfast alternative stop.  The, albeit minimal, outdoor seating offers a gorgeous view. 
The egg sandwich was way more delicious than any scrambled egg sandwich has a right to be!
On ding is that the milk options for their many beverage exclude skim. The only dairy option is whole milk, with soy, almond and coconut the only other choices.  For someone with a lot of allergies (me) this was a problem. I can see it wouldn't be for many others, but it was a surprise for sure.

This was a very lovely and friendly hotel.  The rooms are modern and well kept.  The front desk is always friendly, and the room service wasn't half bad at all.  

I enjoyed my stay here and would gladly come back any time!
Lunch while waiting on our room.   Mediocre bar food.   We did not have alcohol.   I do not recommend the fish sandwich.   No flavor.   Understaffed for a holiday weekend
We loved this bar!!  The bartenders and drinks were great.  The bands were amazing.  We had a lot of fun here!  We will definitely be back to Layla's!

My hubby and I have lived out in the Spanish Springs area for over 20 years and started coming in when this one was opened. We used to hang on the Smokin' side as we felt more comfortable over there, the smaller vibe and the bartenders were always great.

But we started coming to the non side in the last year or so more often. We used to try over there on and off through the years but it always had kind of a strange vibe and it had such a warehouse feeling to it. We like to sit at the bar and feel welcome and comfortable, we enjoy gambling and having some food & drinks. We've finally found it started having a nicer vibe when David and Jo started working behind the bar during the evening hours which is when we frequent the place. We always get great, friendly and fast service. And we no longer feel out of place, we feel welcome. My hubby and I have gone to many, many bars through the years on our travels and local and we love meeting and getting to know our bartenders, many have become friends to us near and far. It definitely makes the difference to want to hang out and enjoy the gambling. It takes special personalities to be good bartenders and keep your business up, not just anyone can do it. We will actually choose not to go to bars on certain nights based on who is working. We don't want to spend our hard earned money if we're not going to enjoy ourselves.

This gem was ahhhhmazing! We stumbled upon this restaurant on a recent girls trip. They offer a sharable menu which we loved, leaving us the opportunity to try a few different things. We started with the Bleu Cheese Stuffed Dates. We are still talking about them, they were so good. The flavor combinations paired so well together. We then shared the Lamb sliders which were very tasty and not gamey at all. Lamb usually scares me. Three Muses did it right on these tasty guys. We also shared the Fist tacos which were also very delicious. They also offered a variety of fun cocktails. There was live music playing and the decor was very eye catching. The only downfall is they do not split checks, so bring cash if you're coming in a group. Worth the wait if you don't make a reservation. I will definitely go back the next time I visit NOLA.

I typically order the same thing every time ..with that being said I LOVE their honey chicken, miso soup, and sushi. I've never had a bad experience and the food always shows up within 20-30 minutes and tastes fresh!

The Monday through Friday happy hour is outstanding! The  menu has something for everyone - great  Chinese, burgers, steak, fish, etc.. Appetizers are awesome - spring rolls and crab Rangoon are a must-try. Virtually all food and drinks are half price from 3 to 5. A great value if you can get there early during the week.

Chick-fil-A is always pretty great. I know it's a fast food restaurant but I think this one runs exceptionally well. The employees are always super friendly and accommodating. I ordered the side salad with honey mustard dressing and the spicy chicken sandwich. When my lunch came I ditched the bun and put the chicken on the salad. Excellent decision. I still got that spicy chicken flavor but didn't get the bun laden with white flour and refined carbohydrates. Delicious lunch in a hurry. I'll be back!

After many raves from friends, I decided to visit this restaurant on my short visit to NOLA. The meal was good. I was especially impressed with the croquettes and wild rice arancini. The wine list is extensive the cocktails we ordered were great and amazing aromatic. 

Unfortunately, the hospitality really hampered the entire experience. We arrived early for our late evening reservation that was not honored- we weren't seated until 20 minutes past our reserved time. This happens sometimes, but in this instance the hostesses seemed confused and began to seat us twice before they finally seemed to get it together. Meanwhile, loitering around the hostess station, is who I can only assume was the FOH manager based on his attire. He did not acknowledge what was going on. We were one of two parties waiting, and the dining room was maybe 3/4 full. 

Once seated, in the back next to the kitchen and a large party, we were not met with a waitress until another ten minutes had passed. She seemed flustered- maybe they were understaffed for the evening? The food came out quickly and was on point. There was no manager presence whatsoever during our visit.

I was very much looking forward to this experience, but even the strong culinary team will not be enough for me to return during future stays.

This is a real deal traditional Mexican restaurant.
They have $4.50 happy hour margaritas, tasty carnitas prepared properly and a full menu of yummy dishes, pork, chicken and carne.
Definitely recommend if your in the Pinellas Park area. Tucked in next to a tiny motel/ hotel place.
Friendly staff and enough booths and tables for parties bigger than 8. Parking lot is big enough.
I'm a SoCal native who has been enjoying Mexican food for decades.

Our Taco Tuesday was brought to you by Bistro Habenero.
We had:
Carne Asada tacos with a chipotle crema
Grilled shrimp tacos
El Salvadoran Pork Tamales 
Cheese Papusas
The service is always polite and attentive.
As always we had a great meal! 
The only thing that kept it from being 5 stars was the asada was a bit dry.

This place is usually ok and I find what I want. Not a good experience today. The people here were just plain rude. I was looking in the freezer department and one of the stockers wheeled up his cart right up to me, blocking my way. Unloaded two heavy boxes, almost on my foot. I had to jump out of the way. Looked at me, made some sort of grunting noise like it was my fault and promptly wheeled away. I also later, asked a lady where the ramen was and she grunted something, kept doing what she was doing until she was finished, then reluctantly took me over to where I might find them. I didn't get what I wanted because she had no idea what I was talking about and was rude about it. The only thing nice was the cashier was friendly. I might start taking my business to the one in st. Pete only.

I was dying to try this place but ended up with take out only due to time constraints. I pray they operate a massive recycling center in the back because no free water (bottles only), combined with styrofoam everything, nearly guarantees them a spot in trash hell. Dumplings are very good but small and somewhat pricey - just 6 set me back $8. I've been told they are labor intensive to make but this seems extreme. There's no way i could bring my teens here and get them full for under $100. Again didn't stay to eat but seemed clean.

This place is legit. The food is consistently delicious and even the vegetables are cooked to perfection. I live in Philly, where there are lots of Asian options - but I go out of my way for Asian Chef. The people that work there are awesome and super friendly, the fried foods are hot and crispy, and on top of that the prices are ridiculously reasonable. You can get a huge lunch for $7! Where else is that possible, I don't even know. Seriously, if I lived around here this would be my go to. People of Mount Laurel - don't take this for granted!!
Pizza was great as well as the sandwich the wait time after placing an order to go, not so much otherwise very good!

Went for cheesesteaks and fries and they were both very delicious! All of the staff were very friendly and welcoming. The prices are super reasonable as well. For two large cheesesteaks, a large fry, and two sodas it was about $22! It's a pretty small menu, but I'm sure the other items are delicious as well. It seemed like they had a really nice beer selection as well. There is also a parking lot out back so you don't have to pay for meter parking on Rising Sun Ave. We'll definitely go back 

Update 12/30/17: We went back again and it just keeps getting better! Tried the BBQ wings and they were so amazing! Best wings we've ever had. Awesome prices too: 2 large cheesesteaks, 6 wings, fries, and a soda-$25!

Dr Matteossion and staff are so friendly, informative and treat you like a returning family member.  Fast service and ordering of glasses and contacts.  Highly recommend both their Sparks and Reno locations.

What a hidden gem this place is!!! The owner is so sweet and wrapped up our purchase because we were giving it as a white elephant gift. 
She has a very unique selection and completely reasonable prices! Go check out and support this awesome small business!

This is a review for the Christmas Eve Bonfire Tour.  Do not waste your money or your evening.  This looked so fun and different.  Unfortunately, the buses left over 45 minutes later than promised.  We arrived at the bonfires after they had been lit, even though we were promised 30 minutes to walk them before they would be lit.  We were supposed to be  back by 9, but didn't get back till after 9:45.  Try finding dinner after 10 on Christmas eve.  The tour guide on our bus was a total waste.  Really not a good use of 5 hour of our time, not to mention the more than $200.
Great restaurant. Excellent food and dessert choices. My favorite is the chicken salad croissant sandwich. Also their soups are delicious. Th Homemade biscuits with butter is also a favorite.

Very nice restaurant in the heart of downtown Boise. The menu had a nice selection and the food was delivered well without issue. Everything was fresh and flavorful, I had the beet salad and the prosciutto chicken.  The chicken was cooked perfectly and the dish blended together very well.

First time to eat at this small quaint establishment. Ate here for breakfast and had the make your own omelette with shrimp,crab, spinach and mushroom. My husband had the seafood omelette, kids had the cinnamon and vanilla pancakes with strawberry, and a egg, potatoes and sausage platter. Very good food; best grits we've tasted. I gave this place 4 stars coz the crab meat in my omelette was lacking. I tasted more shrimp than the crab.
Dr. Maria is so caring--she really took time to explain everything to me. If you have any foot problems, this is the place!

We stumbled upon this hidden gem one day while mattress shopping. I googled mattress stores in the area and this came up. And boy are we glad we stopped by! Victor was amazing at helping us find just the right mattress. I felt like Harry Potter in Ollivander's wand shop, as Victor dug through his stash looking for just the right one for us. Not only was the mattress we bought hundreds of $$ cheaper than what we would've paid anywhere else, but it is the most amazing mattress we've ever slept on. We've never slept better, and I mean that!! I highly recommend stopping by to see Victor. If he's not there, call the number on the door.

So I'm a huge fan of the food and Charro Steaks had become our go to place for visitors and fun nights out. Unfortunately they have decided  to be more of a concert venue then a restaurant. Its incredibly loud so much so the waiters can't hear you, your companions can't hear you and I needed to yell in peoples ears and we were as far away as we could get from the speakers. Although the music was nice and well done I didn't buy tickets to a show, I want to enjoy dinner and talk with my companions. I saw hardly anyone talking. As much as I love the food unless they decide to turn it down (and we did ask) we'll have to find another place.

I was really surprised to find an authentic Taiwanese restaurant in Reno on my way back home from Burning Man. You will not get your typical cheap greasy chinese food here - this is the real deal. Taiwanese food is a real delicacy. Traditionally it is salty but not too salty and has a sweet side :) I had tomato and egg over rice, dumplings, soy sauce boiled egg, oyster omelette, and salted fish. I wish I could eat here everyday! Can't wait to roll through Reno again.

We had 3 people in our group. 1 -17 year old 1-49 year old and 1 -81 year old. We all had a great time. First you walk in and in the parking garage and enterance there are 2 statues to look at. They have several nice exhibits. Dinosaur, space, outside, science, Ryan, Ann Frank and Ruby ( I think that was her name ). The exhibits had fun interactive things to do. There are restrooms on each level. The horse ride was good. I do recommend it

Just pizza has really good pizza, we order from them every weekend. I order their bake potato with cheese and bacon and talking about delicious OMG. They also have awesome subs, but tonight i order a ham & cheese (only) and when we got our food everyone elses food was good but mine. My sandwich had lettuce and mayo on it (which i didn't want on it) and on one half of it, it has little pieces of ham like someone ate it and put on the bread, and one or two pieces on it. The other half had 2 big pieces of ham on it. And it wasn't even cooked. So i called them and told them about it.When the delievery guy got here he said to toss the old one, i showed it to him and he said that wasn't even cooked. And the owner is there and he will take it back to show him. So they send me out another one and this time the ham was really sliced thin like for pizza and not much on it and alot of cheese, burnt. Bread burnt. I won't be ordering anything from them anymore. They lost my busy. Since they moved to 16th Street they went down. We pay alot of money each time we order from there EVERY WEEKEND!!!!!

I have tried many of the places in downtown St Pete so had to try this place. 
The pasta carbonara was not that good and the Cobia was over cooked. 
The Tryst drink was pretty good but 10 minutes to get a drink. They messed up on our order and service was slow. 
This may be a good place to have a drink but I will not be back for food. Probably not even for a drink either Too many other better places than here.

This is probably the blandest pizza in East Nashville. The crust has less flavor than most frozen pizzas. I gave them more than 1 Star just because they are in my neighborhood and I want them to be better than they are. I order from here about 1 once a year and that reminds me why I go other places. Their wings are good but if your looking for pizza I'd suggest going elsewhere.
Karina tended to our order and the quality of the products are extraordinary and so fresh!! Such an amazing quality fudge and such great customer service.

Our first experience at a Vietnamese restaurant and it was amazing. 

You can taste the freshness of the noodles, the vegetables and the meat. 

We are sold and will be back again.

Stunning atmosphere, great live music, friendly, knowledgeable service, great wine selection, and amazing charcuterie boards you help build and they absolutely crush. I loved this place; it's great for couples or for groups.

Even while picking out wine, cheese and meats, sometimes I'm overwhelmed by my lack of knowledge of wines, and what meats and cheeses go with it, but we were helped by a lovely member of the staff who put us at ease right away, listened to our insane food allergies, and helped bring us out one of the best meals I've ever had in New Orleans.

My hubby was craving wings. We pass here often and decided to give it a try. I tried calling 4 times to preorder, but there was no answer. We got there and were greeted by a mumbling cashier. I had to have her repeat what she was saying with each new statement. I ordered a small boneless wing combo plain, with sauce on the side. My hubby ordered a medium traditional with the sauce on the side. All the tables, except for a small one were filthy. A guy halfway bussed one table, so we sat at the only clean small table near thr front window. It was miserably cold!  We waited 17 minutes for our order, which was packed to go, even though we said we were dining in.  We, however, were happy to take it to go because it was miserable to sit there and shiver. Once we got home, (less than 2 miles away) the fries were barely warm. My husband's wings were partly covered with sauce (since when does plain mean cover some with sauce, if you want.  My boneless wings also had some covered and some plain. The fries have some fake barbecue tasting seasoning on them that ruins a perfectly good, partly warm French fry. Another establishment I won't be frequenting!

Since I was a child I've been visiting after hours pediatrics. They have always shown great professionalism and kindness to my family and now my children. I have never had any issues with transparency with the staff, wait times or anything else.

My husband recently sold a car to car max. It belonged to his father, recently deceased. We didn't need to trade it in, and weren't too excited about trying to sell it ourselves. He took it in to them one evening. They looked it over, gave him an offer that was comparable to Kelly Blue book. The next day we took in the title and the written offer. The whole experience took 20 minutes! Hassle free!
Awesome. Had the eggs Benedict. Hollandaise sauce was perfect. Don't miss this place.

Visiting New Orleans for the first time... my sister had a taste for oysters and we found this place here, so we decided to try it.... turned out to be amazing. I order oysters, crab mac and cheese, and southern greens, everything was delicious!!!!

Let's get this out of the way right now: it's pronounced "Ah-vuh" NOT "Ay-vuh" a fact that distinguishes the restaurant from the young lady it is named after.  I have been to Ava plenty of times but never wrote a review prior to now...it's time to spread the love! 

My first experience at Ava was during Creative Loafing's Restaurant Week Tampa Bay in 2015. Since then I've been to Ava several times, mostly for dinner with family and friends and sometimes for lunch. I've also visited Ava to pick up food as an UberEats delivery person.  

Having visited Ava several times, I am certain about a few loves: 

1. The ambiance. It's perfect -- lively yet romantic; trendy yet comfortable. Ava offers al fresco dining (covered outdoor seating) as well as a variety of table styles inside (from classy high tops to traditional table seating). Be sure to ask about the "Secret Dining Room" if you're in need of a reservation for at least 10 guests! 

2. The Casarecce al Pomodoro. I love to order this dish with extra ricotta and sometimes, if I'm feeling frisky, with the Nduja sausage (this is a spicy sausage which is different from the fennel sausage). 

3. The Ava House Salad. It's a bit on the pricy side at $8.00, but the ingredients (mixed greens, cucumber, radish, tomato, red onion tossed in a house Italian vinaigrette) offer the perfect explosion of flavors pre-entree.

4. Joe Maddon. He is part owner of Ava and he is former manager of the Tampa Bay Rays...so duh, he is a love.

Also, for solo diners, Ava is one restaurant that has an incredibly welcoming bar that erases all of the unnecessary shame in dining alone. Trust me, I've done it time and time again.  :)

We found a cock reach in the bathroom and trash had not been emptied. We asked for other room and they showed us two others, one that had ceiling flakes all over the bathroom counter and floor, and the other with a nasty stench. The lady showing the room said that they flakes were from the room being painted recently and didn't offer to clean it and expected to stay there. Supposedly it is under new management and they're renovating soon but I wouldn't stay there until they do. They would not offer a refund for the one night we had checked in to so we will definitely be calling corporate to complain.

We had great service, the grouper was really good and very fresh.  Wasn't crazy about the potatoes. It's very casual,  you get served on wood seafood plates, hasn't been updated since they took over from last place.  It was an older crowd there. They had  live band on Friday. A little overpriced but good food.  Key west martini was amazing.

This is by far my favorite place for amazing tacos and sunset watching in the area! High quality food, huge portions, delicious fresh fish and excellent ambience. Family friendly, also perfect for romantic occasions! Love, love, love!

This restaurant is consistent with good food, new kinds of dishes, excellent choices for vegetarians, the best coffee in town and servers who Are always friendly  and efficient. Super nice patio To bring your dog who also get excellent service. One of the best restaurants in town.

I had the worst customer service last evening. My boyfriend and I went into this gas station for some beer and waited at the counter for 10-15 minutes because they were having a shift change. There's nothing wrong with that, but the lady at the front desk didn't have to be so Snyde about it. Once he waited for so long he came back out to the car and I went in and basically yelled hello across the counter and then was finally checked out, and the lady who rang everything out was rude the whole time because she didn't care, and the other employees were laughing the whole time. Terrible, ignorant customer service

The clerk talked politely and acted rudely, but food was good.

I went there with 2 friends at 7pm on Saturday. I didn't make reservation, but there were not so much consumers waiting. In this restaurant, they have "reservation area" with booths and "non-reservation area" with a counter and small tables. The clerk led us to a very tiny table for 2 people though we were 3, then he left us there and had gone. He had unusual hospitality, but we got a another small table where we 3 could take seats at last.

We ordered two Prim Rib steaks and a roasted salmon, and a server asked us how we liked our steaks cooked. I think that their Prim Rib steak is very delicious and is better than that of Texas Loadhouse, because of not only the meat itself but also the 2 sauces.
However, anxiously, they didn't provide their bread for us. They have unusual hospitality and services.

I am going to try the restaurant again with reservation.

It literally pisses me off how fucking fantastic Three Carrots is. Like, I'm mad when I'm done eating/full, I want it for every meal of every god damn day (sometimes I do actually get it for every meal, WHY WOULDN'T YOU?!). It's not only great vegan food, it's great fucking food!

Ordered from here before they moved to the new location, so maybe the food has also changed. Ordered delivery for a few co-workers. The wait was long. In fact, a prior attempt to order from here was cancelled because the delivery time was 2 hours...we didn't even get things that were cooked, so this was confusing.

I got a salad. It was fresh enough for a deli that probably specializes in sandwiches, but the dressing was awful.  It was thick and gritty with sugar. I actually had to add a few spoonfuls of water to thin it out and dissolve the sugar. I would have actually preferred bottled dressing at that point. 

Overall, no one was impressed. Prices are decent, but the food was just average.
This place has gone downhill in cleanliness. Who wants to do their was in a dirty place?? Owner needs to get on this.

Went for the Saturday lunch buffet. Beautifully set up, lots of dishes I had never tried before. Service was ok- water guys were obsessive as in most Indian places around here and very accommodating to our two small children. Food was excellent! Well worth the few extra minutes drive!

This is a double restaurant. During the day it seems to be a brunch place and in the evening they are brazillian steak house (a la fogo de chao but cheaper). I ordered the chilaquiles for breakfast and they were really good. They came with pancakes or toast (i got the pancakes because pancakes are awesome). The decor is rustic with wood everywhere. Our server was on top of things and made sure our needs were being met. I would definitely go back.
Pitaya Bowl is amazing!! Need to branch out and try other bowls though because they all look so yummy!!

At one point in time, The Foodery was the ONLY place to go for mixed six-packs of good quality craft beer. The times, however, have changed rapidly. The Foodery has not!

This Foodery still hasn't decided whether it wants to be a bodega or a bottle shop, which in a store that small means that there's not a lot of room to walk around. Once you get more than 5 people in the store, you're literally pressed up against each other as you try to open the fridge doors. If you go before 4pm, you'll have room to shop, but the staff the works during the day don't know shit about beer, including one woman who doesn't drink beer at all. The night time staff is more on the ball.

There are literally dozens of other bottle shops now that have better selection and lower prices (Beer Heaven, Beer Love, the Bottle Shop, Pennsport Beer Boutique, the Beer Peddlers, etc.), so it's not worth it to pay the extra $5-$10 per bottle unless you're really, really lazy. It's especially galling when you consider that they own their own beer distributor, Global, but are still overcharging you.

Overall: Grassfed Missouri raised cow with homemade patties! Can you ask for more?

Ambience: This place is located in a busy corner of downtown STL. Parking is street only, just like most places in downtown. When you come inside, you'll notice, this restaurant is pretty big. You almost never need a reservation but it is good to have one for larger parties. The crowd is here everything from families to college friends to tourists.

Food: The place offers Missouri raised grass fed beef. So you know you're getting good stuff. If you're not into beef, their chicken burgers are also really good. I will say though their vegetarian patties aren't as flavorful. I have been to very few burger places that can do a good veggie patty. After all, this is a burger joint. We hope you didn't come here for veggie patty. We asked for ketchup and they had a house made version. I'll say, I'm not a fan of it. It tastes like puree than ketchup. The sauces on burgers could use some inspiration. They have the basics such as siracha, mayo, mustard, bbq... But if you really want to set your burger apart, step up your game on the sauce!

Drinks: They have a pretty nice bar with TVs, if you're looking for a place to eat by yourself. With that said their spiked shakes are pretty awesome. If you haven't, you should try their normal shakes and ice cream too!

Service: It was pretty busy when we came here, yet the service was fast. Our server cared for what we wanted and checked up on us a few times.

Price: $12-$14 for a burger with no sides is alright. You could throw fries with it and charge extra for other sides such as sweet potato fries or onion rings. Still can't complain.

Really 2.5 stars.  Arrived shortly before 1 on a Saturday to an empty hostess station and not a server in sight.  There were three tables with customers so not busy.  We waited a few minutes and the bartender saw us and seated us in the bar.  She was fairly friendly.  As stated in other reviews the chips are not complementary.  I had a craving for nachos as my meal anyway so I didn't care.  The bartender recommended the buffalo chicken nachos so that is what I ordered.  You do not want the nachos.  The tortilla chips are too thick, under salted and boring.  The toppings were quite good.  Hubby ordered the restaurant's equivalent of a pulled pork sandwich and fries.  Sad fries... too greasy so they lack crispness.  The sandwich he found to be just ok.  The pork in my opinion had great flavor.  We were underwhelmed and in a town with lots of Mexican food we will not be back.

Food is always great here. I've had one really bad experience here with the Daniel guy here, he's a very unfriendly guy and should not be working here. But the server Sofia is definitely the most friendliest server there. She's always smiling and talking to you making you feel comfortable, so always ask for Sofia.
This was an amazing restaurant. Our server Doug was very accommodating and professional. We were hungry so no time to take pictures LOL
